review_text: Guy at front is extremely rude, I know it's for comedy but he was extremely disrespectful to me and my friends.
I Didn't feel welcome.... had 2 drinks and left. Not sure if this place is meant for "us"

Came from out of town to visit. Highly disappointed. Waited several minutes to be seated. Waited at least 15 minutes for someone to come bring us water. Waited another 15 minutes and then left. Nobody took our order, nobody cared.
Very rude door man on Friday 3-1-2019. I wont be coming back.
I searched bars open until 4, as a promotion yelp. And this place closed 2.5 hours ago.
BWARE,OVER PRICED skimpy portion dinners,& rude workers at this clip joint.!!!
Great setting, horrible food. Best to have a drink in the bar and leave.

This place is garbage. Read my tip if they don't delete it. The manager and staff that scared and intimidated my kids your so lucky you didn't get a beat down. You definitely deserved it. Overall the worst food ever do yourself a favor don't go there, food poisoning at McDonald's is a better option.

I'm surprised this place has so many good reviews...but then again, not.  The whole schtick must captivate people.  It is fun your first time, it is fun/ny watching the camera screens in the bar, watching people trying to get in, but the food not only sucks - but it's ridiculously overpriced.  I've been here a handful of times from childhood to my adult life.  I will never go back unless I need to entertain a kid and this place just seems to be the answer.  You don't go here for the food.
The Safehouse is a schizophrenic's concept of an Applebee's, forged into the fabric of reality.

I want to give them the benefit of the doubt, since we happened to go on a pretty busy night, but I had a bad experience at SafeHouse. First off, I would not go here if you have any qualms at all about embarrassing yourself. I realize that's kind of the name of the game, but the challenge we did felt very awkward, host was pretty callous about it, so overall me and my partner were just uncomfortable by the end of it. When it came time to order some food, it took well over an hour to arrive. Server seemed pretty over it the entire time, which I understand, but it was nearly impossible to communicate anything. The salad I got was pretty weak, soggy lettuce etc. Maybe it was a bad night, or just simply not my thing, but I wouldn't come back. The idea and layout of the place was cool, at least.
Fun experience but the the food was not the greatest. I'm guessing most go here for the fun though. I would consider going back but only for drinks as they seemed to have a nice bar.

Food was O.K. nothing to write home about.  I went with a group of six and no one was crazy about their dinner.  We also went for a New Years event that advertised open bars, champagne toasts, etc... we never located the open bar even after asking a couple employees.  However, the decor is really neat, and is fun to explore.
Lousy food selection.  Food was served cold and was unappetizing.  Service was very slow.
boring.  Not my kind of fun.
Overrated overpriced tired

We went the 4th of July, and the place is nice but the 75% of the restaurant was empty but they ask you to wait 1.5 hrs.The server was kind of loud and the next table didnt even had a clue on the Martini's prices.She forgot the flags in the burgers, didnt bring plates even we said we will start with a salad to share..plus it was a bit hot.But the decoration and the concept is great.
Not worth going, unless your dad is in town and you've run out of things to do.
The food is bad but that is not what people go for - its the concept

Burger was nice but over done (although we ask for Medium) and a bit dry for my taste.  It looked good but not the taste.  The meat had no taste and thought it was from frozen. All I tasted was the ketchup sauce. The French fries was really good tho.
Have only been here for drinks. Great bar, ok-service, and awesome ambience. Absolutely recommended reserving a table in advance.
It's fun. Interesting to look around for all ages. But the food was only ok and over priced. Drinks were weak and over priced.

I was really excited to go here, as I thought it'd be a cool "speakeasy" type of place. From what I had found on the internet, I was expecting to have to solve a puzzle/riddle at the door. However, when we got there, it was more kitschy than I expected. The spy theme of the restaurant was a bit juvenile feeling. Also, to get inside, our group was basically instructed to dance and hug. Not much of a riddle?The food was fine and nothing to complain about there, I just couldn't get over the fact that the waitress would only refer to us as 'agents' and the check was the 'damage report'.I think this would be a fun place to take kids to, but I would recommend skipping if it's just adults.
Fun for something different, but food nothing to write home about.

Safehouse is such an awesome part of Milwaukee, if only the people that worked there treated as such.  I really hope someone comes thru soon and buys it and just puts some love back into it.  I had Louisiana Chicken which was pretty good but my husbands catfish poboy was just super fishy.
Very fun, but the food is not the greatest. Worth going once for the experience!
It's not too bad.

My kids had a great time there. Definitely a fun place & a good experience. Great tourist place. The food wasn't the greatest if your are looking for a great place to dine. But hey my daughters only eat chicken fingers & fries.keeps the kids interest going & the prices were fairly reasonable.

As a concept, this place is one-of-a-kind. It's a SPY BAR! Things are not what they seem! I saw a table with a group of people come up through the floor!!! (or did I?) It was a great experience. Unfortunately, the food was pretty standard pub fare and the drinks were mediocre at best. Great place to have a little fun, but not a food destination.

Its always a good time, fun theme and music. You wont just sit around and have a beer at this place.Too bad the food is boring and straight for Sam's Club. Service at the bar has always been a let down too.

Yeah I don't know why everyone gives 5 stars for this place. Anyways...the ambiance is really weird which is cool at first. It seems like there are a lot of little gimmicks inside this place that are worn down and no longer work. Anyways, the service is slow. The quality of the food is just a touch above what you would find in a school cafeteria. And...YEP YOU GUESSED IT...the service is SLOOOOW AS BALLS.That being said, the surroundings within the place are interesting enough for a few minutes. Until you get pissed about the slow service. Then when you get the food, you breathe a sigh of relief--until you taste it that is.Our hot wings were not very meaty, and sort of over-cooked. While ordering the waitress had asked me how I wanted my burger cooked--I gleefully said MEDIUM. This burger was more like a well done pile of poo. It was juiceless and tough. The fries were ok.The only good part of this dinner was my two martinis. At least they got the shaken and not stirred part right. Will I be back? Certainly not for the service...and certainly NOT to pay city prices for DOG FOOD.
Odd.Crappy food.
Very great food, atmosphere, and I will return soon

We ordered a Pepsi and a beer along with fried green beans/ cheese curds. Drinks is pretty good. Very interesting bar. The staff quickly addressed the issue to a satisfactory outcome. Overall a nice experience if your expectations are for a spy themed, funny time.
Get dresses up in your best Noir Inspired Garb and get ready to have some fun! Be sure to check out the Magician Bartender and ask about Birthday Surprises!
The place is always fun! The food is Ok, but the experience more than makes up for what the food may be lacking! Go be adventurous!!!
I love coming to SafeHouse! Although service is sometimes slow and it may take a while to get seated during busy hours, it is definitely worth it for the overall experience.

I wouldn't recommend this place for food, but if you're new to Milwaukee or coming in from out of town, it's a must see!  Tons of history and really cool stuff like a rotating table that goes into the other bar next door, trap floor, hidden bookshelves, secret exit and so much more!

always a fun place to meet friend and go!  There is also always something different going on and you can check out all the secret things that have around the place.  Good food and very good drinks, with a fantastic staff.
Very unique venue, so many things to see it will keep you busy exploring every inch of this place. When in Milwaukee, this is a must see.

This is a different little spot in downtown Milwaukee.  Most people have heard of it and what you need to do to get in, but if not, be sure to bring your friends or family here!  Food isn't awesome, just good, but atmosphere is fun.
Great fun!
Great place for special occasions.
A fun place to grab a drink!
A great experience, an original take on a restaurant!!
great comedy shows
What happens at the Safe House, stays at the Safe House.
Worth a stop in at least once. Plus they support Geocachers!
I really enjoyed it here, and we had soooo much fun!!
I appreciate that they had a couple of n.a. Beer options and the staff is always friendly and fun.
Great food, great atmosphere, and great service! I'll definitely be back many more times for sure!!

So yesterday my husband a couple other dad's showed up during late lunch no reservations, which I tell you is never a good idea especially when you need a table for 10! We requested ancient Orange section but the poor girl was totally full not one seat open in her section so yes of course we were disappointed but ancient Orange talk to the hostess and found us a table in Germany, thank you Agent Orange! The kids were disappointed but were extremely grateful that they were able to be seated agent orange promised that she would come by the table and see them when she had a chance. I don't know how she did it because according to my husband the place was packed but she made time for all the kids. Now you know why she's our favorite server she is a gem. We love you agent Orange! See you soon!

Took my friend here today for lunch. I had been here before she had not. She had the MOAB and I had the turkey BLT, we also did the bottomless mimosas. Had a great time,food was awesome. The place was packed but the food was out in a timely manner seeing we were not on a time sensitive mission we were okay with the way. Our spy waiter agent Alto was wonderful and agent cash and agent Rosa stepped in as backup. Had a blast!! Highly recommended for the family fun days.
Great!

I took my boyfriend here on a date here for his birthday. He loves spy stuff so it was the perfect place! Unfortunately, we went on a week day so the service wasn't as enthusiastic as it usually is and the magician bar was closed (though it said open). The menu was all spy themed and my boyfriend had a blast trying to figure out the puzzles. Of course, he didn't know the password so I had a lot of fun watching him do a silly dance to get in!
Always a great experience when I go to the Safe House.  Food was great and the service from Agent Libra was outstanding.   Will be back soon.

Agent Hawkeye is the best server in town. My irritable bowel syndrome acts up frequently, causing public accidents quite often. Agent Hawkeye made me feel very welcome as the feces slid down my pants, and took it upon himself to clean the entirety of it. Even from my leg and my shoe! He made a special effort to make eye contact with me the whole time, just to help me maintain my dignity. 10/10 service, request agent Hawkeye if you come here!

Stopped in on karaoke night with agent stitch behind the bar. Service was fast and efficient, and conversation was enjoyable. Will so come back with friends and such to show them this spot! Everyone was amazing.

It was awesome great service and our waitress "agent Libra" was a great help and a great atmosphere. I highly recommend the "Moab" for a great burger and the cook "agent Remy" was amazing at cooking the dishes for me and my family. If your on a night on the town, I highly recommend stopping at safe house you'll have a great time I promise.
Great cool underground restaurant with lots of different rooms. We had a great time with the kids here.
I haven't been there in over 15 years, but this place is a good time.
Such an awesome place.  Love watching all the things people have to do if they don't know the password.  Check this place out if you haven't!!

Always a fun time at the Safe House.  Got to sit in the booth that spins which was pretty cool.  We took our picture in the photo booth too and saw the magician.  Our servers were great and food was amazing.  Will definitely be back!

I'm so happy with the turnaround this place has made! I remember as a young child living in a small town, my parents made the exciting trip to the big city to go out with some friends.  When they returned from the SafeHouse, they were giddy and tipsy, and also confided in us children the secret password. Of course I committed it to memory.Years later I had a chance to visit, but to be honest it was a little blurry- I came away with the general impression that it was grimy and didn't smell very nice.When I heard that it was bought and being reopened, I wondered if it would be anything like my parents remembered if I got a chance to go visit again. Would the new owners gut it completely? Can't say I would have necessarily blamed them.Instead I was surprised and excited to see that they basically kept all of the original pieces, structures, themes and contraptions with some updates. They did a really nice job of cleaning it up, while somehow preserving its history.On top of that it's really family friendly now, which I love!!! Not just a place to go get wasted, but a fun and fantastic destination with excellent food as well!

The food, the service, the atmosphere - everything was amazing. I was there for a birthday party and we all had an absolutely amazing time. Our server, Agent 00Fox was a hoot and a half (definitely request him if you can!). But most definitely make sure you visit Luca at the magic bar. Absolutely amazing.
Came in December 22nd and Agent Unicorn was the bomb. 10/10 would go back

Had a very entertaining and enjoyable experience. The staff was very friendly, fun, and kept up a great atmosphere; especially our waitress Agent Buttercup! Definitely a place everyone should experience. Will be stopping in again soon!

What an amazing experience!! This is such an unusual restaurant. Who would think a restaurant with a secret entrance and exit would be so popular. Drinks were good, food is slightly above average but the experience is the reason to go. If you have never been there you have to try it.
It's a milwaukee staple. Always a great time.  Favorite drink-spy demise.  Don't forget to check out the secret exit!
This place is amazing! A great place to take friends, family and visitors. My favorite item is the cheese curds! So good!!!!! This is an experience you don't want to miss

We loooooooove The Safe House!!!! Always a great time and you can't beat the fun atmosphere.  They've changed their menu since the last time we were here and now the food matches the great time to be had! Having to give the password at the door never gets old and always makes me feel like I'm on some sort of spy mission! An oldie but goodie, The Safe House is one of my all-time favorites here in Milwaukee!
Great food; great staff!  We had so much fun. Glad we went and we will be coming back. We recommend the burgers--they were fantastic!
This place is a blast! Good food, great customer service and delicious fun drinks.

My husband and I took our Daughter here for her 21st Birthday. We wanted to take her somewhere special to celebrate. Gypsy was our waitress, she really made our Daughter's Birthday special. She was kind and considerate. She made us feel like family. He personality was out going, fun loving and heart warming. Gypsy is what makes the Safe House a Fabulous place to visit and eat. We will be bringing all our children to the Safe House for there first Drink. My Husband and I will go for our anniversary and just to enjoy the fun and friendship...

Our airport shuttle driver recommended this place.  All he said was that it would be the coolest bar I would ever visit. Lived most of my life in New York and Los Angeles so I was pretty skeptical. Ha!  I'm so glad I went.  The place is amazingly cool.  You have to have a password to get in.  Otherwise, you have to do silly things and unknowingly, everyone at the bar can see your silly antics that you're doing outside.  I had to do the hoola hoops and my friend said the alphabet backwards.  Hilarious! Inside was even crazier.  There's a bathroom door that actually leads you outside so you have to come back in and doors that lead you to nowhere or somewhere else. We are so adult like everywhere we go always minding our Ps and Qs.  It was nice to just have some clean harmless fun for a change.
Such a fun place to take out of town guests!!

The best black bean burger in Milwaukee is at the Safehouse! Also, the staff is very friendly and helpful. This is one of the most enjoyable places in Milwaukee to go. If you are looking for good drinks, good food, and a fun dose of history, check it out!
We had a fantastic time. Food was great, must see this unusual spy themed venue!
Fun place to take the family. The food is good, but the atmosphere is what makes this place somewhere to see. A great place to go if you have friends from out of town.
Fun cutesie place!

Such a shame that person had to ruin the reputation of my favorite restaurant. They probably brought the roach with themselves! Shady!!Love this place, will keep coming back. I don't believe or buy that a roach was there unless it was "planted" for a free meal.
Been there several times, so much fun, defintely bring your out of town friends.  It is a Milwaukee landmark. i
Absolutely love this place!! Coolest place around! Drinks are delicious too
Great Place but I can't tell you the password.
Must see while in Milwaukee. Really cool concept!
awesome !!!!
An amazing experience that I won't forget. I highly suggest this place.
If you don't know the password to bad.

If you're in Milwaukee, you absolutely must stop at the safe house at least once.  I am one of those evil people who never tells my friends the password - it's more fun to watch them perform to get inside, which is the custom if you don't know the password.  If you go upstairs, you can look down and watch a magician perform, or a bartender bartending, or various other things, depending on what's going on that day.  There are so many fun little things about the Safe House, it's hard to know where to start.  For example, you could call someone from the pay phone, which has a bunch of sound effects you can play, like breaking glass, tires squealing, gunshots, etc.  Most of the fun is discovering the little hidden things, so make sure to explore - there are some unexpected things you don't want to miss.  For example, try touching burt reynolds inappropriately in the ladies room for a surprise. Or you could go into the little room, close the door, flip the switch, and see what happens.  If it happens to be your birthday, let them know, they have something special for you.  Oh, and right before you leave, step into the phone booth and make sure that you have 75 cents ...
It's OK.  Music is weak.  Drinks are good.  Atmosphere is dark and relaxed.

Gorgeous pub wonderfully tasteful decor.. warm and welcoming atmosphere. Been a couple of times and both times it's been great. First time we only had drinks but we've tried their food on other occasions. Fab drinks selection, wonderful homemade food.  I'll definitely go back, the staff was efficient and polite. Convenient for a few beers when in town and want to try something new if you haven't been prior.
Thank you so much for your generosity. My friend and I really had a great time. Thank you so much see you soon!
Some of the best cocktails in town. A place of comfort and quality.

The owner seems like a real D. His replies to critical reviews on his website are nothing short of juvenile. An adult would use the reviews as a learning experience. Sad, that he instead belittles those that share their poor experience with his business. You can't please everyone and some people just live to complain. With that being said, the reviews seemed reasonable yet his replies were no where near. I've been there once and considered coming back over the weekend wit some out of town guests. I decided to go elsewhere after reading his snarky bs.

Great place with a great atmosphere and the drinks were reasonably priced. Met the owner Anthony and his wife Kristin while we were there and their hospitality was amazing! Looking forward to trying the food out once the kitchen is open.

I asked for the Sobleman but with a black bean patty because I dont eat meat. I requested that bacon not be put on the burger. It arrived with bacon which meant I could not eat it. My side order was the equivalent of cheese curds (forgot what the restaurant called them). They were burned/overcooked to the point where the cheese had dried. I also had a side of mozzarella sticks that were burned in a similar manner. There was a second burger (the  SOB) for my husband. I requested no onions and jalapenos on the burger, but the burger arrived with it. I requested mayanaise on both burgers, but neither had it.  My husband was not able to eat his burger either. This was very disappointing, particularly given that we were very hungry. It really seemed that they did not care about providing a quality meal. If there is any way for my money to be refunded, I would like my money refunded.
If you are a fan of quality meat, good service and a pleasant atmosphere then this place is NOT for you. Would not recommend.
renovation going on
I've heard a lot about this place. But anyone who thinks a 5 foot stack of bizarre shit sticking out of a bloody mary is cool, should probably just die.

This place is awful.  I have been here multiple times and the burgers are consistently bland, greasy, and overcooked.  The fries are dry and tasteless.  I tried a lunch special of theirs - $.25 wings - only to find that they were nothing more than frozen wings they had microwaved.  Also, the service is inconsistent at best.  To top it all off, it is almost perpetually crowded.  I would say something nice about this place but I have yet to find any redeeming qualities in it.I'm convinced that this restaurant's popularity is the product of some kind of collective insanity.
Overpriced grease!!!!!

Ok burgers, shark-jumping bloody mary garnishments, so-so service, attention seeking right-wing owners... As Sarah Palin once said "thanks but no thanks" (irony emphasized), I'll go to Oscars instead.

This place is OK, but not what they are all hyped up to be. Milwaukee burger company is better. I had been longing to get my hands on one of the burgers, it was okay.. I enjoyed my fries more. It being my first time there I thought the menu set up was very basic and non descriptive, it didn't list any of their drinks, had to kind of look around at others plates to see if I would get fries with my sandwich, wasn't sure if I would get lettuce and all dressing for my burger. I was with someone visually impaired so it would've been nice to have a more descriptive menu. We also ordered the cheese balls, amongst the table we discussed if it would be white cheese or cheddar but it was pepper jack (not a fan) so the cheese balls were a waste of money. I wanted Wisconsin cheese curds, but we know next time to try a different appetizer. The service was good, didn't take long for our drinks or order to be taken and they were busy! Only other downfall is the size of the restaurant I wasn't comfortable, not a lot of seating options, it was noisy because everyone is so close together will try a different location next time to see if there is more room.

These are not good burgers. I went here with a foodie and was told the burgers are amazing. I was super disappointed. I try not to indulge too often in a burger, so when I do I want a thick, juicy, grilled piece of meat to sink my teeth into. What I got reminded me of an old-school, precooked, thin gray patty that had been soaking in a vat of grease. It had absolutely no flavor. There was no reason to even request medium rare because I don't think they even bother. My foodie was diving into his burger like it was crack!? I figured out why. He had picked out one that was slathered in jalapeños and other goodies which after tasting his, really did improve upon the grade school cafeteria meat we were eating. Still if I'm going to indulge in a burger, I'd rather eat a better quality meat. I gave them two stars because I haven't tried much more of the menu and I like the atmosphere of the place. Also the fried pickles were actually pretty tasty. Maybe I went on an off night?
A solid burger, err umm, I mean bun. The burger itself was kinda lame, but the Great Harvest bun was darn good.
Decent burgers, not the best not the worst.
burgers are oka little over hypedparking is difficultservice is freindly

This is a good business stop it's a good one stop to have. The bloody Mary's a doer quite extravagant and picture worthy. However other bloody Mary's or just a bottled mix but they add two so it's unfortunate that a homemade custom drink every time. I had a burger here the other day and it was a normal Sobelman's burgers so I wasn't a great and fantastic however wasn't bad they have a good price point at the $8-9 range. A must stop for anybody visiting Milwaukee but again that should not be listed as one of the best burgers in the city.
Great service! You can tell the people have a lot of fun working there. The burgers are more than amazing.
No complaints about my xperience here. Not the best burger ever, but far from the worst. I could do without the frozen burger patty though. I'd go back with friends if they wanted to.
Good Burgers and great service. Pretty busy on a Saturday evening and good crowd mix.   Also good appetizers. Parking in their lot or on the street is    Good. Just a good place to eat and relax.

Hands down one of the best burgers I've ever had, and for my entree, I got the mushroom and swiss burger. I had a little bit of a kick, but I enjoyed it as well. The hamburgers were mouthwatering. Each of my family got a different one. We were all thrilled with our selections.
Went there with a big group and they were so friendly! It was a little hot in there but overall a great experience. Delicious delicious delicious.
I love this place it has one of the best burgers in town. I go there for lunch with my friends once a week and then some
Great bloody mary! I take my parents here whenever they're in town!
great burgers! decent prices. The place is packed and service is good

Burgers are always the best cooked to perfection. The staff always friendly and very helpful. the only down fall is the wait. Guess cause its suck good food there very busy. But every time i good there its an 30-45 min wait. The price of success i guess.
unbelievable Bloodys !!!!Awesome burgersGreat serviceFun people.
Have eaten here for years. Always good food.  Im glad they have become successful.
Theyre bloody marys are so gooood. and you don't need to get any extra food you can enjoy it all with your Bloody Mary.

Great burgers and bloody marys!  The St. Paul location is really nice and inviting, however, the Marquette campus location can be very convenient and fun!I've never been disappointed in what I have ordered.
Very Good Burgers! The whole experience is Milwaukee!

awesome bloody marys, great burgers and fries.  Its always busy, and although I am not claustrophobic, the restaurant is very small and the tables are small and I always just feel like I am being squeezed into my seat for the entire meal.
Great burgers! One of milwaukees best! Also try the bloodies. A meal in its self!
Fun place. Fantastic burgers. Great place for out-of-towners!
Great burgers and cold beer.  What could be better!?
Very cool and divey place! Burgers were awesome!
Had a really good lunch there with a friend recently. Great burger and pretty good service. Bartender was nice but waitress could use a little improvement.
All I can say is great burgers and great beer

Like a bun to a burger and a burger to a bun...Sobelman's burgers are AdRock's number one!Hell yyeeeaaah! Delicious burgers in a super chill bar. The only bad thing - bring back the beer bottle app holders! I don't want my cheese nuggets in a basket, yo!
Disappointing fries, excellent burger, fun atmosphere.
Great burger joint!

I've been coming to this place for a while. I cant get enough of Sobelman's burger. Its just so damn good. My fiance doesnt eat meat but she always finds something or just has a drink while I devour my burger. We got our usual waiter last time we were here and gave her a new drink. He knows she is really partial to Mojitos so he had the bartender put a new twist on it. I guess he made it with Ty Ku liqueur. She loved it. She talks about it all the time when we go out. With that said, the service is top notch.But ya, get in here and grab a Sobelman's burger. You wont regret it.

This establishment is a fantastic choice for casual dining. I tried their Caesar wrap with grilled chicken, which was good. While I'm not a connoisseur of Bloody Marys, this place is renowned for its flavorful Bloody Marys and impressive presentation. At the end of the meal, our waitress brought out some cookies, which was a pleasant surprise. Additionally, there is ample street parking available.
I've only ever ordered togo but even then, it's always so good and hot when I get home! 100 percent recommend.
Burgers are delicious, Staff is very friendly I would recommend anyone who loves burgers to try them out!
Milwaukee's BEST BURGER AND BLOODY!! Great service, great owners, and a great atmosphere.
I would die for their mozzarella sticks.
A staple in the community. A must go for bloody Mary's & burgers. A free birthday burger is a plus.
Great time and great people! You feel like a local as soon as you walk in. Oh and the food is awesome too!
So good!!!!!!!  Best burger you'll ever havein your entire life!
Have eaten here many times, always getting the same thing - the Sobelman Burger. Among the best burgers in the city! Oh, and the Bloody Mary's are good too.
Super burgers and bloody mary's!!!
They understood that I was visiting from California and they actually held a chicken for me. The Bloody Mary needed 4 people to take down. Delicious.
Great Burgers and even Better Servers.

Rick S. May be a true Yelper (whatever that means) but he's off on a few things. First the burgers are not frozen. Second you can see the kitchen from the bar and I've seen them make the chili. It sucks in this day of internet reviews that one "expert" can damage the rep. of a small local business. Yelper get a life.The food and atmoshphere here are something not to be missed. In fact I'll be there this afternoon with family from Seattle!!!
without a doubt the best burger I have ever had. A weekly stop for me.
Melanie and Dave are the best duo ever!!!! Their bloody marys are the best around!!!!!
Best burger I have ever had!  You will be back for more, I promise!
Absolutely THEE BEST BURGERS anywhere anytime!!
This is the best burger and Bloody Mary anywhere ! The rest of the good is awesome and the place is true fun !
Milwaukee's BEST burgers and Bloody Mary's. Great food, great people; great service, great atmosphere!

Best Burgers in the country.  Cheese burgers are my favorite food and I am constantly in search of the next best one.  I travel for work every week and as a result have had the opportunity to try A LOT of burgers.  That being said, this is still #1 for me in North America.
Awesome bloody marys and pork belly sandwiches. Hands down
Excellent!
Best bloody Marys in town!!! Cures any kind of sadness, or hangover
Great Burgers
My favorite burger in the Milwaukee area!
The waitress made me feel at home. Nicest staff ever.
Great burgers and great beer teemed with fabulous service!
I don't care what Food Wars says, Sobelman's is my favorite burger, hands down.
Best burger in Milwaukee.  End of Story.
Came to Milwaukee. Check out a tavern .Get a burger. Awesome.
The best burger in Milwaukee. Period.
Great ambiance. Food menu needs to be revamped. Needs more choices But, it's definitely a vibe!

Unforgettable Experience - Kudos to Juan and Blake!From the moment l walked to the patio bar, I knew it was going to be a memorable evening-and that was all thanks to the exceptional service provided by bartenders Juan and Blake. Not only were they incredibly attentive, but they consistently went above and beyond to ensure my glass was never empty and my experience was nothing short of extraordinary.Their attentiveness was truly remarkable, as they would regularly check in on me without being intrusive. It's clear that they both have a natural talent for providing top-notch customer service with their friendly demeanor and effortless ability to strike up engaging conversations.The amazing bartending duo of Juan and Blake truly made my visit to The Outsider an unforgettable experience, and I can't recommend them highly enough. Their outstanding service, coupled with their genuine personalities, make this bar a must-visit spot. I can't wait to return and enjoy another fantastic evening.

Some friends asked us to meet them here for a round of sunset drinks recently.  It was cool that evening, so we all sat around the fire and let their amazing view was over us, along with the heat from the fire and the warmth from our cocktails ;-)I've never eaten food here, but their cocktail menu is quite elaborate and more than a bit on the pricey side.  That said, the drinks we enjoyed that night were the best I've had in Milwaukee in recent memory, so they were well worth the freight.Highly recommended!!
I love this place! Great atmosphere and views of the city. We need more places like this.
Employee got coronavirus and the place refuses  to close and is covering it up. Screw this place. Time to blow it up on all social media
some of the worst service i've ever had at a bar. seriously avoid.
Great ambiance, good old fashioned. Doesn't serve ketchup. How do you not serve ketchup
drinks were pricey but food was ok
Monday Night . . . Trivia Night . . . be there!  Great cocktails and service.  Even the hot cocktails are very good.

I'm obsessed with Camp! They have THE best Old Fashioneds in the city!!! The staff is amazing and the decor is on point. Everyone is so relaxed and it's a breath of fresh air for Milwaukee. They also have daily specials that can also be found on campbarmke.com!Their summer patio is one of my favorite places to be. A must when in the Third Ward!
It's good, but service was a little slow
Cool spot to hang with friends and have drinks. Bar it's in a unique spot and could walk right past it and not even know.

The interior atmosphere is my type of place; it's old-school, unpretentious and cozy.  It was really busy and loud at 6pm on a Friday night, and the host said the wait was an hour, but the reviews online are glowing so we figured it would be worth it.  I got a burger and it was pretty mediocre, just your average bar burger and definitely not worth parking downtown and waiting an hour for.  I mean, it's OK bar fare, but nothing worth going out of your way for and not worth waiting for.  In the end, we couldn't believe we waited an hour for such average food.On the plus side, the service was very friendly and attentive, and there are some really good specials on beer. The place is cool but next time I'm craving a burger & a beer I'll go to Riverwest Filling Station and get one that's a hundred times better for only a couple bucks more and without waiting.
Overall it is an average place. Convenient and easy parking. Consistent with their menu and food is above average many times. Some days food is better than other days.
Awesome place to have a cold beer and great food. Always busy place to go to. We always go when we are in town.
Great  food!   Service was good, we  had  a  great time. Totally  recommended . !
The food was delicious and the portions were just right. Delicious food. Love the atmosphere inside. Very friendly service.
Food was good and the service was even better. It was a good choice and we would go again.

The food was good, and the portions were on the bigger side! Prices seemed to be reasonable, as well. The staff was also very kind and accommodating. There were a lot of cool decorations. We sat outside, and the atmosphere was great. It was pretty busy but well worth the wait! My waiter was a little frazzled but gave some great recommendations.

This place was def worth a visit. The Blackened Chicken Bacon Avocado is HUGE! The chicken was fantastic, and the gravy was top-notch. The seasoning was great! Can't go wrong with this food. I'll be back to have more!

Food was great I had the Angus beef sliders my friend had the ribs. Lots of food for the buck. Dining area very small felt like we were on top of each other. Lower waitress was very nice and very helpful. We loved the angry apple old fashioned. We left our birthday cake for the waitress. Only telling you this so our server knows we are talking about her! Would definitely go back.
This is a must visit for a true Milwaukee experience.
Their chicken fingers just aren't for me.  I thought they were dry, very thin, and mostly breading.  Brussel Sprouts were great.  And a nice atmosphere.

The ahi tuna steak was so good when I had it! The ambiance was extremely awesome and the service was great! I'm so glad that I found this place, In addition to this... my family absolutely loved this place which is awesome! If I like a place and my family likes it to, then we will definitely be back!
Everything was delicious!!! I will definitely go back and can't wait to try another dish!
Great atmosphere,  fast service, highly recommend!!
Yes! Have you heard? The fish fry is incredible!!! The only down side is this place fills up fast on Fridays so show up early!

My meal was simple: corned beef hash with two poached eggs. The corned beef hash, which I generally associate with tiny little pellets of corned beef, was overflowing with, giant tender pieces of perfectly seasoned corn beef. The hash browns surrounding it were perfectly crispy, and the poached eggs, also perfect.It was so good, after took my first bite, I literally turned to the guy next to me and said 'this is the most exceptional corned beef hash I've ever had in my life.' It turned out, it was the chef's Dad.

Delicious food! Bartenders and manager were extremely friendly!Honestly I wish I could leave a 5 star review because the food is SERIOUSLY delicious but our waitress on Father's Day was so condescending and rude to me and my father; I personally have never experienced anything quite like it before.
Great brunch, very kind staff. Had eggs benedict with tomato florentine. Potato pancakes delish
Great abar nice ambience,  planning to go here again with my girls soon. Seems like a really chill place where you can relax. Music is great and the food the delicious.
I always love going here!  The food is great to have before a marquette game and I love the choices of beer.  I will be returning soon!  Pretty cool bar....
Great atmosphere, server was good and attentive. Food was delicious!
This is not bar food, this is really good food in a lively bar atmosphere.

This area is amazing. Our really friendly and educational server Emily gave us some excellent pointers on some of their specialities. I enjoy the fact you could get a complete meal only from the little plate ( exchange ) menu. We had some soup, home made chips, sliders and some their great thinly chopped carrots. The service was excellent and the setting was great.
Food is always good, nice Milwaukee atmosphere.
This is a famous Milwaukee stop. Fantastic lunch. Great spot after work. Right down town.
Price is right and the food was excellent
Always has solid food and great people!  I love the burgers and miss living close to there.   I would hightly recommend it
Classic Dive. Very Milwaukee! I love it.
Great old fashion bar. We came here for a fish fry and it was really good. The brunch menu also looks great too. Will be back for sure.
We ate a breakfast meal with a large group. Food was excellent.
nice place to hang..... prices are ok and the food is good. if i will go there? yeap!!!! :)
Food was delicious, nice atmosphere. Great Friday Fish Fry.
Great bloody Mary's and brunch!
I enjoyed my burger.  Was right next to my hotel in downtown.
Food was awesome the waitress was also respectful and courteous will definitely stop back in .

Have seen the reviews on yelp for awhile and decided to check it out last night.  The bartender, Darryl was great and had great stories to share.   The food was great, had the blackened tuna with Brussel sprouts (make sure you add the glaze and pecans).  Will be back when I visit Milwaukee again

Ate a delicious dinner there last night. Well worth the 30 mins wait. The owner? / server was incredibly nice. He's obviously proud of the place, as he should be. Lovely noisy tavern style pub with a small dining room. DELICIOUS creamy mushroom & wild rice soup. Also had the jumbo shrimp with crispy Brussels sprouts. Fabulous. Best shrimp I've had in a long time & best EVER cocktail sauce. Loved it.  Am not a drinker so can't comment on that but husband enjoyed his beers. Thank you Swingin' Door! #swingin'door

The Swinging Door is a true Milwaukee bar/restaurant:  Comfortable, relaxed, unpretentious atmosphere with exceptional food and service.  Living in Milwaukee, this is my favorite place for dinner.  The ribs are outstanding and the Friday Fish Fry is the city's best.  When anyone asks for a recommendation for a place to eat, without hesitation, I direct them to The Swinging Door.
Excellent place for drinks and dinner - ours was delightful - starting with luscious mussels, strip steak and Rueben - and ending with salted Carmel Cake
. ......                                .                                     . Great Experience  .
Amazing food and service! Will be back often! Really enjoyed the atmosphere as well and the service too.

Excellent excellent place! All the food is homemade in the service is excellent! Highly recommend! Anything you try you're gonna love. Older place, very homey atmosphere. Can't recommend one item because everything is top notch.!

Wish I was a local to try more stuff off the menu!  Went with a large group with no reservations. Wait wasn't too bad, especially since we grabbed drinks at the bar while we waited.  We got split into two tables, which was not a problem for us. And let me tell you, everyone's order at our table looked delishes and that's what was said.  The bean and andouille sausage soup was on their daily special menu and boy I haven't had one ever as good as here!  We ordered the prime dip sandwich. The au juice was so tasty and hot! Dipping your sandwich into this juice just made the entire sandwich come together nicely. I cannot miss mentioning how good those home made chips were!  And with their home made blue cheese boy I could have kept eating!  Thanks to our waitress who recommended them! For dessert we shared the peanut butter dessert and what a finally to our meal!  I highly recommend this place if you are in the area.
The staff is usually very personable and attentive. The food's good, too.
"Great American comfort food in the heart of Milwaukee. Delicious burgers and fries, attentive service, and cozy atmosphere. Highly recommend!"
Literally everything that came out of the kitchen looked delicious. It never disappoints.
The food was delicious!  One of the best Reuben's in town!  Great service.  We will be back
Delicious food and fun atmosphere
Great food, love the atmosphere!
Great food and great staff. Our lunch experience was perfect. Great atmosphere and very accommodating.
Great food! Great service! The food is amazing order lunch from here any day and you will be happy.
The best people hang here.  Excellent food, fast, fresh and made with flair.   Lots of beer choices.  Hang at the bar rail and meet some of Milwaukee's finest.
Fantastic food. The best part was the bartender, Mera. Super friendly
Great food. Love to hear. One of the best eatery in town hand's down. Nice people, quiet ,cozy. Staff are always nice and friendly.
Food and drinks are great and very reasonably priced.  Might be our new favorite place for lunch!
The food is great I especially loved the grilled beets.
Dear Tourists; Do not go here.This place is MINE
Try Shelly's tuna melt. You will dream about it and be back for more....
will be back! great job keep it up?
Great staff and good food! The portions are big and the prices are very reasonable. They have a couple tables outside too.

Amazing food and service with very reasonable prices. Service was extremely knowledgeable and made the experience even better. Six of us on a work trip and we all talked about how great our meals were. Can't go wrong, try it out!!
Michael R. was amazing. Food was super delicious.  Wonderful dining experience!!
This is the best restaurant in the Milwaukee, WI area. Service is outstanding and food is excellent. You cannot go wrong in ordering any dishes
Very nice menu. Ate at the bar and had great service. Enjoyed their bread bowl, which included slices of cheese pizza. I had the mushroom lasagna, which definitely did not disappoint.
Great food, great people.  Had the Saturday steak special.   Awesome price and quality.   Will definitely return.

Was there on Sunday about 8 AM for breakfast and it was almost packed. Have been here a few time and I've noticed why. The space is clean, the customer service is exceptional, and they serve some of the best meals around. Kudos for the great work and keep up

This place is deceiving. A small gem downtown, that I never would've thought would be so good and so reasonably priced. I dismissed it for over 10 years, and boy do I regret that. They have a new regular customer.
Been there now 3 times for the Sunday brunch and every time the food and service was great. Fun servers and a really good menu. Will for sure be back.

OH MY GOSH!! My hubby and I visited this lovely restaurant, not once but TWICE while in Milwaukee!! The food was AMAZING but the service was PHENOMENAL!! Ask for Mike! He was welcoming, engaging and friendly! If this is what Milwaukee is all about we will definitely be coming back! The drinks were tasty and inexpensive! So whether you're in the mood for brunch or dinner; you can't go wrong with this place!!
Large portions, great service, great drinks ..... AND SUPER GREAT ATMOSPHERE. I love the feel of the place. Loved watching the happiness among the regulars. Super clean bathrooms.

The food is absolutely delicious. I have lived blocks from this place for years, and never really thought to go in. That has changed now and they have a loyal customer in me. Great service, great food and very affordable.

Great atmosphere, great food, and great service. I loved my time at the Swingin' Door Exchange. I went with the family and everyone was in love with it. Its worth the drive even if you live far away. I had the fish and chips (my favorite :))

Awesome place! Exceeded my already decently high expectations! Service and food, of course, are the most memorable parts. An excellent selection of drinks and food. A hard recommend to anyone in the area. Swingin' Door is awesome!

Loved the atmosphere. I went with my family and everyone absolutely loved it. The food was not only delicious, but the service was fantastic. I recommend to anyone looking for a fun night in Milwaukee.

Here from the west coast for the HD rally and stopped in here by chance for a drink today and had some fantastic Bloody Mary's and a delicious grilled cheese! Great local beers too! We'll be back next time we're in Milwaukee!!
Whenever I'm in the mood for some good old American grill and burgers I come here. Great place!
Great spot!  Great vibe! Great food! Definitely a spot to check out! Love the specials!
Had a great sandwich, fries were excellent as well. Good atmosphere, good service, overall pleasant experience.

Best  old fashioned brandy ever! Went here before a show at the pabst theater and had dinner.  The vermouth carrots are amazing. I ordered the grilled Russian it was so good roast beef, braised corned beef, coleslaw, mozzarella and cheddar cheeses on grilled marble rye the meats were tender and juicy! Will be back for sure.
Consistently some of the best food n the city,
Great atmosphere. Had the Sunday Baked Potato special and a side of their famous carrots. Mike and Kim were great!
Great place for the food, and a terrific atmosphere.  Very good service
This is one of our favorites!! They have the best carrots and it is a very cool little bar as well.
Vermouth Carrots!!!  I love all of your lunches, but man those carrots!!  Bomb!
Love this place. Great cocktails and very friendly staff.
GREAT BREAKFAST spot. 5 stars for the atmosphere and location.Wait staff was friendly and helpful.

Now here's a hidden gem downtown!  They have a wide range of options on their menu and specials to go along with it.  I ordered the Ahi Tuna appetizer for lunch and wow, so delicious.  A spicy seasoned sushi-grade tuna steak sliced & served over mixed greens, sunflower kernels, red onion and a side of mustard vinaigrette for only $10.  Not only were we impressed with the food, but the service is top notch.  Also, a very clean establishment.  I will be back with more friends and clients very soon!
Great food in a supper club-like atmosphere in Downtown Milwaukee.
Recently stopped in with some friends for a drink. Great spot and I hope this place does well. Stop by and give it a try if you can! You won't be disappointed!
Amazing food with great service. Definitely one of my favorite places in Milwaukee.
Shelly, K. C. and staff are the best.  Food is awesome!
Awesome experience.  Scott Foote and Mike Hansen are as good as you can get
Great food and great service!!
Food is amazing. Bar has great atmosphere. All good around the board.
Great food, drinks and friendly bar staff!
Love this place for drinks or dinner.  Had a great steak the other day with a soup to start.  Friendly service.  Great joint
Very nice place! Everyone was super friendly and I loved it! I definitely will be coming back again!

Can't get enough of this place, the daily specials are spot on (endless mussels?!?) and the staff are on point from the moment you walk in. Everything is just excellent, from the generous drinks pours, to the quality food and large portions. You definitely get your monies worth, perfect spot to stop by for lunch when you're downtown or a cool spot to start the night out. Definitely check it out!
Love the Pizza and atmosphere is great for happy hour!

Absolutely love this spot. Walking by you wouldn't think anything of it, but once you step in and look at the menu, you'll quickly realize this isn't your normal pub grub. The staff are on point, the drinks are solid and priced well, and the food will leave you feeling happy and full at a price point you can't beat for down town. The owners work the restaurant as well, and they take pride in what they do and make sure everyone has a quality experience start to finish. The place is packed from the moment dinner starts to the time they close, so get their early!
Fabulous Place! Went with my BF, his brother, his sister (her future hubby) and their parents, wow! We all left full and happy!
Best tasting glass of water in Milwaukee.
This place has the best food.  Everyone is very friendly and make great drinks! Always has great food specials  for dinner or breakfast.
Great food, great atmosphere, very friendly & courteous staff. Very attentive service. Will definitely be back & definitely recommend it to friends.
Great Food! Great Drinks! Great Service! Highly Recommended!
ol time atmosphere with great food! get the vermouth carrots!!
All you can mussels Wednesday night. Great tacos on Tuesday. Friendly staff. Good prices. I love this place! Milwaukee treasure.
These burgers are in my top three! Very tiny place, but amazing every time.
Great atmosphere and the staff were also great!
Charming place with great atmosphere! The staff is friendly, and the food is excellent! Located in the historic Mackie Building right below the famous Grain Exchange hall.
This was a fun place to find! The drinks were definitely interesting and original. Fun for date night!

Still the way a cocktail lounge ought to be. Haven't been here for a while, but I decided to review based on past experiences. They'll gladly make you a drink based on your own flavor experiences & requests. You can just say the fruits, flavors, aromas & whether sweet or sour, the bartender & the staff will fulfill your whims. The decor is just as refreshing as the drinks are, & the vintage old time feel it offers is timeless. MKE or Milwaukee, crash into my arms...

Not retro, simply never shifting. The bartenders work with no cocktail list for three customers, but without an approach interchangeable with the first half of that compound word. The drinks are outstanding and creative, the decor is classic, and the vibe is area friendly. The knowledge behind the pub is unmatched!
I like the dark atmosphere!

A very unique experience, truly something in between a bar and a restaurant. Environment is covered in vinyl, and feels straight out of 1970. Also probably the most diverse crowd I've seen in a Milwaukee bar, always a plus if you're looking to meet new people. For the indecisive, it's great to be able to just tell the server "something fruity," or "something with whiskey" and try new drinks!

I love everything about this place, the decor, the staff, the drinks (OMG the drinks!!) My one bit of advice is, "trust your bartender." These people are truly masters at their art. go out on a limb and try something new. tell your server or bartender what drinks/flavors you like, and have them surprise you. trust me on this one, you won't be disappointed.
I was blown away by the service and the selection was unbelievable.
Tell them any drink. It will be good
This place rules. If you haven't tried it, you must.

This intimate and charming bar offers a unique experience. Forget menus! with expert staff who guide you to the perfect custom cocktail based on your preferences. Experienced bartenders craft cocktails tailored to you.  I recently enjoyed a perfectly crafted Pornstar Martini - a delightful surprise!  I've been here a few times now, and each visit has been memorable. The intimate and cozy ambiance makes it ideal for  conversation with friends or memorable dates.
The only way I could mThe only way I could do that was if you wanted me too I could come and pick

By far one of the coolest bars in the entire country! No menu, educated and fantastic bartenders who interpret your favorite flavors and custom mix you a drink...if you don't like it, you don't have to pay for it.Great ambience, no TV's and the oldest free standing bar in America!

I had a wonderful night at Bryant's. Our cocktail waitress was incredible! I wasn't able to photograph our drinks due to the intimate lighting of the velvet lounge. That's really my only regret. Booking this package was effortless, our drinks were delicious. 10/10
I love the drinks here so much fun to see what I get next. The ordering style can take a minute more than ppl are expecting but worth it!
They are amazing! The drinks the service! Everything is top notch the ice cream drinks are to die for

Love the vintage vibe! Great place for cocktails with friends/SO. No menus here... order what you want or tell your server your favorite flavors and let them work their magic. Surprise cocktail?! Yes, please!

Consistently gets voted as one of the best bars in Milwaukee and cocktail program in the states and it's easy to see why. The inside is darker and brings you back to the era of an old cocktail lounge with literally hundreds of cocktails to choose from. The wait staff is tentative and knowledgeable as they are there to help pick the perfect cocktail for you - so you don't have to worry about the vast variety of options. All the cocktails are simply superb.
After a few drinks, I always wonder what the fish are thinking....

Came here on Saturday night and sat upstairs in the exclusive Velvet Lounge! Our group of six was celebrating a birthday and and the fun, classy atmosphere was just what we needed. When you turn thirty you don't really want to celebrate a birthday on Water street!Bryant's is the opposite of Water street. Cool vibes, a sumptuous setting, delicious drinks and amazing service. Our server Fay was obviously busy but we never once had to flag her down for more water or cocktails! Just as important, her recommendations were spot on. Kudos to the bartender as well. We will be back and in full force just as soon as another celebration requires it.

We were here in November and received some pretty poor service (from a relatively new server). This time, everything was great. We were in a hurry and Faye made sure our drinks were out quickly. She gave great recommendations based on what we wanted: 96 tears, Franks Drink, and one other I can't remember. They were all delicious. She was sweet enough to give us her card with the names of what we had (which of course I can't find now!). Bryants is back in proper form! We'll be back!

Started in the 1930s, hasn't changed since the 1970s, no menu, but they can make between 400 and 500 drinks, simpy at your request.  Similar to At Random, when At Random isn't open (which is often).  I was told that the guy who started At Random (in the late 1950s) worked at Bryant's in the early 1950s.  Very cool.  Chicago:  Why can't you have something like this?  A perfect romantic spot.
Excellent cocktails and service.
Drinks were great! Ask Max and he will give you a drink you will love based on what you like!

I absolutely love Bryant's.  It has a fun, retro atmosphere and cool, attentive bartenders who never fail to deliver a delicious treat.  You are made to feel welcomed immediately, even on a busy weekend evening.  There isn't a traditional menu.  You tell your server or bartender what flavor you're looking for and you'll get a few options to try.  The drinks are typically large and strong...especially the Brainbuster.  This is a cool place to have a few cocktails any evening.

Looking for a cool hangout for a cocktail?  Want to drink something hand crafted with the finest and freshest ingredients?  Want a cocktail that you won't find anywhere else?  Then Bryant's is for you!  From the faux leather booths to the mirrors behind the wall to the vintage Macintosh sound system Bryant's is as retro as it gets...and yet stays on the cutting edge of cocktails, along with the classics.  The bar staff is extremely knowledgeable and friendly.
Always in moderation.

It was my birthday today and I couldn't have asked for anything more. The crew members were great and sang me happy birthday over the mic! I had a great time and a birthday to remember with the awesome service!

One of the most unique bars in the city. I've never been anywhere like it before. Mini golf is fun, drinking is fun, but to be able to drink while putting together your own mini golf course then playing through it is a blast. It's a perfect date night spot and would be a great place to host a birthday party or team building event. The staff are all very professional and friendly. They really enhance the whole experience. I am excited to return with my boyfriend for some of their black lighting golf or fireball golf. Make sure to reserve a time online because spots book out fast!

Nine below is awesome!!! Went here for a date night and it was definitely a success. This place is lively, creative and all around fantastic atmosphere! The concept itself is like no other. You and your group are assigned a hole to build and once it's over you get to play all nine holes. They have all the props you could want and then some. My girlfriend and I had a blast building our hole but the best part was definitely playing a round of mini golf after. Props to all the customers and staff for a crazy fun night!

Nine Below is definitely one of a kind! I have never been to a bar that not only has mini-golf, but where you can build your own course! There are a lot of options for course items, so something for everyone! I went with a small group of friends, but I could definitely see wanting to come back for a birthday, corporate event, or bachelorette/bachelor party. The staff there is very friendly and nice, and there was also a great selection of drinks and local beer. I would recommend checking this place out next time you want to do something fun and different during your weekend!

Such a unique experience you cant find anywhere else. Building your own mini golf course is such a fun idea because it's never the same! And you get to see what everyone else builds as well, which is also a great way to meet and talk to everyone else building a course. Lots of cool and interesting cocktails, and a friendly staff. I love it because it's an activity that really doesn't require any kind of skill, so anyone can do it! The best night to come is when they have Fireball Golf, they have glow in the dark golf balls and neon lights everywhere, such a cool atmosphere.

Love the concept of this bar. The space is super cool and inviting, definitely never been to anything like it before. Building your own mini golf course is super fun, never really expected anything like this! Really loved all of the props. This is a great spot for a birthday party or just a fun night out. The drinks were pretty cheap and the staff was super friendly and encouraging.

My husband chose Nine Below for our date night. It was glow in the dark "fireball" gold that night and we really did have a blast. He's an engineer, so you know he loved building the course. We met another couple who was also out for the night kid-free and we all had a great time.

I would just like to second what Dan S. had to say. I was on that retreat he mentioned. The course building was a fantastic team-building activity. As Dan said, we had an open bar for our group. There is a decent selection of soda if you don't want to drink alcohol. It was a lot of fun building the course with my coworkers and playing each other's holes. I had a blast at Nine Below and would recommend it for any group outing. Go check it out!

Had a blast here with my group of friends. The price was spot on and the golfing was super creative. Drinks were on point and the service was fantastic. They clearly focus on that here. We all agreed - highly recommended!
Nic needs a definite attitude adjustment and I will not be returning nor will any of my friends

Don't see how you couldn't enjoy yourself here.  A variety of games all over, bar and seating areas, televisions showing classic/cult movies (but put the Brewer game on upon request), music, and outdoor areas

Last week a friend of mine invited me to this place (during a weekday).  I've driven around this place many times and never noticed it before. But I was really pleased to see how fun it was.They have a great selection of beers and ciders, some unique flavors and large variety you'll enjoy. I had the meatball pizza, and it was really flavorful, with plenty of meat, cheese, and sauce.If you are a big fan of arcade video games, you will like the selection. I wish they have more Nintendo classics.I Loved the 80's / 90's music and videos on the screens.  For some people, it can be a bit loud though. I would go back and try the Mac&Cheese pizza!

One of the best bars in the city! Not only do they have an insane amount of choices in beer, but they also have tons of classic arcade games. The tokens are very reasonably priced. We usually say we'll go for one drink and a few games and end up spending several hours there. The staff is also usually very friendly and the pizza is worth the try!
Up and down rocks. I love the beer selection. Old school gaming at its best.
Best arcade bar around! Perfect spot if you like Skeeball and enjoy some friendly competition among friends!

This place is so cool! I instantly felt like a kid again. The decor is awesome and the games were all just 1 token each. The tap list was huge and I was very impressed with the beer selection. This is a great addition to Milwaukee!
Nice!

Too many other great bars in West Allis - don't waste your time or money with this place. Owner is an absolutely jerk. Bad experience once but went back just in case it was a fluke! Not a fluke - just a crappy place with a horrible owner.

If there is one thing I can say is, DONT GO. This is the most DISGUSTINGLY disrespectful bar I have ever been. The owner is the worst human I have ever met, calling our party "white trash" after using their bar games, spending hundreds of dollars there, and treating the staff with the upmost respect. Words can't describe the disgust of this bar and the people who run it.

Owner is an absolute mental case. He's got this thing about bar stools. Not sure what his deal is but I've never been in such a toxic establishment.  His bartender apologized for his behavior but it was a scary place. We had 6 of us in this dump and he was acting insane within 10 min. It was  very early in the day and we moved a barstool and he went nuts. We left immediately to be followed by a few regulars screaming don't come back all the way to our cars. He's a racist dickhead and won't be back .

I've heard bad things about this bar in the past and saw the one star reviews, but decided to try it out anyway because of the location and general vibe of the bar. I regret it, the owner is a complete asshole and likes to go on power trips. I wouldn't support this establishment and regret giving them any of my money.

Manager or owner- not sure - clearly drunk and angry. Yelling at customers  during the afternoon- prices are good but you can go somewhere else, pay a bit more and be able to sit down and enjoy yourself

Wow we're do I start , so me and my girlfriend we just passing by and said let's stop for a beer , walked in went to the bathroom then proceeded to the bar the bartender looked at me and said I cannot serve you,  I said why , he said he can't serve me because I have face tattoos, I was in shock so right off the bat I get judged!!!!! WOW!' Speachless , my face tattoos are simple and Christian !!! You really want my input on this establishment move on ! Their should be no place for Discrimination in any establishment!!! Period!!! #facts
White Sox, aka the owner.  No idea how to manage a bar. Made stand at the bar rather than bring up a chair.
Neal does not like ice fisherman patronizing.  Thinks all of them should die while fishing. Would never return.
The bartender is the best.. so many beers.. prices can't be beat.. $3 craft beer plus beer specials!

The Drunk Uncle is great - 48 micros on tap from Milwaukee and across the country as well as an excellent specialty selection of whiskeys, tequilas, and gins.  All tap beers are $3 every day...except Sunday, when they are $2...except Saturday, when the IPAs are $1 from 2 - 8 pm.  The liquors are also a bargain.  However, this is NOT a cocktail bar.  Most cans of beer are $2 every day.  This place is very casual and it's always a good time.  Your budget will go a long way.
April is the best bartender ever!!! Our Saturday's are always the best because of her.
Nothing Wisconsin then buying $20 worth of pull tabs & free beer then $10 cases of sour beer !!!
Great beer, great service, with an awesome environment. 10/10 would recommend to anyone looking for a new spot to hang the hat.
fantastic bar, welcoming environment. owner is so cool
Absolutely amazing bar, so fun to watch Baywatch and wrestling from the 90s.

I stopped in the other night and was blown away!   I never knew a place like this existed before but I will absolutely be back.   48 beers on tap, amazing bartenders, pro wrestling on the TVs along with Baywatch and some vending machines that have to be seen to believe.

This place is a unique dive. It's clean, spacious, and ready for you and/or your group to enjoy it. $3 pints for most beers, $1 IPA deals, and $3 8oz specialties make for an EASY decision. Fun 'barcade' in the back offers a niche selection of novelty items to be enjoyed.You are able to bring in your own catering/deliver food to the bar for your event, and I imagine you just have to ask Neil if that's okay! Neil is, presumable, the drunk uncle for which this bar is named, and Neil is a great character: charismatic, welcoming, and passionate about his bar.If you're looking for your next favorite bar, look no further than The Drunk Uncle!
EXCELLENT selection to choose from WOW. Seriously fun bar with great staff, fun games at the bar and kept this girl smiling and safe. I had a blast there and will definitely be back!

These guys keep bringing it. Today they did a 28 tap line party with LakeFront brewery.  That's crazy.  They told be this is officially the biggest party the brewery has ever put together and I believe it.
