This is a great bar with an extensive selection of beers on tap for extraordinary prices. $1 IPA Saturdays are great! Plus, this is the only bar I know of cool enough to show AEW PPVs. The only complaint is that sometimes they could use an extra bartender due to the crowd. I bought a Jim Cornette action figure and a pack of Yo MTV Raps out of a vending machine here, and that's worth a 5 star rating.
Awesome place to hangout. They have tons of great beers and they play wrestling on the flat screens. Such a fun bar!

A must go...where else are you going to go that's got some amazing beers for $3. No joke, 3 bucks! Neal and his staff were very welcoming and my friends and I were able to enjoy some beers and shuffle board. Looking forward to going back again. Thanks for the good night Drunk Uncle, we'll see again soon!

Randomly stopped in at Drunk Uncle, I've never been there and lived in the area for about 5 year. Awesome selection of beers on tap! Neal, the owner, is very personable and is quick to recommend beer when you are undecided. You also can never go wrong with 48 tap lines that are $3 taps every day!
Yo. This place is legitness. Good drinks. Good service. Good people. Bartender was chill. I'm in town for my second weekend in a row. This bar beats anything on Water Street hands down.
Neal the owner was amazing. Brought a work group out and was not disappointed in the least. The beer was cold, the prices were great, and the conversation was great!!!

Great bar!  Fun atmosphere and good place to hang out with friends at! Neil does a great job of taking care of everyone in the bar and giving great customer satisfaction.  Awesome music and fun loving people in there the entire time. Best bar in Milwaukee!

There isn't enough good things to say about this bar. First and foremost the prices are incredibly cheap and free beer during packer games. The owner is a super cool guy that enjoys wrestling and will most likely buy you a shot or a beer if it's your first time there. Great artwork, clean beer lines, and the bathrooms smell good. It doesn't really seem like this Bar belongs in West Allis but I'm glad that it is!!! Also there are always movie deals where you pay $20 to get a ride to and from a movie with food and beer included for a private screening.

What a great surprise. This place has a very friendly atmosphere. It's pretty simple a corner bar that has been upgraded. The selection was good and the tap beer is on a constant rotation. The bar tender who I later discovered was the owner explained how he goes about rotating the beers. He also has shuffleboard and pinball machines adding an old school touch. Overall I will definitely return. Thanks for a friendly simple night out.
Awesome drink specials, good service. The best corner bar in the metroplex. Has great microbrews on tap and they always rotate. Not enough good things to say. Highly recommend.
Always a good experience here! Nice local bar close to my place. Would recommend to anyone. I mean, it was a bit slow earlier and I got drunk and watched Star Wars! Bartenders are awesome!
I just stopped in last Friday, and they had a huge selection of $2 craft beers, great music, and a great atmosphere. Definitely my new favorite bar in West Allis.

Favorite bar in Stallis!  My husband and I have been coming here for a while now.  Relaxed atmosphere, GREAT beer selection, and friendly people.  Owner and bartenders are attentive and down to earth.  Always a good time, whether there's 4 or 40 people in the bar.  Check out the monthly beer tastings too!
Neil,Is a amazing bartender. The best beer prices for a micro beer.. They are very cheap. Sunday funday specials rock!!! I highly recommend.. It is a great corner bar :)

So much fun! Neal; the actual Drunk Uncle,  has an awesome selection of beer.  He does bus trips for haunted houses, pro wrestling, movies and sporting events. You name it Neal will entertain the idea. He is an awesome dude and is hard working. Once you visit, you are a regular. Support local businesses and come and drink some great beer!!!

This tavern by far is the most relaxing and friendly class filled establishment in west Allis. I have frequented taverns all around the country and this by far stands "TOP DOG" against the rest. The owner and the patrons welcome you with open arms and please be ready to be either left alone or very close family. The choice is yours! Much love The Drunk Uncle!
Neil is the man.  This is the perfect townie bar for the out of towner. Immediately walking in we were greeted and given a stool.  Great beer, great people, open to all!
Cool placeBright and clean.The bartender and the patrons were a lot of fun.We'll definitely be back.
This is not your average West Allis corner bar. Very bright and clean inside.The patrons we met were a lot of fun,  Bartender was great. We'll definitely go back.
What an unexpected beer and liquor selection. Sunday open to close its $2 for everything, yep, EVERYTHING! Super friendly staff and shuffleboard seal the deal.

Went to DU's for a Packer game and it was the most amazing experience ever.  $2 everything and free Papa John's pizza during the game.  The two staff (one of which may have been the owner) were great.  Tap selection consisted mostly of Lakefront Brewery beer, aka the water of the Gods.   Overall, my friends and I have a blast.

Super friendly, relevant music on a Wednesday and I got a free shot my 2nd time here after getting chatty with a bartender. I like it here. No one goes to West Allis to club. This place is perfect for me!  cute girls and beards everywhere!!
Fun bar with reasonable prices and fantastic bartenders...Sunday funday everything is 2$....even top shelf...
Awesome bar. Owner Neil is a great dude, and very generous. Free pizza for wrestling pay per views!!

To be a 6 year veteran of drinking locally in West Allis I can say hands down this is a very comfortable entertaining atmosphere with warm welcoming company. Drinks are poured correctly at very reasonable prices with amazing drink specials throughout the week. **including 20 dollars all you can drink top shelf included on Saturdays** to say that this is like any other West Allis bar would be a complete and utter insult. This is definitely a open arms bar that supports locals and passing through idividuals. This is an upper class bar with a welcoming blue collar feel. Everyone is created equal, regulars or new comers. Hope to see you here!

Took the 12 PM brewery tour on Saturday. $10 gets you a beer & a very cool glass. The staff was awesome and very attentive. The founder gave part of our tour (awesome) and I later saw him taking out the trash. Talk about an all hands on deck operation! That was awesome to see. Our tour guide was very knowledgeable and was open to lots of questions. Many other breweries keep it light and funny, but this tour was very educational about the history of the building, how the brewery got its start, and the brewing process. I loved it! The Amber Ale was by far my favorite beer I tried. I also came back at night. The atmosphere was awesome, but service was a little slow for a place with no food, but I'm sure the kinks will be worked out soon since they are so new! I look forward to many more visits to City Lights.
Very great food! Vibe is fun and chill. Lots of space. Great beer selection. Can't complain about service.

City Lights Brewery has amazing beer, friendly staff, and a fun atmosphere. The patio is very large and is great for events, and sometimes they even have live music! I think this is one of the best breweries in Milwaukee, I would highly recommend getting a flight so you can try out a couple of different beers, some of my favorites are the Mexican ale, the amber ale, and of course the coconut porter. Check this place out!
Great beer. Great food. Fun environment. Big outdoor area!
Super dog friendly and great beers and food!

This is the textbook definition of a bro bar. They have TVs and it's nothing but toxic men who patronize and work at this bar. The bartender who always wears vests and ties was super rude to me. Plus, the old fashioned was way too sweet. The drinks aren't nearly as good here as they are at female-pwned businesses.

Great location on the river and a fun place to hang out. Really cool that it is also dog friendly. Unfortunately, the bartenders on the night I was there recently were total dicks. Every single one of them. It wasn't just just to me. It was to everyone. Do these a**holes really hate their jobs that much? It was disgusting. I'll be back once they fire the whole crew.

They make great cocktails, at a reasonable price. Get there during their happy hour, and sample from their drink menu. If you get hungry, try the food truck in the back. They usually have a fire going in the back, and that invites you to mingle with strangers. There are a few booths, a couple tables, and a small bar. I also like that they don't have a massive TV. Get your drink on at Boone & Crockett!
Fantastic interior design. Drinks were excellent. The most unique and delightful drink I've had in Milwaukee!  A welcome, sophisticated addition to the neighborhood. Please support this business!

B&C is a much improved venue over the former Gumby's.  The interior has been transformed completely and compliments the menu very well.  Unfortunately  the theme has not made it out side onto the patio.  Although a nice space, it lacks thematic intensity that delights one inside.  Hopefully the patio is  work in progress and it is not the final intention to drink your $10 summer drink on a pressure-treated picnic table accented with giant plastic bowling alley ashtrays? Regardless of the thematic disconnect between inside and out, I would highly recommend this bar.  It's something different and original, and should be supported as a great addition to KK.

I really love this place! I just popped in while visiting from out of town and was super impressed with the staff, especially since it was a packed Saturday night. There were only a couple of bartenders working the whole place, but they handled everything like pros and super quick. When I had a hard time getting an Uber, they made sure I got back to my hotel safe. Everyone was really friendly and on point. I'll definitely be back next time I'm in town, mainly because of the awesome bar staff!
Great service, yummy cocktails!
Best cocktails in the city and a great view of the Hoan Bridge. Plus there is a taco truck there!

The best spot in town for a QUALITY cocktail. They have an awesome happy hour. Love the new location and having gypsy taco right there is such a great and welcomed touch. I have never been disappointed with a stop made at Boone!

While not in search of Zelda, retrieving the Master Sword or vanquishing Ganon I like to stop by my favorite bar in the galaxy.... Boone & Crockett. Some of the things I really enjoy at this amazing locale is that, although I mainly drink Milwaukee's Blue Ribbon Award Winning Beer exclusively, they have an astounding selection of exotic and local beers alike as well as wonderful craft cocktails that rotate with each passing season. Most importantly though, they have bartenders with man-buns that usually wear tanktops, when I am out to have a good time and a few drinks this is one of the most important things I look for as far as atmosphere in a bar/pub locale. I also enjoy the fact that they do not have table service, it allows me to get that little extra bit of exercise that helps burn off the calories every time I venture from the table I am at to the bar a mere 3 to 10 feet away (depending on whether you are indoors or on the beautiful outdoor patio). No doubt John Revord and his brilliant staff of knowledgeable bartenders and bar backs created every thing this brilliant establishment includes for specific reasons, some of which are pertaining to things I mentioned above. Either way, anyone having issues with this place really should just grab a 4 pack of 16oz Steele Reserve cans and head back home to their 4 family apartment is West Allis.
went with friends as i was visiting milwaukee and experienced fatphobic behavior from the bartender.

I'm going to start this one out good, but know that's where it may not be headed.I stopped in while I was in town and got a few drinks. Their cocktails and specialty drinks are to die for. They have some really unique things. I also really liked the interior as it was cozy and welcoming. Now, the service on the other hand I can't speak so greatly about. When I first got in and seated it took easily a half hour to get a drink and that's not even on a crazy busy day. After that there was no friendly check ups or anything - I always had to flag someone down to get another drink. The bartender was a complete dick - and I use that lightly and generally wouldn't say that but he was. I attempted to up his tip from what I generally would do and that was no initiative for him either. I'd say maybe try this one out but be prepared. Not sure how I feel about the service compared to their menu.
very unique and well decorated.

This is actually the greatest goddamn tavern in Milwaukee, and perhaps the most effective pub on the North Coast. The Base occupies a spot in my liver heretofore held solely by my locals of 8 years in Champaign Urbana - the Esquire and the sadly-defunct Blind Pig - and the eternally-to-be mourned Point in Atlanta.

Love coming to this place! The atmosphere is spot on, from the decor to the lighting and even the music. They have a wide range of drinks to pick from (and just the list of all the rums they have will keep you coming back as well!). And the staff is friendly as they come will being the most professional group in the city. Can't say enough good things about this place, just go check it out for yourself already!
This place is so cool! The traditional drinks and cocktails are highly recommended. The crowd is also very lively. I will recommend this place to my workmates.
mmm. Mai Tai.  You won't regret it.
A very good dive bar without being too dirty.
Great drinks. Great Atmosphere. Reasonable prices.

GREAT DRINKS. GREAT ATMOSPHERE! This was my first tiki bar experience, and it was amazing! It was a two-minute walk from my house to a small slice of paradise.This place makes you forget about the frigid cold for a moment and it makes you feel like you're not in Wisconsin anymore.I now have high expectations now for tiki bars thanks to my experience at Foundation.

Fabulous unpretentious Tiki bar. Very subdued, romantic lighting. Wondrous hand made & detailed decor. Delicious tasting drinks. Enough said. Try it out yourself & see what I mean. It's a visit to the most authentic, unpretentious tiki bar environment I've ever witnessed. I know, I know that's a rather superlative statement.

This is the best. I freaking love this place! TIKI drinks for life!Great bartenders, great drinks, great prices, great vibes. This place has been around forever, and when I re-visit the area, it's always a top priority to visit.
My favorite bar in Milwaukee. Great beer selection, Very cool tiki bar!!!
So, so good. If you haven't gone yet, go.
LOVED IT.  I am a sucker for a Tiki bar, and Milwaukee has one of the best!

My favorite bar in Milwaukee. Delicious, potent drinks for all tastes; ask about the secret menu if one of over 30 cocktails on the regular menu doesn't tickle your fancy! Huge rum selection as well. Dark, funky ambiance, bartenders very skilled and personable. Crazy busy on weekend nights.
Best Mai Tai and tropical bar in the city.
just love this place.
Excellent Tiki Bar and you can buy the cups your drinks come in! I'm always scoping out vintage shops to find these cups, glad I have a new resource.
Simply the best... period. If you haven't been, go. And save me a spot.
Amazing drinks-amazing staff-amazing ambience!!
Best Mai Tais I've ever tasted.
Love this place, love the drinks, love the music.
The best place to goif you want to drink from analien's head cup
Best. Mai. Tai. Ever.
It's hard to fuck up a coke. Hehe. The place is cool. Go.

The security guy at The Sofie doesn't know about respect. He's so entitled to treat you poorly just because he's in charge. He grabbed me by the arm aggressively when I tried to say hello to one of my friends at the door because according him I needed to ask him for permission. So stupid.
Great bar staff that take care of you. Our first wine was terrible, the second one on the house made up for it

I am visiting for the weekend and walked in expecting to have a good time based on the atmosphere, however that was not the case. This was my first time and definitely my last. I was verbally assaulted by one of the bartenders and a few of the customers. The experience I had was so bizarre, me and my friends got mocked and shit talked for simply wanting to close our tabs after one drink. I've never seen such disrespect from an employee toward paying customers, it did not make sense and honestly blew my mind the way middle aged men were speaking about 20-something year old women. Never going back.
Poor service, rude and condescending, staff  staff would not recommend
Great place to hang out. Really good service. Bartenders are Amazing! So are the oyster tenders.
Bartender was a rude asshole. Would never go back there again.

The sign outside the door says $2 burgers, yet you have to pay for EVERY SINGLE TOPPING (Tomatoes, Cheese, Bacon, Lettuce, etc.) which ends up being A LOT more than $2! Then when friend #1 asked for an extra side of fries, one of the guys that worked there replied "No, you have to order a whole new burger to get fries" Then when friend #2 ordered a burger and declined his side of fries, friend #1 asked to have friend #2's side of fries. The guy then replied, "No, this isn't a flea market!"This is absolutely the WORSE customer service I've ever experienced and WILL NOT be returning back........ EVER!!!!

A few friends and I tried to stop in for dinner before the admirals game tonight. Unfortunately, we didn't even get to ordering because the waiter accused my 26 year old friend of having a fake ID. He said he would grab someone else to see if they would agree that it was fake, but instead came back five minutes later and said "it's fine, you can just have the beer." My friend said it was fine she'd just have water. He never came back. We sat there for about 10 minutes waiting for him to take our order, but he never did. He was checking on the other 3 tables with customers and just totally ignored us. I have no problem with a waiter who doesn't feel comfortable serving someone grabbing a manager to double check the ID; however, this man was rude and unprofessional. We went a few doors down to Buck Bradley's and had a delicious meal and great service!This is my first and only Yelp review!

Do not go here! Not family friendly. My husband was offered drugs while in the bathroom and then saw the guy who was dealing drugs be friends with all the staff. At this point I was going to talk to a manager but after seeing everyone know this individual I was turned off about the whole experience. Food was poor, service was slow. Don't bring kids here! Clientele very young!

Third time is not a charm. I was in the mood for some wings and came back to give them another chance. Was expecting a lot more after the owner had reached out to me about my first yelp review. The service is non existent and it seems that all the workers are more interested in hanging out with each other then taking care there tables. Its more like Who's in charge! I had to ask for refills every time and even had to ask for the check to escape this place. The wings are not good. I see all these yelp reviews about good wings and I get excited to eat them but they have been different all 3 times I have been here now. Must be different cooks or something. Cheese curds are good but you can get cheese cards everywhere in milwaukee. No wonder it the most lifeless bar on the street!

Had dinner last night with a standard size group, no crazy orders but everything took sooo long. No kidding, we wanted to stop by for a quick"ish" bite and it probably took over two hours from getting our drinks to receiving our bills. It wasn't even that busy.
Slow dive bar on a bar street. I had a chicken sandwich. Chicken was undercooked and service was slow. Cheese curds where also very greasy.
Owner doing his best to keep improving, will give them another shot.
The Cowboy burger was decent but they barely give you any fries.
Service was good. People were friendly. The food was the best part. I would recommend. Good bar food.
Good, solid food, wings were very good, sandwiches were good, and the gumbo is very good.

I usually don't like eating our but my perspective changed when I visited this spot. Great value for your money and your tummy. Ready and attentive staff who will sort out your needs as fast as possible. This restaurant is now my favorite eatery for sure.It was by chance that I entered into this restaurant after being I to another one whereby the staff were very rude and unprofessional. Upon entrance I was greeted with a smile followed by a complimentary snack to welcome me. They definitely brighten my day.
Very busy place, with an excellent burger!! Can't wait to go back and try other items.

Wonderful place in downtown Milwaukee. Went before a Brewers game to benefit from the free shuttle to the game. Had the Mac and cheese brat which was fantastic. Additionally tried the cheese curds. They're a must get! Sat at the bar and the service was outstanding, shuttle to and from game was simple and the motorist was wonderful. I am going to be back next time in town even if I am not hitting a baseball match.

Amazing new spot! Customer service was outstanding as well as the food was wonderful also! I 'd the cheese curds and chicken wings. Adored the reality the chicken wings were GRILLED. You do not find that everywhere and it's my favorite. I strongly recommend this place.

The best bar in Milwaukee for any and every occasion! The food is amazing and atmosphere there can't be beat! Alec is the absolute best! Be sure to ask for him when you visit! Overall, 10/10 would recommend!
Cici was awesome. Fantastic service and great food. Definitely recommending this place to friends.
5 Star Customer Service with Leigha. Great food with a great server with a beautiful smile. I'll be back for sure!

If you're in Milwaukee looking for a sports bar, look no further.  Dre and Leigha have the bar firing on all cylinders.  The service is incredible, the wings are delicious, and the environment is even more electric.  If you're on the fence, stop by and thank me later.Great job @Who's On Third staff!!!
Steve, Andre, and Alex are all amazing and the food is spectacular!!

My buddies and I are on the quest for the best buffalo wings in Milwaukee. Whos On Third is at the top of the list. Great place to stop in and catch a game or enjoy a drink with some friends. Can't wait to come back in the summer from Brewer game shuttles!

Fun place! The food is not exactly the greatest, but the drinks are excellent and they serve them at decent prices as well. All the staff are funny, friendly, and welcoming. They really make you feel right at home!
Awesome food, great bartenders, and an awesome atmosphere for sporting events. Close to the Bradley Center so you're just a a few steps away from the games!

Had a great time at Who's before and after the Keith Urban concert.  Great crowd and great service.What we ordered:  Bourbon Chicken, Cowboy Burger, Siracha Ginger Wings, Cheese Curds and Blackened Chicken Wrap.Food came out a lot quicker than I thought it would having been very busy before the show.  I thought for sure we would be waiting a while for the food so the kitchen did a great job handling the rush of food orders.  The wings were as advertised - #1 - the sauce was amazing and the wings are grilled (which is my favorite way to cook wings).  The cheese curds are to die for.  I want to eat those everyday of my life.  They are light and melt in your mouth.  Overall, a great experience on a very busy night.  I will be back very soon to check out their brunch which looks delicious as well.  If it is as well done as their dinner I have no doubts.

My husband and I stopped here to grab dinner before heading down to Summerfest on Friday 7/8/16. We received awesome service from a blonde bartender, I believe her name was Rachel? Definitely started our Friday night off right! Great service, food & always a fun atmosphere!

I went to Who's a couple Sundays ago before the Brewers game because I heard they had a shuttle to the games.  I got there and they had BRUNCH...I had no clue.  I wasn't expecting much when I ordered but I had to order it.  Glad I did because it was delicious.  I had the omelette and it was definitely one of the best I have had.  The big bonus was I got a free mimosa...you get a free mimosa with your brunch purchase.  How awesome is that!?  I am already a fan of Who's and glad they are doing brunch because that is one of my favorite meals.  Another great experience and very convenient going to the Brewers game with the shuttle.

Awesome atmosphere everyone I visit Who's on third! My usual bartender Mike knows my usual order. Their Menu has a Great Selection of eats. Especially the Wings on Thursday 50c Wing Night. They Have an Awesome drink Selection. Enough large Tvs For your sports Viewing Pleasure. I've Never Had a Bad experience at Who's on third nor Have a Witnessed anything out of the ordinary.

A five star is deserved here. Food was great , cheese curds even better. Though it was a packer game day our server ( Tatyana )handled everything like a pro, made sure we were doing ok and kept our table cleaned and ready to go for our next order of drinks.  We brought a large group of about 25 people and I can't say we were ever disappointed !  a place we will for sure come back to ..
Amazing
Customer service was outstanding..one of the better bars in Milwaukee!! Will definitely go back.

The reviews were right, best cheese curds in Milwaukee for sure.  The bartender mentioned they battered the curds in beer from the local lakefront brewery, whatever they're doing, its great.  Didn't get a chance to try out the wings, but from the advice from the couple next to me, its definitely on my list to try the next time I come in. The service was fast, the bartenders were great.  I'll definitely be back soon.
I don't know is on third.
Yummy french fries!

Great bar, extremely friend staff and owner, draws a solid crowd. Went there for happy hour and had a blast with the crowd that was there. There was a poll that I personally conducted in which 100% of people that were asked ranked their cheese curds as the best in the world.

I hosted a client happy hour on Thursday, April 24th and we had a great time. Our server was attentive, but not to the point of being annoying. We sampled some appetizers and  really liked their sriracha ginger flavored wings. Their beers were nice and cold and those who ordered drinks were also impressed.
This place is a joke. Pretty funny watching the owner try to insult people who dont leave a stellar review on here, pretty much shows what to expect in this dump. Stay away!

Having bouncers manhandle a woman, ripping her clothing off, and thrown out the door is deplorable. Not to mention I bring this information to their attention and they blocked me from commenting and left no response. I personally don't feel safe being a patron of this establishment.  The staff is horrendous. Definitely not the same "hot spot" of my youth.

F**k this place. Turned out my friend cause he has a tattoo on his neck?? WTF? The bar was empty on a Friday night and we were paying customers. Will not visit another of their establishments. Would not give any stars if I could.

Food was meh, I got the Cajun chicken wrap and tasted more ranch than anything remotely Cajun. My partner received the wrong order but was pleased none the less and the food was fast. Waitress was lovely and kind. The atmosphere is that of a loud and crowded bar, plenty of men screaming at large TVs, so that can be fun on the right day. Not sure why it's 80 degrees inside when it's a beautiful 65 degree evening in May. The most disruptive aspect was a man who was shouting at the top of his lungs and slurring his words. Very obviously over-served. At one point when directing a young waitress running the disorganized attempt at bingo, winked at her after asking her to perform the songs, which was the final straw causing us to leave. Overall, average to below average establishment made worse by this drunk patron.Edit: I'm not certain it was the owner or manager or regular but they were directing staff as though they were exceedingly familiar with everyone. The only other time we have dined here he was also present and visibly drunk as well and came up to us and greeted us.
Thank you Andy...good looking out.
A quality stop on a pub crawl with friends. Prices are pretty standard for cocktails and overall a good atmosphere.

My favourite Sunday night hangout. I confess I have not even come close to the area on a Brewers match day but I wouldn't pass it up after the welcoming manner in which I've been treated. Excellent Local Pub!
Food is good and reasonable priced. Staff is so nice and friendly. Had a great time there.

Pretty Great Sports Bar. A couple of friends and I stopped in to check this place out. I have heard about it for years, and never came in. We tried their food, which for bar food, was pretty good. Bartenders were fun, and love to shake dice. Overall had a awesome night, and we will be back. Thanks Kelly.
Fun place great service, the guys and I had a blast!
Automatically 22% tip on top of $7 beers not worth it. Will not be coming back. It is so not worth it at all

Nice space and concept, however this place is geared toward corporate events you can throw on the company card. The price for shuffleboard ($25/person/hr) is absolutely absurd- hence why it was completely dead in there on a Saturday afternoon. I've been to similar venues in Brooklyn and Chicago and those prices were cheaper! You could at least rent the board by the hour and not have to pay a crazy per person cost. I came with a group of 10, all ready to spend on drinks and various activities but most felt like they were trying to rip us off. Lower your prices and people will flock here. My fear is that it's too late as word of mouth has spread. Pricing seems to be a major miscalculation by ownership.

NorthSouth Club was fun! They opened early to accommodate our team building schedule. Shuffleboard was a blast, the staff was friendly and kind. Alyssa did a great job coordinating everything we needed for the day events.We will definitely be back for more fun in the future!

North south was an amazing place to go to and have a drink with great conversation. URI helped me multiple times at the bar giving me the best recommendations I've ever had. Eggy was a dope dude to talk to and was from the Philippines. The crew really helped out making this experience one of a kind for the first time experience. Madi was fast and efficient when I needed assistance with the activities. Lilly made me laugh endlessly cracking jokes while I waited for my drinks.

We came here to see what it was about and were pleasantly surprised. Macy was a super nice and very knowledgeable axe master who made us feel welcome and made the whole experience awesome. can't wait to come back

This was a great team celebration!  so much fun and the staff was great!  Palma was extremely friendly and helpful!  I've gone here several times and everyone has a great time whether it throwing the axe or shuffleboard.  I highly recommend it!

We held a private event at NorthSouth Club for our interns. The entire staff was great (especially Emily) and the planning process was made super easy by Alyssa. Our interns loved the shuffleboard game, as that isn't something we have in Minneapolis! Would definitely hold another event here in the future.

We had an amazing time having my daughter's bachelorette party here.  From the time we got there until the time we left, we all enjoyed the atmosphere, drinks, and snacks.  Madeline was amazing as our axe throwing instructor.  We all had flannels on and she wanted to match us so she threw on a flannel just for us.  My daughter said that she had the best time celebrating with her bridesmaids in such a fun way.  I will be keeping this in mind for future events and celebrations.

NorthSouth Club has something for everyone! Whether you pick shuffleboard or axe throwing, someone will come over with the equipment and teach you how to safely play. Both games are a ton of fun, and there's a full bar for you to take advantage of while you play! The space is huge so no matter how full it gets, it doesn't feel crowded. The staff are absolutely incredible. They are professional, hardworking, and funny. The space itself is kept quite clean, despite its massive size, making it the perfect spot to host a team building event or a birthday/bachelor party. This is a Milwaukee must-do!

NorthSouth Club is an AWESOME place to go for any type of celebration or get together. Half of the space is "backwoods" themed, where there are about 15 axe throwing lanes, while the front is more southern feeling, with a cabana area and deck shuffleboard! When my friend and I went, we did axe throwing, and it was a blast! The axe master helped my friend out so she was really able to get the hang of it! (see the "bullseye" picture!). We also loved how they have a great tap beer selection, with both Wisconsin classics (Spotted cow!) and a variety of options from local breweries. The space is huge, so perfect for any type of corporate event, and there is really something for everyone there (they even sell "make your own s'mores" trays!). Would highly recommend checking this place out!

The first thing you notice when you walk in is how HUGE the space is! It's great for hosting parties or even if its just a group of friends you have plenty of space to yourselves without feeling crowded, and you can choose between axe throwing and deck shuffleboarding, or both if you want. A huge bar with lots of fun tasty drinks, and an amazing themed interior that ranges from a beachy Miami feel for one area, to a north woodsy theme for another area. The staff are friendly and helpful, and there's so much to see inside. Such a cool concept and a fun place to learn a new activity, or improve upon your skills as an axe thrower!

Booked a reservation here for my bachelor party and had an AMAZING time! We got the entire back to ourselves, with 3 throwing lanes, a lounge area, and some super good food catered (the sliders were on point along with mac n' cheese). The ambiance of this place is excellent, our Axe Master was very knowledgeable, and the bartenders definitely knew what they were doing. Surprisingly enough the beer was pretty cheap, their draft list was choice, and they had a great selection or crafts! Kind of the whole package, this place. We had a great time and definitely recommend NorthSouth for any private event, party, or even a date night.

First time at NorthSouth and it was so much fun. The place is absolutely huge. My friends and I did axe throwing and shuffle board, both were a blast! The Axe Master, Colin, was awesome and able to quickly adjust our throws so we could stick the axe with ease. The bartenders were great and the service was fantastic. Shuffle board is super fun and makes you feel like you are in Gulf Shores or Florida, perfect for an escape from a cold Wisconsin winter night. All in all this place is awesome and we are lucky to have an entertainment bar this amazing in Milwaukee.

Booked my husband's 50th birthday party here.  It was very easy.  Their Events Coordinator walked me through the entire process.  Leading up to the party, she answered the numerous questions I had promptly and helped me choose the right package for the group I was planning on.  Catering options are available, but we decided to bring in our own food and cake.  A table for food was setup and waiting for me right next to our axe throwing lanes.  Most importantly, my husband had a lot of fun.  I will be recommending this place to all my friends.

Went here for a 50th birthday party not knowing what to expect. It was so much fun. We were a group of 16 with a wide range of ages, but everyone really enjoyed it.  The staff was very helpful. I will most likely do it again.

My wife and I stopped in recently to check this place out on a whim.   Axe throwing and shuffleboard?!   It was awesome!  Very reasonably priced drinks with friendly service.  The bar is huge and the fun decor adds to the experience.Axe throwing was a little difficult at first, but with help from our "Axe Master" I was doing better in no time.  My wife still kicked my butt, though!  Axe throwing is probably the main reason people come in, but the shuffleboard was more competitive and interactive for us.  We'll be back on a date night again soon.
Coming to NorthSouth was such a reprieve from the gloom outside. Zoe especially made my night with the recommendations and the stellar service.
Such an amazing time at NorthSouth Club with Zoe!! Great trainer and helped us have a ton of fun! Highly recommend!!
Our group had an amazing time!!! Our ax master & manager Alyssa was excellent! She was fun, knowledgeable, professional! We will definitely be back!!!

This is a great place to go with a group! The layout is absolutely great. Lots of space and lots of activities. The whole concept is something very out of the box and unique. Our guide was great and helpful. The service at the bar was prompt and friendly. Would certainly come again! Great experience!

I went to NorthSouth Club with a group of friends on Saturday night and we had a blast! Staff were super friendly and attentive.  This is a great place if you are looking to do something different in MKE.  The concept is so unique with the southern Miami vibe in combination with northern Wisconsin.  Special shout out to Jack who was really helpful with giving us tips on axe throwing.  We were all pretty nervous but he helped to put our worries at ease! Great service, great drinks, great time! Would highly recommend for a weekend activity with a group of friends.

I went to NorthSouth Club with a group of friends on Saturday night and we had a blast! Staff were super friendly and attentive.  This is a great place if you are looking to do something different in MKE.  The concept is so unique with the southern Miami vibe in combination with northern Wisconsin.  Special shout out to Jack who was really helpful with giving us tips on axe throwing.  We were all pretty nervous but he helped to put our worries at ease! Great service, great drinks, great time! Would highly recommend for a weekend activity with a group of friends.

Went here with a friend looking for something fun to do on a Friday night. This part of town is constantly getting better with great restaurants and now its got another great addition.We showed up and were greeted by friendly staff at the check in counter. The space is decorated really well with lots of great plants and some really awesome trees! There wasn't a wait to play shuffleboard (the ax throwing was totally full) so we grabbed a few drinks and headed over to our court.After a brief overview on how to play, we were left with our tangs and biscuits (for real, that's what they're called) and we had a totally enjoyable time walking up and down the court.Definitely a good time and we'll come back sometime to try the ax throwing for sure!

AWESOME! I had a great time here. I can see NorthSouth being even more popular in winter when you can escape inside for a tropical drink or bonfire punch. I came with a group of friends on a Wednesday and it was packed with tons of people throwing axes and playing shuffleboard. We did the NorthSouth Experience which meant that we could do both at once. That was a lot of fun to be able to go back and forth whenever we wanted. The staff was really friendly and the prices were reasonable, especially considering that we were there for a while. Plus the space is super cool with trees, cabanas, and taxidermy. I will definitely be back!

The drinks here are so good and come in instagram worthy glassware. The decor is so on point. Half of it is styled for the "south" with cabanas and the shuffle boards and the other half is "north" with axe throwing, taxidermy and birch trees. I always thought shuffleboard was for old retired people, but I now get it! So much fun and you don't have to be retired to enjoy it. I have come back multiple times and brought new people to shuffle and they all love it. My favorite snack is the s'mores, bc duh it's s'mores and I even bought one of their flannels and get compliments on it.

Went here on a Friday night with a group of friends and was super impressed with the entire experience. Between the cool shuffleboard courts and the axe-throwing lanes on the "north side" there was plenty to keep our group occupied. The drinks were solid and the service was good.My favorite part was the layout of the space. They did a really nice job blending the north (axes) and south (shuffleboard) concepts together. I'll definitely bring more friends back here. HIGHLY RECOMMEND!

Had a blast here last night with our company. Some of us were a little nervous about the axe throwing, but the staff was very helpful and we felt safe the whole time. Shuffleboard was a lot more fun than I expected. I would come back here with friends or for a date night any time.

Great view, but, it would be nice to have better music. They have the same entertainers all of the time!!! Get some people from Chicago or Minnisota.Please give us different and not the same.
A little bit of a time warp here. I totally could see myself here more often if it didn't feel like it needed a refresh and the group was 15 years younger. Great view though. Great view.
Went for a drink before dinner with guests in town. Great view of the city and good drinks. Good for a drink or two as they are fairly expensive. Great service!
Great drinks, great service, and a great view.
Always a excellent place to listen to music with friends.

Visited looking for some secretive, still-elusive schwag referred to on Yelp. Very happy that I visited! I shall return. Nice blues, great views and some reasonable prices for a setting like this. (We would definitely pay more at any similar place in other cities in this and other countries!)

I saw a glowing review for the Brat House in a magazine on my flight in.  I grew up in Milwaukee but have lived in Dallas for 11 years.  I was looking forward to having a brat again, so I was intrigued by the concept of the place.Overall, I was disappointed with the regular bratwurst.  I agree with previous reviewers, that not only having to ask for, but pay extra for saurkraut is ridiculous for a place that boasts to have the best brat in Milwaukee.  The brat being served on a pretzel dough bun was new too me and was really good, but the brat itself: 1) lacked size, barely bigger than a hotdog 2) lacked texture as it was like biting into a marshmellow.  The potato salad was decent.  Strangely, my order of a draft Lakefront Brewery microbrew came in two half pints, which is the norm here.They do have some interesting specials that sing to Milwaukee clientele, including Schlitz draft specials, and Jager shots with Schlitz chasers for $3.The service was good, but seeing as though the place was empty, isn't saying much.

We ended up here as we were catching a party bus to Alpine Valley and I was a bit skeptical since I think pigs are for pets, but then I saw they serve 'Beyond Sausage' and I was SO VERY HAPPY. Not only can you order a Beyond Brat, but you can put whatever toppings on it you'd like. They have so many different options that I had a hard time deciding; saurkraut and mustard, peppers/onions/cheese, jalapenos and cheese curds? Oh man, the options are endless....... Delicious! Im usually not the biggest fan of Brats, but when its done like this, how can I not?! Everything was cooked to perfection and I was completely satisfied with everything. Literally amazing. Can't believe I've lived in Milwaukee so long (literally walking distance from this place) and I just tried it this week. So friendly, fast service and was so delicious. Great place. Very lively. The service is quick and they are super friendly.  The food is very good.  The place gets busy but well worth the wait.

Received a recommendation from the local hotel that they serve the best brat in the city. So I stopped in and it was awesome. Great place to stop for a brat and beer. Back in Milwaukee for business. Frequently come to Milwaukee on business and stay at the Hyatt and visit the bars around the area. Stopped in for happy hour and had a great brat. STOPPED IN WITH A GROUP OF FRIENDS-PLACE WAS A LOT OF FUN-attentive bartenders and waitresses-food was the best brats I have ever tastes-they serve it on a pretzel bun-fabulous-SAW AD IN MAXIM AUGUST 2009-RANKED AS BEST BRATS IN THE MIDWEST

Enter the wooden sawdust strewn floors and history patched walls for a trip back through time. Share the experience with the spirits of Milwaukee's famous beer barons, their barley pops and the sausages that make Milwaukee known worldwide.The Milwaukee Brat House, Milwaukee's historical social pub is a gathering place, a watering hole, a canvas of local hero's, antiques, art, history and literature.  The mood is humble, positive, a charged battery for the thinking and working man.  The large brat grill, aged artwork, newspaper articles covering the walls, the sawdust floors, and the medicine jacket dressed waiters and bartenders help give our Brat House an atmosphere that many will consider, correctly or not, reminiscent of "Olde Milwaukee."The Brat House serves only a few local ales, served "two at a time" priced at $4.00 for both.  The sturdy 8oz beer mugs are carried 8 in each hand, soundly placed on the long wooden bar or round wooden tables throughout the pub. The wine racks are dressed with affordable, wine spectator reviewed bottles, most priced at $15.00 and served in short Italian style cylinder or favored stemless hand sized bowl shaped glasses.Their menu of Milwaukee's famous sausages cooked openly on a glorified large grill or the fine option of fresh sandwiches, bistro burgers, cheese and onion plates or sides of baked beans, thin sliced cucumber salads, potato salads, American fries or chips do create the scene for fast service, delicious food choices and comfortable socializing.  The Brat window, allows walk up customers to quickly purchase at work desk lunches, or the bar time food crowd to safely purchase an affordable Milwaukee favorite: BRATS!At the Milwaukee Brat House, everyday is a fresh start, life is wonderful, things are looking up, "we love America" and Milwaukee is the greatest city on the greatest lake in the greatest country, and if you are inclined to burst into patriotic or college fight song, They'll sing along.Be forewarned, their motto is: "Be Good, or Be Gone"

The brewery tour was a great deal when it was $7 per person. But then they raised their prices and my spouse and I stopped going. Today I went on their website to check the price since we are doing a different tour and I see that Lakefront raised their prices on the tour once again, now it's $10 per person. We thought it was a reasonable deal for two people for $14. But now since the only way to get an actual tour and not a "mini tour" which is completely useless, it's required to book online therefore there is a $2 "ticketing fee", making a tour for two $22. We refuse to pay $8 more for the same tour we once enjoyed for less. Lakefront, you have lost a lifelong customer. We used to do a tour weekly AND purchase Lakefront beer in the grocery store. Now, not only did we stop coming for tours but we also have stopped purchasing your beer. Now, some of you reading this may think that we either can't "afford" a $10 tour or we're "cheap" which couldn't be further from the truth. There is simply a point at which we refuse to pay more and this is one of those things. Lakefront has raised their prices to the point where a $10 tour is no longer a "deal".

All in all, a disappointment for such a huge "Hall". Service, as busy as they were on several occasions, never improved. Slow and inattentive... is being generous.  Fish Fry was soaked in grease, which means they were rushing the fryer and not letting the oil temp recover.  I had the baked cod on several occasions. Lakefront is a good brewery, if not a great one.  Some of their beer is just OK but they do have a knack for Lagers and Pilsners; they seem to specialize in making traditional, German-style beers.  Case in point: the Riverwest Stein, a very drinkable, classic Lager.  Their Extended Play IPA is another highlight: it's an unusually mild IPA which makes it much easier and more enjoyable to drink multiple.  However, I was disappointed in their Klisch Pilsner and the Eastside Dark, which are both fairly generic.  There's something about many of their beers that feels too safe and uninteresting.  That doesn't mean there's anything wrong with the beer - it certainly is never offensive in flavor - but it never really 'stands out' among the increasingly competitive American beer market.(Not related to the beer: Their brewery tour is quite fun; I definitely recommend it.  When I took the tour, the guide was very friendly and funny - he obviously enjoyed his job.  Also, Lakefront is fairly generous with the free pours; every tour gets you four free sample drinks and a glass.  It's fun to drink there, too, since they have a huge indoor beer hall and a beautiful bar outside on the river.)

Lakefront brews beer, gives tours, and holds Friday fish fries. THE BEER (4 stars): A nice mix of various styles, with stronger offerings such as local staple Riverwest Stein, summer weiss Wisconsinite, and amber ale Fixed Gear. Gluten-free offering New Grist not exciting. THE TOUR (4 stars): My original favorite Milwaukee-area brewery tour. Healthy samples, opportunity for group song, festive environment. Definitely most fun with a large group. THE FISH FRY (3 stars): Used to be one of the best in town, but recently the brewery took ownership of the food prep. I prefer lightly-breaded perch, but the new recipe is heavy breading with an off flavor that really masks the perch. Atmosphere is lively and polka music a lot of fun. Overall, a recommended stop for out-of-towners for the tour, but try some other local fish fries instead.

Tl:dr Rat Pack inspired cocktail lounge serving old school drinks, & ice-cream drinks. At Random is from an era that is, & should be a part of our soul.Somethings in life, love, & business should not change. Why reinvent the one thing that works best? Unless...I'll tell you more later, or if you take me out to At Random. It's an old school cocktail bar in one of the progressive neighborhoods of Milwaukee called Bay View (alongwith Riverwest, Wauwatosa, Third Ward, Fifth Ward, Walker's Point). It used to be the place to bring a date in many years ago, & it still is. Because sometimes somethings shouldn't change like that. Service: if it's your first time, then you will likely be walking in not knowing what to expect. Maybe you rarely drink like I do (I'm much more of a taster of many drinks, than drinking one entire libation). Although, I try to learn as much as I can about perfecting cocktails for friends. You may or may not order virgin drinks, if it's your first time, & trust me Like A Virgin will not be blaring loudly, it'll be something from Frank Sinatra or Nat King Cole, & really something from the Rat Pack induced goodness. You will be greeted by deep darkness, & merriment concurrently as the hostess usually merry as ever seats you in old fashioned charm. The drinks: The menu is the same. No need to improve on perfection. Grasshopper, Mai Tai... The decor: it is extremely tacky, but why would you have it any other way? It's fittingly appropriate for a time with a new sense of commercialism, speed, & futuristic thinking. There are fake plants, flowers, silver garlands, poinsetta lights, & vinyl booths, with two seater booths for a rendezvous in silence, or in shameless conversation. There has been talk that the owners want to sell this long established gem of a spot, but we can only hope that you'll employ your grandmother here. Ever visited Enoteca Maria's in Staten Island? If not, you all should. All the employees are nonnas, or Italian grandmothers. They have gone with international themed foods with a much broader concept, as they now offer "Nonnas of the World" (!) in addition to their Italian grandmothers, they now have grandmother chefs from Sri Lanka, Philippines, Japan, Algeria, Moscow, etc., etc., etc. How fabulous is this??? You can check their Nonnas of the World Calendar on their website to see which grandmother is cooking on which day. Such should be a random take over of At Random to employ our older generation an outlet to partaaaaay! The more some things change, the more At Random stays the same. And, that's endearing.

I've never seen anything like this, ever, anywhere.  You walk into the most romantic, 1950s soda shop, but 80% of the drinks are alcoholic.  No beer, no wine, no food and definitely no credit, but this is a once in a lifetime experience.  Most of the servers have probably been working there since 1950.  I had the peanut butter cup drink and my girlfriend had the cookies and cream, but they have all the traditional cocktails as well.  Call ahead to ensure they are open, as apparently, they are open 'at random."The service was fine, but don't expect much.

You have to be in the mood for something like At Random.  It is a throwback to my days of washing glasses in the Country Club Bar in the 60's when I was 14 years old.  I think that the bar, complete with the blender for the ice cream drinks is the same - and I do mean the same, as when I left it back then.  It is dark and the decorations are vintage.  I still had my hat on after coming in from the cold air outside when the little white haired hostess asked me politely, but firmly, to see about removing my hat and pointed me to a hat rack halltree in the corner to hand them on.  Are you getting the picture yet?  The Christmas music was playing softly in the background.  It was the day before Thanksgiving, so I asked teasingly if they had any Thanksgiving music.  The same hostess proceeded to sing a made up song about turkeys along with the melody of the "random" Christmas song that was playing.  The drinks are all specialty drinks with no commoners allowed to sit around just drinking beer or wine.  I had a "Golden Cadillac" and it was good.  You could not create this atmosphere on your own if you tried.  Lots of people snuggling in the corner booths of the dimly lit atmosphere wishing each other a happy holiday.

restaurant_name: J&B’s Sports Bar & Blue Ribbon Taproom
review_text: My wife and I have been going to this bar pretty much since it opened. Some of our favorite things there are the mozz stix (wrapped in wonton wraps), mac and chefs bites (wrapped in wonton wraps), the quesadilla is awesome and the fish fry is amazing. My wife particularly enjoys a "make your own burger" with the toppings of your choosing. She also likes that they ask you how you want your burger cooked (not like typical bars that cook it to be medium-well or well-done). The beer selection is great as well. Specials everyday of the week and $2 PBR's all day everyday. Very friendly staff and you can't beat the atmosphere. Party Rock Bingo and Trivia nights are pretty entertaining as well. I highly recommend this place to everybody!

This is my very first time signing up for Yelp and writing a review but I felt it was worth it.This bar drastically blew my mind tonight.I work at a bar literally a block away, and some coworkers and I walked over there to celebrate one of our friends birthdays, and boy, was I disappointed.As soon as you walk in, there was no cover, and the place is actually fantastic the way it's laid out. I work at a bar myself, and I've always been a sucker for a place that has a horse shoe bar.That being said, the place over all was a joke.I got my first drink fairly quickly and started a tab. Once finished, I ordered my second one after a 20 minute wait.It was not that busy and somehow the bartender forgot about me, so after a fairly decent wait I got his attention again and reordered.He then proceeded to refill my drink in my rocks glass over my melted ice water and not fill the glass. I was drinking double jack and cokes all night.When I asked to settle my tab immediately after he poured me that drink, the bartender asked me for the spelling of my last night three seperate times. When he finally came back with my credit card, my tab, for two double jack and cokes, was $20.Now, like I said I work at a bar a block away, that cocktail would cost you $7 over by us, not $10 each. Also, even in downtown Milwaukee (Water Street) that cocktail would not cost that much.Also, I don't mind paying for extra service and everything like that, but his lack of attention, forgetting my order, and then finally, to be hit with a tab like that after only two drinks (one and a half if you ask me), that really set me off.My first fifteen minutes there, listening to the live band (which was fabulous) and hanging out was fantastic and I was ready to recommend it to people. But in about an hours worth of time, it completely ruined itself for me.Maybe it was an off night? Or the bartender himself was having an off night.Be it as it may, I highly recommend you second guess your choice if you're looking for a bar for a date night if this is the type of service they're going to provide. There are a lot of cheaper options in this city for that, after all, it's Milwaukee.
