One of the nation's best intimate jazz venues--a cozy little slice of heaven. Always my go-to after dinner place when I am in town.
If you love live music with a fun, relaxing atmosphere then this is the place for you!

I had been looking for a decent jazz club and a friend told me about Caroline's. So I made the 180 mile round trip from Madison  and this place delivered. It was everything I had imagined a truly authentic jazz club to be. It was a wonderful and very entertaining evening. Don't ever change!
I really enjoy the live music and atmosphere.

Get your fedora and your jazz attitude on. This gem is like stepping into a time capsule in order to hear some of the best jazz the midwest has to offer. The doorman will great you and collect your five dollars (WORTH IT) and maybe take your picture for the facebook page later in the night. It's always fun to see his pictures a few days later, the bartender Michael sporting suspenders and the polite, mysterious intensity you would expect from an authentic jazz joint.  The house band takes its lead from the drummer whose skills will melt your brain. The cocktail waitresses are always sporting some kind of dress that harkens back or fits the decor (which is in good old Milwaukee style... classy and old school). There are always characters to be found in the crowd; dapper steampunkers, blues dancers, purple zuit suit-sporting jazz cats, first-daters in the know, regulars, smooth talking brass players picking up extra gigs.. the list goes on an on. I can't recommend this magical place for drinks and spectacular music enough.
You can't use MKE brewery chips at the brewery. The employees hate themselves because the management clearly sucks! 12 bucks for the worst cheese curds in town! What a joke!!!!
Negative fucking zero stars If possible. party of 8 sitting on rooftop. Bartender disappeared for over 25 minutes parties sitting next to us waiting too. Fuck this place.
The owner parked in the Tesla parking spot and being an owner I asked him to move and he said fuck you and fuck Elon musk and call the cops on me.

The people that come to this place are ignorant and racist. We had numerous racist remarks coming from other customers aimed at my boyfriend who happens to be black and was the only non-white person there at the time.
New name and owners. Old business gone from this space. I have nothing to say since I have not been there yet.
Great environment and brewing operation. Their food was great and while I'm not a huge micro brew fan the light one I had was good. And got to see Jerry Springer! Lol. Would definitely go back.

This is a super modern and fun brewery in Milwaukee! The tour is great because it includes a pint glass and unlimited beer for the duration of the tour. During nice weather, the rooftop here is a nice place to hang out and has a great view of the city. Amazing beer too! The best seasonal beer is definitely "weekend at Louis", it is a blueberry iced tea infused amber ale :)

Left feeling like a fool.  We live in the Third Ward and love the walkability to the many restaurants, bars, theaters, etc.  We try and patronize our neighbors.  So we were excited to try Fools Errand which is located in the space of one of our former favorite venues, Coquette Cafe.  We made plans to do dinner with out-of-town clients on Thursday, July 15, 2021.  On Thursday, 6/29/21, more than 2 weeks in advance, I went online and made a reservation for 5 for dinner at 7:30 p.m.  The day before our dinner, I received a text message reminding me of my reservation and asking me to confirm it.  I followed their instructions and selected "1" and received an instant reply that my reservation was confirmed.  On the evening of our reservation, I had our 3 guests over for pre-dinner cocktails outside.  Approximately 1/2 hour before we were to sit down for dinner, I received a voice mail message from Matt at their sister restaurant, Dan Dan.  Matt indicated in his voice mail that Fools Errand was closed that evening and that my reservation was cancelled.  Imagine my distress at being left high and dry at 7:00 p.m. on a Thursday evening with hungry out-of-town guests and no dinner reservation. When I called Matt back, he apologized and said that the was going to try and make it right and promised to send a gift card  so that we would try Fools Errand on another evening.  I then scrambled and was eventually able to get into a Walker's Point restaurant.  After having boasted to the clients about being able to walk to dinner, we ended up having to drive and sitting down over an hour later than planned.  That was July 15th.  Do you think that I ever received the promised gift card?  Nope.  I guess that I am the fool.
Oh my gosh this place was so delicious. The service was fantastic and the location was great. Public parking can be found just across the street. I would absolutely visit again.

I have been to the High Note Lounge many times to perform stand up comedy and stick around for karaoke after the open mic. I've normally had fun times at the High Note Lounge each time I've been there these last few years, but I was recently at the High Note Lounge, and I unfortunately had a bad experience there this time. The High Note Lounge hired new bartenders who were very unfriendly and disrespectful. When I was there recently, I did my usual stand up comedy set, and during karaoke, one of the bartenders who was also working at the door asked me to step outside. He asked me to stay away from women and touching them inappropriately, but I did not do any inappropriate touches with anyone I interacted with at the bar. All I did was make eye contact and have a friendly smile with them while dancing to some of the music. When I tried to explain that to the bartender, he did not believe me and he creeped me out when he told me that he's been observing me all night. I then went back in and sat down at the bar and stayed away from dancing. And then when it was my turn to sing another song for karaoke, I went up and sang and did what I normally do on the stage, but then after the song ended and I sat back down at the bar, another new bartender lady who was also working at the door told me that I needed to leave immediately. The bartenders misinterpreted me and told me that they thought I was making other people uncomfortable, but no one I interacted with talked to me about that directly. If they had talked to me directly and asked me to stop doing something I didn't realize I was doing, I would have listened to them. The bartender threatened me and told me that I have to leave in the next 2 minutes after I was trying to gather all my belongings and get out the door. The bartender even grabbed my jacket from my chair before I even had a chance to put it on and she forced me outside before I even put my jacket on. Rushing someone out the door like that is rude and disrespectful. I think the High Note Lounge could be better staffed by more friendly and understanding bartenders and people working at the door and people who understand other people's perspectives and not only theirs. Because of the bad experience I had at the bar that I've never had before, I unfortunately don't feel safe coming back to the High Note Lounge again. I do not recommend this bar especially if you don't want to be put in a tough situation with the bartenders like I was recently in. It is not worth it.

ZERO STARS. from out of state and the rude security guard José assumed that my friends IDs were fake. Not to mention he yanked my sister by her shirt. So uncalled for. We are all 23-25 yrs old. Refused to give IDs back until we threatened to call the cops. Didn't even bother to scan the IDs or ask for additional proof of identity. what a joke. Took our business elsewhere.

This place is horrible. The bouncers have no idea how to do their jobs. I was rejected because he thought my ID was fake just because it was from out of state and that I look younger than I am. Our friend with a FAKE ID was able to get in while me, at age 22, was not. The bouncer was very rude, uncooperative, and called me the N word as I left. Do not go to this bar!

I've been coming to this bar for 3 years!!! I never had a problem with this place until recently. The bartender over charges if you keep your card open and the karaoke dj will skip over your song for her boyfriend. I  waited 3 hours to sing my song while he sang 5 times ahead of me. I hope its not going to continue to be like this... Otherwise Im done!

Rather than prattle endlessly with a long-winded litany of whining (*), suffice to say this venue offers what one expects of a "karaoke bar": (a) alcoholic beverages for sale and (b) opportunity to sing. For my part, I'll patronize Amelia's on Layton in the future, which I vastly prefer for the karaoke experience, pub experience, dining experience and service experience. fyi: Bring earplugs to protected your hearing, as you would to any amplified venue. (*) Also bring some carry-in fooding, to protect against munchies.Still, most nights of the week, one can sing, one can drink, and one can easily find parking.(*)See harborfreight.com/50-pai…or walgreens.com/store/c/ma…

This morning lace is great. I really like the song selection, and the bartenders are fantastic. For my first time in Milwaukee, this is the best karaoke place. I definitely suggest this if it is the first time for you. The drinks are cheap, good and fun for downtown Milwaukee.

Always a pleasure to come to - Staff is always friendly (on multiple occasions greeting me at the door)  and more than willing to adjust to the needs of the customers and the drinks are inexpensive but great tasting. The premises are always kept clean.I have gone to multiple birthday parties on site at this location and have never been more pleased with the results. Keep up the good work and this location will continue to be one of my favorite spots in Milwaukee.

Awesome selection of Karaoke @ the DJ's are oh so handsome! Looking for a Mojito? This isn't the bar you're looking for. Looking for one of the best places to party, sing & dance the night away? THIS IS YOUR BAR!
Highly recommend this bar! The owner, bartenders, and karaoke DJs create such a fun atmosphere and they are incredibly hospitable. Bring a group to enjoy Friday night karaoke and get ready to party!
Generous and hospitable. A real gem. Don't be fooled by the generic karaoke bar look. This bar is something special.  It's the people that make it special.

This was my first visit to Third Space. We took a tour, which was led by the co-found/Brewmaster Kevin. He was incredibly passionate and I really enjoyed the tour. Some other brewery tours are entertainment 1st, education 2nd (which is also awesome!) but this tour was VERY educational and I loved learning about how they got their start. 2 beers and a glass for $10 isn't bad either!  I really enjoyed the Java Blanca and Happy Place. That's Gold was my least favorite of the taps I tried. The beer garden is going to be awesome in the summer--can't wait to enjoy it soon! Will definitely be back.

This place is a joke! We made a reservation online, they charged our credit card, drove 25 min here with our 2 kids, to find out they "lost" our reservation. They can't even refund our money.  Beware!!!!

Omg! Had the best sandwich ever. Highly recommend the brisket sandwich and the chicken blt. Our server Jeff was very attentive as well. Dont let me forget they have live music and a beautiful patio!!! Great job thirsty duck for a great night
I wouldn't even give this place one star. Long story short the staff is extremely disrespectful. Take your business elsewhere!
over rated. largelyyyy. Go drink somewhere with cheaper drinks and nicer bartenders.
YA come hang out
Great Yelp event! Minutes from everything in downtown! Couldn't be a better location to wind down and enjoy the city! Come visit our Mixologists!

No menu, no prices so do what we didn't and ask how much everything is. Two mushroom caps with crab, $64!!  Two fish dinners (Walleye with vegetables) was $66. So Friday fish dinner at the sports bar was $130. Highlight was good service from waitress.  One and done for us.
This place is more bar than restaurant. Need less emphasis on the restaurant and promote it more as a bar
Racist... If you are a person of color DO NOT eat here. If you don't believe me go and find out.

Let's see - Charged 3 different prices for the same drink in one night by the same bartender. Owner is a real jerk.The manager is a drunk.Most of the cooks are messed up drinking or drugging on the job.Should I say more ???

After looking into yelp reviews decided to take a chance with the 4th base bar. A bar, yes that is what it is or so it looked, and not a clean one. Very run down but stayed anyway to try their food. No menu feels awkward to say the least so what we ended with were just two burgers and fries. 10 bucks a piece was the cost plus two beers. Pretty standard for the area. Too many great food places in the area so probably will not be returning.

Talk about something different! I asked about a menu, and they didn't have one. I walked over to the deli case, and then it all made sense, and fresh vegetables, seafood, huge steaks. Everything looked great! I tried the salmon, and I got a huge piece. I tried it with some steamed and sautéed vegetables, along with rice that they make in-house. It was amazing. Great Flavors! And a ton of food.
What a great concept!! What an awesome chef!!! Great atmosphere and service!!!Definitely be back!!!

I came in earlier today for the first time and it was beyond my expectations! I get nervous going to bars but Jules made me feel so comfortable and was the best part of my experience here!!! She's deserves it all and more. I will definitely be coming back because of Jules!
Food is delicious and the service and employees are always fun to be around. And there's a lot of old sports memorabilia all over the walls and ceilings that are cool to look at too.
The atmosphere is great a little tight but welcoming service was wonderful food over the top
This little bar is the best of the best of bar restaurants. If ever in Milwaukee stop by ! Friendliest bar ever!
Really any concoction your hungry for Antonio will make it delicious!! Wonderful staff and amazing food! Check this place out!

What a great time we had! It's so refreshing to have a laid back place with quality. Most of the time you get a relaxed neighborhood place and dive bar food. This is the opposite. Classy food options and still can drink and have fun like a normal bar setting. The best thing I loved about this place is I got to choose! Me! It was amazing. I was really hungry for a burger because I saw one go out and it looked amazing. Now I walk over and look at their deli case and it's amazing! So what I decide is to do An appetizer of 2 bacon wrap scallops and the ordered a burger with sautéed Brussels sprouts. What a combination that was! It was perfect. I couldn't have asked for a better meal and better combo then what I had. Love it. Hidden gem. Unlike any other place I have ever been.

Absolutely Phenomenal... Had a great lunch here this week and combined a steak sandwich and 2 of these huge bacon wrapped scallops in the side. I ordered a la carte and the guy who waited in me was amazing! He told me to tell him what I wanted and he would make it happen. I was super excited and love that things were just as delicious as they looked. Looking forward to the next visit to take down some of there fresh vegetables and seafood!

My favorite is the Salmon Eggs Benedict with hash browns! Amazing.  I am always taken good care of here on weekends and can enjoy my meal, and drinks with a good group of regulars. Last time I had a grilled chicken wrap and I cant wait to try it again the next time. Best place to watch a game and eat a good meal.

Talk about something different! I asked about a menu, and they don't have one. I walked over to the deli case and then it all made sense. Fresh vegetable, fresh seafoods, huge steaks. Everything looked great! I tries the salmon and wow I got a huge piece. Tried it with some steamed and sautéed vegetables, along with rice that they make in house. It was amazing. Great Flavors! And a ton of food. Couldn't eat it all.
Best bloody marys in town! 4th Base favorites include Perch Fish Fry, and Ribeye Steak Sandwich. Ate the 1/2 lb Bacon Cheddar burger with BBQ

Had some delicious bacon wrapped scallops today! Some of best food quality around. Was so pleased to see the deli case full of their fresh foods. Great looking items and only place I have been with a great selection of vegetables. Can't wait to try the huge crab legs next visit. It wasn't a cheap meal but I could tell it as high quality and definitely worth it.

What a great experience! It's very different and a little unorthodox, but everything was great! I was told to walk over by the deli case and wow! All this fresh food! The size of the salmon and crab was impressive. I wanted to tackle the Porterhouse also but didn't have that size appetite this time. I went with the blackened Cajun Salmon, and steamed vegetables and this homemade rice! Everything blended perfectly. After that I tried a latte that they make and that too was wonderful. This place was perfect for me because of all the sports stuff hanging all over. TVs all over the place and a relaxed atmosphere made for a great time! Go in with an open mind and leave full and satisfied.

WOW! Place doesn't fit the quality of the food. Hidden treasure for sure, food was so good. I love the fact I could order anything lol Cheese sticks, dynamite!!!! The sauce was so amazing. Highly recommend.

Food is really over priced. Atmosphere is cold and nothing happening at night. We shared the fish and chips and deviled eggs. Batter was soggy and and smelt very fishy. Better places to go. Service is also poor.

New place that opened up. Use to be an Irish pub but now is a british pub. Not much changed inside.  Place is way over priced. Payed nearly $30 for a drink and fish and chips. Fish and chips had a soggy batter and tasted like old stinky fish. Barely ate any of it and was hopping the waitress would of asked. Service was slow and there was only 3 other people in there. Place is hidden down from Bel Air but with those prices, slow service, and terrible product I will take my hard earned money elsewhere.
Very good and have dined again. Have dined in pre Covid and take out during.  Would recommend.
Great atmosphere. Friendly staff.
JP was the best!!! He made us laugh and he took great care of us

Always love coming to red lion! Been coming here for years. Never a disappointment! Great drink, food and vibe! Oh yeah, JP is by far the greatest server on Water Street! Be sure to have a chat with him while there, he's the best.
JP is amazing! He was kind, funny & prompt with his service. If you walk past JP & don't laugh, there is something wrong with you.

This was such a fun place to go with my friend for a night out. Our bartender JP was super awesome and friendly. He also introduced us to the English Tea shot, which was delicious! Definitely recommend this place!
Authentic British Pub, scratch cooking, good for all occasions, with a fantastic rooftop patio, and international staff.

I stopped in a Monday night because I was up in Milwaukee for work and just happened to drive by. The space was very warm and had a genuine "pub" feeling that was really welcoming. The bartender was Scottish (I think) which was awesome and made it feel authentic - plus he recommended a really great beer called "Old Speckled Hen" which I'd never had and may be my new favorite beer - so creamy and easy to drink. I wasn't terribly hungry, but I couldn't resist trying the poutine (how can anyone resist trying poutine?) - and YUM. I wanted to lick the plate. All in all, I loved the vibe, the bartender, the food, the beer - and I look forward to coming back to Milwaukee again to try more of the menu!
First time I've been axe throwing, I was awful at the beginning of the night but with help from Justin I was hitting bullseye's in no time. Very knowledgable staff, and cool neon Halloween theme!

Great spot with people who know how to have fun. My server was a young lady and she herself said she isn't great at the axe throwing but she was great at connecting with customers and helped the group when we maybe didn't do so well. Great vibe for family and adults alike.
We went for a team event for work, let me tell you that Nobody when home without having a blast! The staff was knowledgable and there for everything we needed. Caroline was an awesome axmaster!

This place was the bomb! We went there for our Apex team event and Janessa and Jack both were phenomenal! The woman who taught us how to throw was pretty good! She really had that down! What a great way to start the night!

We came last night to celebrate our January birthdays and had a great time. Our Axe Master, Katelyn, was phenomenal! She took the time to help a few of the people in our group who had never been axe throwing before so they could correct a few things they were doing incorrectly, which really improved their experience. Everyone at the bar was very attentive and the environment was fun and very clean. Thank you all!

We held a Staff Retreat at North South and it went very well! The coordinator was very accommodating, consistent communication, met all our needs and made the experience of booking the event very easy. Staff members Alyssa and Madeline were sweet and helpful and there for anything we needed. We had a great time!
Super fun! The drinks were good (love that they also have a good mocktail menu) and the staff is super friendly and attentive. Great place for a date or to go with a group of friends.

We held our company event at NorthSouth Club. We all had a blast! Never threw an axe before, but are now fans and will definitely go again! Axe Master Miles did a great job teaching us the art of axe throwing!
Super fun! Staff is great. Colin was super sweet. Gave me a discount on my shirt because I needed the display one and it had dust on it! How dare they!
I had a lot of fun prices are very reasonable, will be back many more times. If you're in the area I definitely suggest you check it out for a good time.

Staff focused on COVID-19 saftey.  AXE MKE staff all wore masks and the place was spotless!  Constantly cleaning while taking care of us!  Axe Master Kevin was so helpful teaching us technique and proper use... We will for sure go back!  SUPER FUN! Good music and great drinks!

A truly unique experience can be found at this bar where you can grab a beer and throw axes. The space's cabin aesthetic really adds to the experience and the staff is beyond helpful. Their energy really feeds into yours and they'll make sure you stick the axe into the target! I came here for my friend's birthday party and had an absolute blast from beginning to end. This would be a really exciting team building exercise or space to host a birthday party. Everything from the drinks to the targets are perfectly made to ensure a great time! And they do axe throwing leagues so if you're really good, or just having a fun time, check it out!

AXE MKE is hands down one of the best places in MKE. The idea of throwing axes and drinking definitely seemed funny at first, but with the safety precautions and instructions that the axe master gives before you start, you feel very safe and have TONS of fun doing it. Who knew throwing axes could be so therapeutic?! I have been to AXE MKE a couple of times, and each time was better than the last! The staff is very fun and friendly, there is a good variety of music, and their cocktail and beer menu is great (my friend was a huge fan of the peanut butter pie cocktail- which comes with a Reece's peanut butter cup!). They even have some seasonal targets! I went with my family for my birthday back in October, and we got to throw axes at pumpkins and bats instead of the normal target! I would highly recommend AXE MKE for a date night, birthday party, or bachelor/bachelorette party!

Super fun experience! Was a little wary at first of the idea of axe throwing but they go above and beyond to make sure the space is safe AND fun. The employees seem to be having just as much fun as everyone else, and even when I didn't get the axe to stick, they helped me with great instructions and support, and I finally got a bullseye! Reasonably priced drinks and a wide array of snacks to choose from, Axe MKE is a great hangout for friends or any team building activity.

This is the perfect place if you're looking for a fun night out! Whether it's a bachelor party, birthday party or just a spiced up date night, Axe MKE is by far one of the most unique bars I've been to. The staff is incredibly knowledgeable. And best part, beside the stellar drinks, is the heavy duty bell you get to ring once you get a bullseye. I highly recommend this bar to anyone, it's a great place to sip on some tasty beers or cocktails all while throwing axes. What more could you ask for!!

If the concept of drinking and throwing axes if intimidating to you, have no fear - the axe masters definitely know what they're doing. Very patient and helpful. Definitely a fun and unique concept for a bar. Drinks were tasty and reasonably priced, with friendly bartenders and staff. I would recommend this place for a party, or even just a casual drink if you're looking for something cool and different. I really enjoyed the atmosphere - very cool rustic "outdoorsy" feel that you don't get in many places in Milwaukee.
Such a fun time!  Shawn was hilarious and helpful!  We definitely enjoyed drinking and throwing axes:)
Jnnjjjjjiijujjjujjiijjjjjjjiiijiiijjiujnnnjjijinnj­jjjjjjjjinjnjjnnnnjijjijunnnujjijjjjjju
My old local #1 spot.....love this place.  Try Wednesday taco night.
Stopped in for dinner and a couple drinks, had a great time! Friendly staff, great bar food!

The accommodations, Food, Service and Staff were Excellent. The owners pop in frequently and take great care of their customers. Will Definitely come back.. + it's by Wick field for a quick drink after playing sports & Will shuttle you to watch the Brewers! Damn.

I absolutely love this place! It's great for any occasion and accommodates everyone in my circle of friends. The menu has a large variety of options perfect for dinner, lunch or just something to nibble on. I love the BBQ pork sandwich and the teriyaki wings.  Bloody's are fantastic and  they have a great selection of craft beers. I recommend this bar for a night out, to cure that hangover or to catch a ride to miller park!

I'm a huge Milwaukee Brewer fan. I was turned on to Obriens by a friend that said shuttles to the home games were free and fast. She was right!!! I grabbed a microbrew tap beer(which they have many to choose from) a burger that was outstanding and away my friends and I went to the game. If your just out to watch a game they also have plenty of TV's.
Just ok....... barely acknowledged me.
Great place for a little rest and relaxation!
Ordered lunch online while enjoying some wine across the streetFast service, friendly delivery and absolutely will be back !
Beer was good. Food was good. Service was painfully slow. Painfully. I mean slow.
Amazing drinks amazing atmosphere and amazing waiter. All I have to say is, get the big a** pretzel!!!!!!
Bird was friendly and attentive, along with the other bartenders. Great food and service.

Our party of 6 visited on Sunday, 6/6/21.The entire facility is spectacular! The shady parking lot, comfortable tunnel bar, beautiful spacious air-conditioned restaurant, fire pits and outside seating, well-trained, friendly staff, excellent food and beer, easy to use online menu or paper if you prefer. If you have not explored Explorium, you have put it on your to-list.(P.S: Download their app and have a "FREE beer tomorrow" or today.
Poor customer service and a manager who apparently believes that the customer is never right.

I was very disappointed...ordered food waited 50 min for a burger and wings never told it was going to be that long ordered the Big O ..no bacon no chorizo. fries cold .. waiter didn't bring food someone else did he never came back so I could tell him ..I stopped another waitress ... but he gave service to other tables ..I watched him service the Mexican people well...I'm a great tipper I refused too  ...he didn't even bring the bill he told me that the bacon was mixed into the other stuff no chorizo...it wasn't. it's red from spices not on my burger not even seasoned...I will not recommend this place to my customers or friends and family!  This was the worst customers service I've experienced in a long time ! Lesson learned!  GO TO STACK'D downtown they're the best!

4/21/2018I will never understand how anyone can brag about a frozen burger, out of the Reinhart or Sysco box.I had high hopes yesterday when a friend & I stopped at Oscars, but as soon as I saw the perfectly rounded piece of meat, I knew what I was about to bite into, another, throw the frozen puck on the grill burger, dang!The bun "looked" good but was rubbery as if it had been nuked!If anyone wants to make a great burger, it must hand-pattied & come from fresh ground 80 / 20 chuck but not from "tube" meat, plus a bun or roll that's "properly" toasted!We stopped at 12:30, the place was packed (and noisy) but the service was great along with the sweet potato and regular fries.I give Oscar's 3 star because of the service & fries but the burger, I would call a 1!Come on Oscar, get fresh meat!
Ate there once burger was really good and the staff was friendly.

Had great service by our server Samantha. The food was very average and quite disappointing how many amazing things I've heard about it. Started with the Jimmy nuggets.very average. My girlfriend got a burger medium and I got the. Big o mid rare. Both burgers came out quickly but we're both well done. Good bun and toppings on the big o but the patty itself had very little flavor. the parmsean fries weren't great themselves. Overall a disappointing  1st experience  since it consistently gets mentioned as 1 of if not the best burgers  in milwaukee. I will be back to give a 2nd try since so many people rave about it but after my first experience I walk away wondering what all the hype  is about.
The service was good, the food was very good and the menu was easy to understand. A great selection of beer with more than 20 to choose from.

Found this place by a general search and was amazed! Service was top and the server was more than amazing, very attentive and quick for both food and drink orders. Very affordable. Would highly recommend!
Awesome as usually. I haven't been there in a long time. Burgers are still an awesome value for what you get. I expected to pay more for a burger of this quality.

I always love coming here, they are always so nice, and do a great job. Though overcrowded most of the time, I don't mind waiting, they don't really communicate that there will be a wait or someone does a rush job. Great as I always got a beautifully constructed big gringo burger and lovely fries on the side. The flavors all worked together, and it tasted really great. It was the best I've ever had, and it was definitely worth the money spent.

They are very arrogant, when I recommended them on how they should improve their dish they talked down to me. They believe they know everything , no courtesy at all. The chef was so rude..these guys won't listen to you then why even open a public place in the first place.
Well cooked and optimum quantity was served to me, I don't think that I have eaten anything that tasty. They did everything we wanted to do!  Great food and friendly environment.

Yesterday was the first time we visited this restaurant. But It is surely not the last time. The evening was excellent with the wonderful service, with the marvelous food and drinks, and with the honest charge. We will surely visit there in a short time.

Oscar's Pub & Grill is a good place to get some well-made hearty burgers. There's a parking lot next to the restaurant plus street parking. During Brewers season and Summerfest they own and operate a shuttle bus that is also parked on property. There is a back patio addition that is open but only during summer season. There is a bar with seating but it's best to allow the hostess to seat you.One word of caution is the noise level. This place is popular and there are no noise absorbents along the walls. If there is an important game on TV and the place is full, it will be loud.

What is there to say about Oscars's that hasn't been said? Its almost like comfort food to me. I have been here several times and never once had a bad experience. A great place to the the Brewers and Packers with my buddies from town. My only complaint would be, at times, the service can be a little low, but other than that, come in and have blast!4.5/5
It is not the fanciest place in the world, but it does what it need to do. I love love love the burgers and the service. Always fast and friendly. Prices are great too. Its a recommendation from me!
Great food, friendly atmosphere, awesome price and great beers. Overall, great experience. Parking is free.
Awesome burgers!! It's a little bit difficult to find but it's definitely worth the trip.

I had the pleasure of dining at Oak Barrel recently, and I cannot say enough good things about the experience. From the moment we walked in, the staff made us feel incredibly welcome, but our server, Liz, truly made the evening unforgettable. She attentive, friendly, and went above and beyond to ensure that every aspect of our meal was perfect. Her knowledge of the menu and ability to anticipate our needs added such a personal touch to the evening.The food at Oak Barrel was nothing short of exceptional. While everything we tried was fantastic, the cheese curds were the undeniable highlight. They were perfectly crispy on the outside and deliciously gooey on the inside, with just the right amount of seasoning. Paired with ranch, they were absolutely irresistible. The rest of our meal was equally impressive, with each dish prepared to perfection and presented beautifully. It's clear the kitchen takes pride in their work.The cozy yet vibrant ambiance of Oak Barrel rounded out the experience, making it the perfect spot for a memorable meal. Between the amazing service and the outstanding food--especially those unforgettable cheese curds--it's a place I'll definitely be returning to. I've already started recommending it to friends, and I can't wait to visit again soon!

We recently had the pleasure to have the Oak Barrel Public House host our daughter's wedding rehearsal dinner.  We had a private event space that contained a great bar and plenty of seating.  They can accommodate up to 80 people.  We had 52.  There was great food on the buffet that we chose - cheese burger sliders, meat lover's pizza, chicken tenders, house salad, and the best Mac and cheese.  All of the attendees raved about the Mac and cheese.  But the best part were the bartenders, Evan and Bertha.  They were so friendly and efficient.  Bertha made sure that the buffet never went empty.  We really can't say enough about how professional they were.  We had over 50 people and they all were so pleased with the food, the drinks, and the excellent staff.  Also a big kudos to Mackenzie, the event planner, who helped coordinate the event.

Amazing! 5 stars all around! Came to MKE for a quick getaway from Chicago and so incredibly happy to stumble upon Oak Barrel. Came in on a busy Saturday night (big name concert in town didn't help!) but were greeted by friendly faces and sat right away. Immediately upon sitting we were given a small bag of bacon fat popcorn. My husband and I had to fight our 3 year old for it.  It was a perfect little salty starter. Cheese curds for mom and dad and a grilled cheese for the little one soon followed. Awesome move removing the crusts off the grilled cheese - toddler gave it a big high five (..way better than a yelp 5 star review!). Curds were absolute light crispy little bites of perfection.  The star was the Dynamite Chicken Mac and Cheese.  Wow!! Crispy, cheesy, perfectly spicy.  We're still talking about it!Service was great and the manager was seen multiple times around the place checking in on everyone and helping his staff. This place is so on point with the service and amazing food that we can't wait to visit again and make it our first stop!

Food was great and our server, Maggie, was super friendly and made great recommendations.
the pretzels were so good!! our server Maggie was so sweet and great to us!! I got the horseshoe it was a lot, but so good.
Avery is an amazing server.  Very prompt, friendly and, responsive.  We had a great time!!!  Thank you Avery!  Sorry my mom kept dropping money!

Came into oak barrel tonight for the first time and I'm glad we came here. Our server Nina, had great beer recommendations. Riverwest stein which is an amber on tap was great, as well as the cheese curds.
Loved it here. Great food especially the popcorn, Nina is fantastic. Really loved stopping in on my trip here

Amazing food and always a great atmosphere when we come. Top place to come before any Marquette Game. Our servicer Nina was so attentive and sweet, always checking in on us. Always a top place to come back to.

Shoutout to game day brunch at Oak Barrel!!!!!!!!! Nina was the best waitress ever and the breakfast potatoes slap. PS the Big Breakfast comes with pancakes :) They do not skimp on the champagne and it is worth every cent!
thanks to our great server Nina!! Great place to start your day awesome bottomless mimosa deal :)
Came for a brunch with a big group of friends and had really good service from our server, Nina!!! Good brunch food and bottomless mimosas was a blast!
Nina was the best server ever!!!!! We had a huge group and she was so accommodating!!!!
Nina was the best server, she really had amazing vibes and was so sweet. 100% coming back and asking for Nina as my server. Also want her to join my friend group!
Nina was a great server! Food was amazing too! Great place to go for bottomless mimosas

Went here before the Marquette game & it was so much fun! Nina was our server, she was quick, attentive & made great recommendations. Bottomless mimosas here are the best deal! Will definitely be back.
Carianne was fantastic. Real cool and knew the menu very well. Awesome place, would def recommend
Great place to watch the game! Avery was amazing and took care of wonderfully. Definitely recommend the Moscow mule
omg Christine and Maggie are the best!! Made TampaBay feel at home. Such great service,such personality. Never going anywhere else

We went here for dinner before a show downtown and the staff were so friendly and helpful. Our server Avery was great helpful if we had questions and very knowledgeable of the menu. The popcorn was a great pre dinner snack that we will definitely be trying to make at home.

Loved the food and service was great!!  Will be back!! Nice atmosphere!! Called after the show at Miller Highlife Theatre and table was ready when we got there!! Recommend Wisconsin burger, Smash burger tacos and had great drinks!!
Ate after a show at Milwaukee Theatre. food was good, Service was top notch! Our host Avery was EXCEPTIONAL. Definitely recommend!
Food was great. Sarah is awesome very intantive great service. Will definitely be back
Awesome ambiance before an event at Fiserv. Food and drinks were great! All paired with even better service from the bartender Sarah. Will be back!
Sarah was our bartender and she was amazing. Kept making sure we were doing good with drinks and food. Very friendly atmosphere!
The bartender Sarah was fantastic very attentive and aware of what was going on very friendly and absolutely fantastic service and food.
Oak barrel was great! Awesome popcorn and really great atmosphere. Maggie was a great server!
Avery was the BOMB!  Great service! Great food! I would recommend requesting Avery if you eat here.  She will take great care you! The music was spot on too!
Awesome bar, great drinks.   Sarah the bartender knows how to make her drinks!   Loved the mules and old fashions.  We'll be back soon for shamrocks in our Guinness!
so good, BEST CHEESE CURDS EVER, the service is always amazing and seriously the food is just so so so good

Great food, as always. We highly recommend the chicken tenders. We had our wedding rehearsal here last year and people still rave about them. We came in tonight after the Holiday Lights Celebration and our server Avery was fantastic. We appreciate their kindness and attentiveness. Will be lifelong customers!!
we had our first meal downtown in some time and I'm glad we choose Oak Barrel. The service was great. Sarah was sweet and super fast. It was a great experience and we'll be going back again soon!
I had a great time and the service by Sarah was spectacular. I am new in town and heard to check this place out and I'm glad I did.
Eddie the bartender was amazing. Pizza was phenomena. Great atmospher. Will definitely be back!!
Sarah made me a great sangria, I'll be back again! She was so sweet and the food was delicious!
I had Sarah as a bartender and she rocked. She was friendly but also attentive and prompt, which was perfect for my lunch bre. Also the cheese curds were amazing !!!
Sarah made me a Jameson orange mule and it was so refreshing!!! Amazing service. I will be frequenting this establishment.
I was in town for a concert and was assisted by Sarah who was kind and made an amazing old fashioned. Will definitely visit again!
Emily W. was great! Service was fantastic and the food was incredible! this place is awesome!! definitely coming back!...side tip... get the bacon popcorn!!
Emily W was great!!!!!!! super personal and professional. Nice to have good service  food was great too!

Sarah the bartender was excellent!! made me the best whiskey sour I've ever had and was so helpful w the food menu. try to go their now as much as possible because her service and knowledge of the restaurant!! The bottles behind the bar are so creative and the idea behind it is so cool, I definitely plan to get one of my own back there soon As it really brings the whole establishment to life And creates an Amazing ambiance!!!
Their Mac and cheese is phenomenal. Eddy, the bartender, was fantastic and makes every drink just perfect.
Great food and excellent cocktails. our server, Emily w. was attentive but kind and was great at her job! will def be back!!
Abby K was great and understanding as we had to wait for 2 more people.  She never made us feel rushed to order.
Food was really great alongside the super friendly service from Avery and Emily W!!!!!
Abby H was great! She was quick and super kind. The food was out quick and tasted delicious!

Wow. The food was way better than expected. Had the cheese curds and pretzel sticks. Both were fantastic. We visit Milwaukee a few times a year and somehow haven't stopped in here yet. The service was particularly great. Abby H was very accommodating for our group and provided a great experience.We'll be back, for sure.

Abby H provided the most fantastic service. She was super personable and accommodating. The pretzel with béchamel cheese and cheese curds were phenomenal. I would highly recommend. The bar had a great feel.
Avery was the best server ever and the Wisco burger was fantastic. 10/10 will be back and request Avery again.
The biscuits in gravy were some of the best I've ever had and the service by our waitress, Avery, was second to none. Would definitely come back for the bottomless mimosas soon!
Amazing food, good bottomless. The server, Avery, was super genuine and helpful with recommendations.
Stopped by here yesterday for a few drinks and had a good time! The bartender Sarah was very attentive and friendly. She also makes a good old-fashioned! Thank Sarah!
Great food even better service. Quick and fast with orders. If you come here ask for Avery you will not be disappointed.

Had a wonderful dinner there yesterday before the theater. Highly recommend as service was superb and food was delicious. Our server, Avery, made great recommendations and was super helpful and knowledgeable in making menu suggestions. We had the bourbon glazed Brussel sprouts and caprese pizza which had just the amount of spice. Avery's shadow trainee, Emily, was also lovely and made great suggestions.

Every time I have been in Oak Barrel the staff has been amazing. Especially at time when we here so many places are lacking in this area. The bartenders and servers couldn't be more kind and attentive. And if you want Wisconsin comfort food  and cocktails this is the place to go.We recently hosted a 65+ person welcome party/rehearsal dinner at Oak Barrel and every guest raved about the team, the space and the food. The night exceeded our expectations and that is in BIG part to Mackenzie Beesley (sales and marketing manager). Mackenzie made the planning process so easy and ensured the event went off without a hitch. We will be forever grateful for her and the team helping us kick off our wedding weekend in style and family fun.I can assure you, we will back be, especially before Bucks games!
Avery and Emily were great servers! Food was delicious and came super quick which was perfect before we went to a show at the Marcus theater.

We were visiting Milwaukee for Halloween weekend, and decided to stop into Oak Barrel for dinner. Our  server was Nina who was very attentive and sweet. The place was decorated nicely for Halloween, and the food was amazing. The cheese curds and pretzel sticks are a MUST! We will for sure be back next time we are in town.

Stopped in Friday night after the bucks game and we can't wait to be back. Nina was our waitress and she was great! Even though it was late she was still attentive and kind to our group! The cheese curds and drinks at oak barrel are soooo good

Last night we stopped in before the Bucks game, and even though the place was packed we had amazing service! Nina, our waitress, went above and beyond for our group. If you're looking for a place to eat before a Bucks game definitely check this place out!

Stopped in for dinner while visiting.  Was seated quickly and given great amount of time to review menu. Great drink options and food. Ordered Whisky Bacon Pasta- highly recommend!! Waitress Avery was great took the time to make sure we got exactly what we wanted.

Avery was our server and she was great!!  we had a big party of 17 and she was on point with EVERYTHING!  Bacon Jam Burger was great!  Pretzel bun was great!  But I'll be asking for Avery every time!  Thanks Avery!
Great food and atmosphere. Avery was our server and was excellent! Avery checked in on us and recommended drinks when the ones we ordered couldn't be made. We will be back!
Was served by Avery, and had a great time. She was very attentive. Super good service and decent food.
Abby was amazing. She provided awesome service and the food was great! Go Bucks. Thank you
Great brunch spot. Avery was very nice and got our food/drinks to us super quick. Highly recommend the cheese curds.
First off , the fall drinks are excellent, Avery is extremely informative and gave us great service which truly made our date night even sweeterI love this place and will continue to come back!!

Three words: BACON FAT POPCORN!!!! This place is awesome, and I will be back. Nina was our server tonight, and she did a great job with our larger group. Friendly staff, great location with it being right by the fiserv forum, and great beer.
Nina had amazing recommendations for our first time trying out this place. I ordered the Wisco burger with the sweet potato fries and it was SO good. Fall sangria was 10/10
Oak Barrel has great food and great service! Avery was an awesome waitress! we will absolutely be back
Our server, Avery, was super awesome! Food was delish too :) Go bucks! Will be back for another game soon
Avery was awesome, she took care of our group very well while we were watching the bucks game. Food was good the deals are pretty good too
Some of the best burgers we ever had. Our server was so nice, glad that she talked us into going with the WiscoBurger when there was so many options to choose from.

The husband and I went to Oak Barrel last night and enjoyed a smash burger and a flatbread pizza. Good bar food! The interior was well decorated for Halloween and the staff was friendly and attentive. Avery and Abby are the best! I'd go back here for sure.
Maggie was phenomenal! we had a huge group and we didn't have to wait for anything! she was spot on and a joy!! Such a wonderful waitress and so very nice!!!!

Maggie took great care of us for my little sister's 21st. We had a big party of 12 and she was patient and so nice to all of us. Would definitely do a big group here again if she is our server. Also the food is tasty every time, I suggest the oak barrel skillet.

We had great service!!! Maggie was so helpful and respectful!! She was spot on, she was funny made our experience great! Food was amazing! They stayed on top of our bottomless mimosas! Food came quick, chill environment!

Avery was amazing. food was great. great service. great ambiance. I got the Philly skillet and it was amazing. Was a big  enough portion I couldn't even finish! The bottomless mimosas were great as well.

Amazing experience! I absolutely love returning to this place. The atmosphere is amazing, food is fantastic and drinks are a hit! Avery was also a grade A+ host! She's so sweet and accommodating and did everything in her power to make sure our dining experience was perfect. Thank you again!!
Just ate at Oak Barrel before a Bucks game.  Food was so good.  It was our first time here and Avery was great helping us pick our meals.   Highly recommend!

This place was right next to our Airbnb and we came in towards the end of the night. Avery, our server, was so fabulous and was so attentive to us coming in at different times. Would totally recommend!
Perry was a stellar server was super entertaining and super knowledgeable. Will be returning!
Perry, our waitress, was knowledgeable and attentive. We all did the bottomless mimosas and they were a perfect ratio of Prosecco to orange juice. We will be back!
Perry was amazing!!! Give her a raise and let her play bar dice with us!!
Perry was our server and was great! She knew the menu and gave us food suggestions. Food was delicious will be back again!
Awesome experience!  Maggie our server was fantastic! I love going to downtown MKE and Maggie & Oak Barrel made the trip more than worth while.  Terrific. ​

Stopped by due to our normal place being closed. Pleasantly surprised, food was outstanding, and our server Maggie was even better. Will definitely be back next time we're in Milwaukee! Our new go to place when seeing a show at the forum.
Food was great. Maggie was knowledgeable and very helpful when ordering. Would certainly recommend and will come again.

Had a great time here for brunch!! Food was awesome and we couldn't deny bottomless mimosas too. Our server Perry was great as well, she definitely made sure we were good with whatever we needed. Would highly recommend!!
Our server, Perry, was excellent. never had an empty glass, everything was catered. Absolutely nothing but good things for her and this establishment
Perry was AWESOME! Constantly checking in our party. I had family from from out of town and was debating where to go. Perry made it all worth it. Food was great!
Maggie was incredible!! She was very Knowledgable about the menu. She had great energy!
the food was incredible, ambiance was immaculate, and our server maggie was a STAR!! highly recommend for anyone in the milwaukee area!
The food was phenomenal and the vibes were vibing. Avery was the BEST  server !!!!!!!!!!!! Will be returning

Our server Avery did an AMAZING job of making us feel welcome and was on top of everything! We had the pleasure of also meeting Breonte and he was also extremely welcoming. The food, drink, and atmosphere were everything we were hoping for! Five stars all day!
Our group went here for part of our bachelorette party. the food was delicious and our server, Avery, was amazing! Avery went above and beyond to make sure we enjoyed our time here!
Food was amazing, great menu options, server Avery was friendly, attentive and kind. Manager Breonte came and gave a special shout-out to our bride, we had a great time!
Avery was one of the best servers I have ever had. She was patient & fun with our bachelorette party! We met Breontae, the manager and he was great too!
Food was great and Avery our server was fantastic. Very accommodating and helpful to a large group of people!
Had an amazing time. Great food. Great atmosphere. Great servers. Maggie and Amelia were fantastic. We will be coming back soon.
I love Oak Barrel! The cheesy food is my favorite. Avery is a gorgeous soul and always makes us feel special.

My friends and I came out for appetizers and drinks on a Friday night at 7. We had a reservation made online and got seated immediately. We loved our friendly server, Avery! Quick service & yummy food and drinks
Food was great and our waitress Avery was excellent and took good care of us. Will definitely dine there again!!
Our server Perry was excellent! The bacon flavored popcorn was delightful and the service was top notch.

Seriously, I don't know if we waited more than 10 minutes for our food.  The service was amazing!  We eat dinner somewhere between boomer o'clock and a quarter til millennial (5:30ish) , so it wasn't too busy.  Avery was AH-mazing, and our food and drinks were great!
Avery and Maggie were the best. We came in with our friends from New York and LA and they had an unforgettable experience.
Avery and Maggie were the best!!! We had a great time :) Bottomless mimosas and excellent service
Came here for a girls night out. We had a wonderful time. Great Food. Great service. Our waiter Avery was very helpful. Highly recommend!
Good food, quick service. Drinks were reasonable for the area and Avery was a great server!!!
Went for lunch on a week-end. Able to sit outside and receive great service by Avery who was friendly and attentive.  If ever back in Milwaukee and want pub style food - I would return!
Food was awesome, atmosphere was better than expected, and ask for Avery! She was an awesome server!

My husband and I had our after wedding party here and we had so much fun! Meghan and Kaitlyn were such a blast and quick to make drinks. We did pizza off the menu for late night snacks and had so much fun celebrating with our friends and family! Thanks !

We hosted my husbands retirement party at Oak Barrel on Saturday and it was amazing. Food was so delicious and everyone loved it. Drinks were also great and staff took amazing care of my family and guests. The panner we worked with Mackenzie made it so easy to plan our event and helped us every step of the way. We will definitely be booking more events here in the future.

Really like the place. Came in for the Packers game. Nice vibe for the game. They did touch down shots when the packers score. The wisco burger was so good!!!  Server was top notch. Definitely recommend checking it out.

my family and i had our sons rehearsal dinner at oak barrel public house in the window bar and everything was amazing. Meghan gave amazing service and made great drinks! the food was impeccable and the venue was immaculate. we will for sure be coming back when we return to Milwaukee!

Food is great. The bacon fat popcorn is amazing. Get the Wisco burger. It's one of a kind and the best burger I've ever got. Great selection of tap beers too. Wife liked the veggie options as well. I'd say well rounded menu.

We held a private event at Oak Barrel and Mackenzie made the planning process so easy! The onsite staff was great (especially Skye) and were able to handle our pretty rowdy large group. We would definitely come back here for our next private event.

Cassidy and David are by far the best bartenders. They were very helpful with choosing what to drink and very personable. We actually came back twice in one day just to hang out with them. Highly recommend visiting.

I love this bar. As a young woman I feel extremely safe here, which is something I can't really say of any other bar in the area. The staff is so friendly and kind, they are quick and it's easy to build a relationship with them! Out of the hundreds of regulars, they somehow manage to remember you! I've never felt unsafe at OB and because the staff is so attentive, if any issue were to arise, I know I would get prompt service if need be. Love the drinks of course, too! GET THE BLUE MOON SHOT! You wont be disappointed.

Came for the Bucks game. Had a great time. They play the game sound too. Tons of beer, tried the spotted cow and a lakefront beer...I think it was. I'm not sure, but both were good, server was attentive and the pizza was spot on. The crust is thin and crispy and the sauce is more savory than sweet. Definitely would come again.
Bentley and D'juan were excellent bartender/servers and chef Dillon made me some outstanding dry rub wings and sautéed broccoli I will bring back my wife and friends
Paul is THE BEST mixologist!  Hung out at the 2nd floor bar where he set our whole group up for a fun pre-concert experience.  Can't wait to return!

A friend recommended this place to me. So finally I stopped by yesterday and we had a great time. I really loved the bacon bourbon maple waffle and the bottomless mimosa and bloody Mary's. Yummmmmm. Highly recommend

Stopped in to try out some brunch today.  Was hoping to sit on the patio but the weather was a little cold and rainy to sit out side, but we did get a nice table by the window area.They had a bottomless mimosa/bloody special going on for brunch which was pretty sweet that we could swap between mimosas or bloodies.  We ordered the bacon maple syrup waffle....mmmm! I was in heaven, it's the perfect kind of dish, bacon and maple syrup :)  My girlfriend tried the french connection omelette which i would have tried if she hadn't eaten it all before I got a chance.  The server was great, she recommended some dishes to try for dinner later, which we will definitely have to come back and try!  I highly recommend this place, it's perfect being right in the heart of downtown and the ambience, service and food was great!
Every $9 mixed drink was super watered down. Very disappointing!! Waitress was very attentive though, she made up for the terrible drinks!
Matt the bartender is awesome! He's super nice and funny. Thanks, Matt!

f*ck this place, d*mbass bouncer took my friends legit federal ID, we called the cops on him and then he wouldn't let us in after bc he knows he's stupid and doesn't want us to tell his manager that hes an idiot!
Great place to meet up with friends and shoot a game of pool.
The food was delicious and staff was great, awesome atmosphere. Will definitely be back and recommend....
Service was AMAZING!!! We had Tara, I came in having a hard day and she turned that all around. The food was incredible (her recommendations) I cannot wait to come back and come visit again

This is my second time here and once again it did not disappoint. The honey chicken biscuit was outstanding!!! Sat at the bar and Matt was out bartende/server. What a great guy! We wanted and waited for nothing. I'll be back!
Great food options, everything was delicious! Had curds, corn ribs and the fish sandwich. Loved the decoration, open seating and music fit the setting. Jocelyn was our server and was fantastic!!
The food was excellent and the customer service was excellent also this is a real good place the food is delicious.

Jocelyn was so amazing, she catered to our personalized dietary needs and desires. Her recommendations and soft talk was very engaging too, without being intrusive and the food was amazing too. overall great service and food!

Our waitress Tara did excellent service for us tonight. it is always appreciated. and she is definitely committed to her job. she deserves a raise or promotion of some sorts. would come back again only if she is my waitress, lol.
Food was great. Portions were worth it. Atmosphere was good. Tara was amazing. Definitely can't wait to come back and try the burgers.
One of the best chicken sandwiches I've ever had, the recent menu changes seem to be off to a good start
Food was so-so, atmosphere is cold, owner is very rude and not accommodating. Very disappointing

Been here twice now, and the quality of the food is pretty consistent. Atmosphere is good and food is delicius. Love the sliders. Don't expect to be sat when you walk in. Make a reservation if you can. They always have a waitlist. Service is lacking. Servers could be more attentive and friendly. Other than that, it is a great place to have brunch!
I went once with my parents and it was very good, but a little expensive. I had a blood orange mojito and it was delicious. I wish they had more non-meat options.
This food is god damn awesome!! Period.

My friend visited this bar a couple days ago. While he was waiting in line to use the bathroom, he was approached by a woman that he doesn't know or had any interactions with. She said that he looked like a "smug white dude" and assaulted him. My friend ended up being the one that was kicked out instead of the woman that assaulted him. The bar did nothing to help or assist my friend, and victim blamed him. This really has my friend shaken up. Don't go to this bar. It has major problems that they choose not to address.

The food pictures are nice and must be ok, but since I'm not sure of my tetanus status, there's no way in h...ll I'm getting out the car. The parking lot is a junkyard of "working" food trucks(?) and trailer park motif. The owners are lucky redneck mentality rule the area. Only things missing were a hound dog and old washing machine on a porch, with dualing banjos playing in the back. Sooo. Sooo weeeee.
Went for a fish fry, was not impressed. Thought it was pricey for what we got.

I had been to Bildas before, and had an excellent, huge fish sandwich.  I brought my husband and daughter this time-but we all were very disappointed.  Flies were everywhere!  They were landing on our food and faces-it was sooooo irritating!  My husband ordered the all-u-can eat fish fry-and was pretty disappointed because it was dripping with grease!  My fish sandwich was great as were my french fries, but it was hard to enjoy knowing he was not enjoying his meal and we were shooing away flies the entire time.  I hear they have great pizza-so i am not ready to give up yet...but will probably order take-out!
The Reuben sliders are the best.  Great food, great beer selection, and a casual atmosphere.  I'm coming back.
Great beer selection. Very friendly owner and wait staff. Shrimp was fantastic. The pizzas looked great. Can't wait to go back again.
Great fish fry (7 days a week) the B's Border Burger served with jalepenos, gauc, and pepper jack is best burger in Washington County!!!!

restaurant_name: Best Place At the Historic Pabst Brewery
review_text: One of the best historical tours in Milwaukee. Great efforts in preserving this brewery and adjacent buildings. Our guide was very enthusiastic and knowledgeable.

restaurant_name: Best Place At the Historic Pabst Brewery
review_text: This is truly The Best Place. Great staff. Awesome cafe. Their gift shop is like a beer museum. Organically started. Family owned.

restaurant_name: Best Place At the Historic Pabst Brewery
review_text: The tour at the Best Place was one of my favorites I have been on! It was unique in that it started in just one room with about 30 minutes about the history of beer and how PBR was involved in it, with a slide show of pictures. Our tour guide was awesome too, he had worked for PBR for a long time so was very knowledgeable and passionate. Anyone would really enjoy this tour!

restaurant_name: Best Place At the Historic Pabst Brewery
review_text: For those interested in Milwaukee brewing history, this can't be beat.

restaurant_name: Best Place At the Historic Pabst Brewery
review_text: Wow! The best beer history tour. Wunderbar! The owner spent time with our small group and made the visit very interesting. You have to go here!

restaurant_name: Best Place At the Historic Pabst Brewery
review_text: I love this place... I just love it. I'm pretty sure it's my happy place.
blechdirty and not friendlyvery toxic and not inclusiveseems cliquey and not welcoming unless you fit their expected type
Tati is my favorite bartender! She's make my drink's exactly like I like it in a timely manner. Big shout out to her & the brownstone family!!
I've been frequenting here since June & love the environment! Staff are AMAZING & the food is great! Definitely stop in if you can! Best,Ferrelle

My favorite place in Milwaukee. Great food, great drinks and the best hookah in town. This is the place to be. The staff is amazing they make you feel like family. The decor is beautiful and very upscale. Love it.

Me and a colleague visited this place a few months back and all i can say is  WOW!! small but what a vibe this place produces!! Black owned and supported by the locals this place has all you need! slammin DJs, Dope Bartenders, friendly Servers and a fantastic food Menu!! there were a few fan favorites that stood out besides the Owner/GM thats always on the scene makin sure everyones having a good time. there was one bartender who had nearly 100 safety Pins in her mask! shes AWESOME!!! she has a great Pour and very knowledgeable in drink making! id definitely chill here again or anytime im in Milwaukee
Very clean establishment, service on point,drinks on point, food was  delicious. Highly recommend .

Honestly what Milwaukee needs their is nothing like this place in the city. Quality cocktails, great service, the owner came over to greet us and ask about our experience. Reminds me of a lounge in DC so much! great to enjoy culture and intellectual conversation all in one. Will def be back every time I'm in the city!
Fantastic staff, shisha, and drinks.Highly recommend Wednesday night karaoke.The atmosphere is warm and human in downtown Milwaukee. It was a highlight of my stay.

This place for me lives up to its reviews my 1st experience will not be my last. The drinks, food, music, patrons, and staff were extremely friendly and professional. If you want a place to go for an all around great experience PLEASE VISIT BROWNSTONE, SPECIAL THANK YOU TO MANAGEMENT AND STAFF YOU GUYS WERE OSCAR WORTHY!!

OMG!!!!! My husband and I heard the ad on 98.3 and decided to check it out. What a great decision. They have happy hour from 4:00 pm - 7:00 pm....which consists of $5 wings, $5 martinis/wine, and $7 flatbread. I must say - NEITHER OF US WERE DISAPPOINTED. I want to give a special shout out to Free - she makes the best dirty martinis my husband has ever had. We will definitely go back. I had the mushroom flatbread - it was fresh and filling. The atmosphere was relaxing. The staff was great. Even the owner, Cory was great.
this place is gross . the owner acts like he's the shit .. I think this place need a health hazard check ..
What a big dump! They don't play music! You have to pay for music! It's so boring inside its unbelievable! This is a perfect place for an alcoholic. Cheers!

My favourite dive bar. A house cellar down the road complete with miniature pool, darts, jukebox, dog water bowl, plane bottle shots, year round vacation decor, popcorn machine, and your neighborhood friendly bartenders. Super kick butt chill place to love.
ok place

Won't be purchasing again until your company is not longer using X. This is not cool since the company supported Dems in the past. Time to stand up. And this is NOT about politics. X has become a sewer. Your company does not belong there. Especially with your home page text of support for the community.

Went to  Good City for the first time yesterday.  The staff was not friendly as we entered and ti took a while to be served after we found a seat.  I told the waitress that I had celiac and asked her about the gluten-free options.  The waitress told us that the fries were gluten-free and reassured me that they had a gluten-free dedicated fryer.    This was not the case because I got very sick after eating there.  The food was also mediocre.  My burger was dry and the bun fell apart.  My husband's greek salad has no salad dressing and the waitress never checked up on us so we could ask for some.  The beer was good but I would never go there to eat and I would warn anyone who is celiac that they should not eat here.  The waitress seemed to not understand the importance of cross-contamination for those with celiac and never checked to make sure she was correct about the state of the kitchen.  Overall, expensive for mediocre food and bad service.

During my road trip from Boston to LA, we figured we should check out some of the local breweries in Milwaukee. We hadn't eaten dinner yet, so we were trying to find breweries that served substantial food. After calling six different ones, we came across Good City Brewing!I can appreciate that this place had a full kitchen with a good amount of options for food -- more than just your typical pretzels and chips. The food wasn't amazing, but it was decent for brewery food and it did the job (not getting us too drunk too fast). I ordered a couple of the 5 oz tasters, which were good! Make sure to look at the board as they have beer specials that aren't printed on the menu.

Draft & Vessel Tosa meets at the intersection of modern design and old world charm.The property has impeccably well designed modern exteriors meshing wooden overhead trusses and dark metal beams extending out from the roof that visually connect two buildings on site.These buildings are split by an outdoor pathway that leads to a cool & hip patio in the rear. The patio is broken up into several seating areas separated by small plantings that create nicely appointed human scaled spaces. Visually, this space is anchored by a couple tear drop shaped bamboo chairs hung from an overhang connected to the main building.The main building is home to the largest of three indoor spaces and includes a near 40Ft long glazed wooden bar with a continuation of wooden trusses overhead and dark subway tile as a backdrop. They offer a great selection (20+?) of beers & adult beverages on tap.Booths & tables with oversized oak barrels to sit within, provide a backdrop similarly seen in many old brewery storage tunnels used to keep beers cold back in the day.The smaller building is across from the main building & split up into two rooms. The first is a retail / tasting room located towards the front of the property & has a massive selection of bottled & canned beers / cocktails / wines offered to go. The second room is towards the back of the property adjacent to the rear patio and is a perfect escape for a private venue.There is an open courtyard towards the front of Draft & Vessel that provides great outdoor seating and a perfect perch for people watching as folks walk to & from the Village.They don't offer food but did design a ramp that provides space enough for a food truck to roll up & into the open courtyard. I've been told those plans are in the works!This place is hip, it's cool, it's in perfect scale and it's incredibly welcome as the newest neighbor to our community!See you there!

BEWARE OF DOUBLE TIPPING.Two of us recently had a Friday fish fry. We have both eaten at Victor's for many years. The food was good, as usual. We especially love the loaf of baked bread that comes with every meal. But we noticed something unusual when the bill arrived. We had asked the server to split it in half and we were each paying with a credit card. We both like to pay the food amount with plastic and then pay the server's tip in cash (we both are generous tippers for good service, usually 20%). The two cash register receipts (each for half the total amount for the bill) were stapled on top of a carbon copy of the server's hand-written bill. So we each signed our copies and put down a 20% gratuity in cash (though we could also have written the tip on the cash register copies we signed). Luckily before the server took the receipts and cash tip we looked under the stapled receipts and found that the server had already added an 18% tip to the bill and had rung up the total due with that included. So in essence we would have tipped twice had we not noticed. Needless to say we quickly re-pocketed our cash. We were not happy with this "little trick." Is it even legal to write a gratuity on a bill for only two people? And should the server have alerted us to the practice, as it certainly was not printed on the menu? What if we chose to tip 15%?All this leaves a bad taste, and we certainly will think twice about going back.In the end the server got less, as we would have tipped 20%. Not good for the restaurant and not good for the server. Shame on Victor's.

$10 for cheese curds? No. $10 for 7 cheese curds and a plate of terrible French fries.
over rated!!!
Food was OK but service was horrible, do not recommend!
Now all beer and bar no more food really, it's become a live band spot with sticky floors and kinda nasty.
Average and slow. Very slow. I could have gone on a boat tour while waiting.
Decent food. Decent Beer. Service was also to par. Nothing really jumped out though.
Nice place for a burger and a brew.
great spot for brew and bands, it appears that food is no longer their main focus by looking at their ads.

Some friends and I went to Milwaukee Ale House for dinner recently.  It was a weekday, so even though we didn't have reservations we were seated quickly.Service was on-point throughout the meal; our server was both friendly and helpful with several spot-on recommendations :-)As expected, this place has a really good selection of draft beers on tap.  Not so expected (but very welcome) was the fact that they've also got cocktails and wine available.On to the food!As I'm still a relative newbie to the Milwaukee food scene, my friends and I got a couple of orders of cheese curds for the table, they did not disappoint!  They came out hot and delicious, pairing perfectly with our beer flights.  Other dishes that stand out in my memory were the buffalo chicken salad (VERY good) and the burgers (juicy, nicely seasoned, and cooked medium-rare exactly as requested).To summarize my first visit: Service was helpful and on-point, the food was really good, and the wide selection of draft beers ensured that we didn't depart for home thirsty ;-)I look forward to returning!
Great place. The beer was wonderful and bartender was very friendly and knowledgeable.

Stopped in for Mother's Day lunch.  Mothers received a complimentary Bloody Mary. Just the right amount of spice. Well done. Our server, Mike, was very friendly and on top of everything. Loved the humus pita wrap with chicken. Paired with the chips, it was delicious. Others at our table had the bbq pork sandwich and the black and blue burger. Enjoyed it all. Great food and friendly service. It's why we stop in when visiting Milwaukee.
Always great food and drinks! The weekly events are great and we usually are here for trivia on Wednesday's!
I find the people that go here and the people that work here are a dream! Very Nice all around wonderful experience! A+++
Decent food but great micro-brews

Awesome beer (just as I remember - except I missed happy hour by 8 minutes!). Great service. A really fun and classy group of bartenders. Pizza was really decent. Didn't knock my socks off but lots of flavor and certainly better than most all bar pizza (hint: it's not frozen pizza ;-)Had a good time and then headed out to patronize another 3rd Ward establishment so the swing dancers could take the floor!
Two Words: Veggie Wrap! I have yet to find a wrap as delicious as theirs!
Love coming here when were downtown. Love their GF pizza, Being GF is hard to dine out sometimes but this place is awesome

Milwaukee Ale House is one of my favorite restaurants in MKE! It has great food, amazing MKE Brewing Company Beer on tap, and a cool environment (my friend and I are convinced they have the best cheese curds in MKE). It is my go-to restaurant when I have visitors from out of town, and it never disappoints.
Great drink selection.....good food too!!!

Really really really good bloodys. The mix is perfect, thick but not too thick. The have a super nice patio---2 floors---and the menu was decent. Opted for grilled cheese and soup and a bloody that could definitely be for 2 people. Good recommendation!
Great place. Usually very busy, but never disappointed.

I love this place! One of my favorite bars in Third Ward. The food is bar food for sure but it's very delicious and not so processed like most bar food. Service is always good place is always busy right on the river and an awesome beer list
Very good beer and appetizers.

Came here after a Cubs and Brewers game, I'm from the Chicago area and I thought this was a pretty nice place, food was good, we sat out on the patio area along the River and there was a nice breeze, would definitely come here again sometime when I come up to Milwaukee.

I learned a valuable lesson on Saturday.  The Milwaukee Ale House is probably the BEST place in the city to watch a Badgers game.  The place was packed and the game was probably on at least a dozen TVs in the main room.  They also had a screen hanging above the stage and the game was projected on to it.  The crowd was really, REALLY into it.  The atmosphere and the energy was awesome.  It probably helped that Wisconsin won the game in a total blow out but I'm sure it's always that fun when the game is on.As far as food and drink goes, we had a few different Millwaukee brewing co beers that were great and a ton of fries and cheese curds which were also good.  I was a little suprised that the fries were pretty standard, mcdonalds-like fries.  I was hoping for something a little more substantial.
Good food & great beer.
