restaurant_name: The Fire Pit Sports Bar & Grill
review_text: My boyfriend and I used to go here all the time for the taco pizza. Seriously, it was amazing. We hadn't been there in some time because we generally only go for our birthdays which fall in late August and mid September. When we got there this time, the hostesses were too busy chit chatting with each other to seat us. When they finally noticed us, we were given a table and the standard dining experience started. Our waitress was nice. We didn't see our favorite item (our reason for coming) on the menu and were told it was removed long ago. We moved on and ordered the fish fry and the ceasar salad. It was my boyfriend's birthday so he eagerly bit into his fish which was breaded and fried cod. It was cold and pink in the middle. Biting into the raw fish turned his stomach and made him ill. The waitress was kind enough to have the cooks make a whole new plate but honestly, it was too late. My boyfriend is not the type to complain so I politely asked to speak to the manager who seemed less than concerned about our negative experience. A comp would have been nice, but an apology wasn't even given. The manager seemed irritated that I asked to speak with him. Very bland salad and raw fish... with a rude manager who made me feel like I was wasting his time by politely informing him of the raw fish means we most likely will not be returning. The restaurant was dead so there was no excuse for his attitude towards me.

restaurant_name: The Fire Pit Sports Bar & Grill
review_text: I challenge anyone to find a better burger than the BlackJack burger. You can't.

restaurant_name: The Fire Pit Sports Bar & Grill
review_text: Love this place! Amazing burgers and late night food! A perfect place to check out to watch your favorite game. I mean come on! They have over 30 TVs! Great diversity of beers too! Plus they have free music on Thursday, Friday and Saturday nights!
Great service.  Great food.  Wonderful environment. We will definitely be back. Friendly bartenders !
Great atmosphere and even better food.
Game machines are nicer than most people in the area and they have really good food.
Great food and free pool......................

Be warned. What used to be a pleasant bike riding stop, has been infected with Trumpism. They prohibit masks and literally say, "if you're wearing a mask we will treat you like a robber". So the failure to commit to public health practices is supplemented with a commitment to violence. So welcoming. Makes you wonder if a place doesn't believe in communicable disease, what's the state of the kitchen? Do they allow their staff to wash their hands? I'd steer clear.

We've been to Brass Tap a few times now and each experience has been pretty good.  The service has been prompt and friendly each time we've been here, whether seated at the bar or a table, even when it was really busy, so that's a huge plus.  There's a huge selection of draft beer, almost all American craft beer, much of it local.  I'd prefer some more European / Belgian beer options, but that's just me.  There's lots of bottled options too.  The cuisine is acceptable bar food, nothing mind-blowing but pretty decent.  Prices aren't too bad.  Good place to stop for a bite and some brews you may not have tried before.
Great selection of beers on rotation. Friendly staff. Food is the 4 out of 5.
Great service. Great beer selection. Awesome food. What more can I say?   I can't wait to come back again, definitely a place that you should bring your family to.
A lunch regular for me and the office! Foods always great and waiters are attentive! Love the atmosphere.

Stopped by here while on a business trip.  The atmosphere was perfect, food and drinks were on point both on taste and price point.  Staff was amazing, Krystal took care of us.  She was funny and reccomended a few places to check out before leaving. The staff there is like family and keep the place entertained.  One girl even broke out the flossing dance!  If we are ever back we will be coming back!
The beer selection is amazing! The food and the service is great! There is always something going on there. They have tons of different events weekly. It's so much fun!

Went there with my girlfriend and we had a blast.  Beer selection was great and the staff was super friendly.  Our Bartender Krystal was so much we didn't want to leave.  Cant wait to go back. Thanks for the great service guys!

A hidden gem! 80 beers on tap, and you can taste before you commit to an entire pint. Great food and service in an atmosphere suited for any age. Live music on the weekends, fun events (bingo, trivia, etc) and happy hour during the week. I always recommend The Brass Tap to friends and Family.
Best Beer Selection Around!! Food was great!!

LOVE THIS PLACE!  Our Server, Annie, was excellent in bringing us lots of taps to try.  So many taps, so little time!  The food was great too!  So many places have horrible servers - I must say Annie is a GEM!

Wow... I can't say enough about this place! Aside from the obvious... BEER (80 taps and over 100 bottles, with new ones added daily!?) there are so many other reasons my wife and I visit at least twice a week. I'll start with the atmosphere. As I already said, my wife and I visit at least twice a week. Usually Mondays for trivia and Friday or Saturday, occasionally enjoying live music. I've also had a few business lunch meetings during the week. Lastly, "The Tap" has become my go-to for Packer games, due to the free TD shots and Jersey giveaways. I can't think of any other place in town that I can enjoy myself for 3 completely different purposes. It's really an all-purpose tavern. That brings me to my next topic... the service. No matter if it's a packed house on Friday night, or a handful of people eating lunch on a Wednesday afternoon, we've always received prompt, friendly service. I don't know where they find these bartenders, but the knowledge they have of beer, local breweries or international ones, is impressive to say the least. The servers must be treated well, because they legitimately look happy to be there. Which is more than I can say for a lot of the national chains in the area. The owner is frequently behind the bar or taking tables, and, although I'm embarrassed to say I can't remember his name :/, he always, no matter how busy, takes time to stop and welcome us back. I've heard a couple employees say that he even does dishes when the kitchen gets backed up (what OWNER does that!?) On to the best part.. THE FOOD!!! I can't decide if my favorite is the prime rib sandwich, the fish fry, or the chicken tenders. The latter two have been revamped recently with the new menu (I'll get to that). They batter them in house in a beer batter. I've tried to squeeze the recipe out of some employees but either they don't know, or aren't telling. They rolled out a new menu a couple months ago that is quite diverse. They've added some healthier options like a Quinoa dish and lettuce wraps to name a few, my wife is into that kind of thing, I'll stick with the more traditional options. Almost forgot the burgers. I was always a Red Robin fan and I prefer them here. I recommend the Pub.I didn't plan to be this long winded, but this place is doing everything right. Only negative, (if you can call it that) is it does get rather crowded. I'd love to see them expand some day in the future.

I visited here on a thursday night for the first time. The selection of beers were awesome, and the servers made sure to make sure I wasn't left with an empty glass for to long. I have yet to try the food yet, I am saving that for my next visit. If your looking for a chill place to have a good beer I defiantly recommend Brass Tap!
One of the biggest and best beer selections in town. Foods pretty fantastic as well!
Worst bartenders ever!! Unfriendly and slow!! We won't be back.
Enjoyed the night with my friends, finished a lot  of bottled wine and beers. This place was extremely nice!

Blackbird has an amazing happy hour specials, that go daily. They've lots of chairs and a lot of board games. It is interesting to go with a group of 6 or so individuals and play apples to apples while appreciating $2 riverwest stein.
Never had a bad time to be had.

It's would be a great place if they didn't allow dogs into the bar. And a lot of peopletake advantage of this. Way too many dogs. I don't think it should be legal to have any animals in a drinking establishment, especially one that serves food (pizza).

I was happily seen here by a friend while I was on holiday. Art Bar is amazing! If I had this spot in DC, I Had almost live here. Alcohol, java, ACTUAL ARTWORK, as well as a friendly staff. What more could I ask for? Oh, yeah, cool customers. Test. It is an excellent little spot to go using a sketchbook.
One of a kind. Must experience once so you can say you have lived a full live. It's whatmakes the area so unique. Try it!
Love the full vibe. The beers are great, the guy next to me says he knows or worked with the pizza guy and I told him to give him a high five!
Still love this place! I love coming here on Tuesday, for brunch, you name it. Check it out.
This is one of my favorite bars in Milwaukee. Great atmosphere and a diverse selection of beers.
A very progressive and fun place! I love everything about it. Great staff!!
Becky is the best bartender in the world
Not for us.  Limited selection but the dessert was yummy.  Would not recommend.  Not comfortable seats.
Super small plates, super high price. Go elsewhere if you want to leave full. Wine and beer selection is good, but not worth ordering off their menu for it
Didn't have any of the whiskey I choose off thier menu. The specials were tasty. Service was friendly but they could be more consistent having whats offered.

The place itself has lots of different tones of beautiful wood from walls to floor. Gorgeous to look at and very barn house chic feeling. Our kids ordered the cheese flatbread (waaay better than the typical kid's meal pizza option) and the berry crepe with vanilla sauce (basically dessert ).Excellent choice for breakfast on Sunday. Having the ability to put my name on the wait list as we were driving to the restaurant was nice. Great service.
Decent food, but it doesn't live up to the hype you hear about it. Would recommend getting their early to avoid a wait.
Thoughtful creations and presentation of all foods and cocktails.
It took a while to get our food but when we did it was fantastic!
Story Hill is pretty damn good.
Delicious and beautiful brunch. Will return!

We loved everything about this place. We went there for breakfast. The food was delicious, made with fresh ingredients, and there were inventive things on the menu like the crepe-urrito and dolsot (a Korean bowl dish) along with "comfort" items like gingerbread and omelettes. Service was attentive. The place is cozy. It is a combination wine & beer store, cafe, and bar, divided into three parts--but it works. We will be back.

This place is a must try. Only have been there once but was very impressed with the food and the service. Pork was amazing. The fish with the egg on top, not so much, but still very well done so I still rate it quite high. Will be back soon to try more!

My first visit to BKC was for breakfast. I had the SHAKSOUKO which I have no idea what it's definition is but it was a tasty dish with baked eggs over a somewhat spicy tomato sauce and goat cheese, sumac mayo, lentils, and a very generous portion of fresh leafy cilantro. It comes with flatbread. I am a potato head so I also ordered the CRUSHED SPUDS which are not crushed at all despite their name but are whole potatoes with seasoning and some sort of oil...truffle oil maybe? Anyway..I enjoyed all of it. Usually breakfast potatoes are greasy hadhbrowns and these were a delightful alternative. My cheese and orune busquit was average but the Rosemary apple butter was quite good. Place was clean and comfortable. Our server was there for us to answer questions and keep the coffee coming. I will be back very soon to try more unique dishes.
A very nice Happy Hour experience. Foods very good& many drinks are offered.Servers are friendly&helpful.
avocado toast is the best thing on the menu! I wish they offered the soup and sides on the weekend brunch menu. still one of the best hidden gems.

This restaurant is designed for anyone who enjoys food and great cocktails. We tried the cocktail flight and they were all delightful. We had escargot, beef tartare, pork schnitzel, salmon, cauliflower .. and more. Every dish was perfect. If we had one suggestion it would be to have less salt on the pretzel bread.... But then again, that's a matter of taste. The server explained the dishes well and spent time at the table explaining everything. All the staff were great. Kitchen staff were also accessible and interested in our experience. I'm definitely going back when I am in the area next!

I have never had a bad experience here. Food is delicious and always made well, staff is friendly, welcoming and accommodating, and the restaurant itself is clean and a warm atmosphere. Always a go to, especially when friends and family visit.

A fun and funky atmosphere, and they had some unique options. The service was excellent. I did six small plates and was impressed with my torta, although the mayo flavor did get a bit overpowering towards the end, the first time for dinner. We will be back.
This is definitely one of our favorite restaurants in the Milwaukee Area. The food is always creative, classy and delicious.
Wonderful food and great service. The food is fresh and delicious. Highly recommended! Thank you for everything!
If you go there get the rolls because the bread at this place is soooooooo good. Good food good place.
Went there for lunch and had a great experience. There were four of us. The waiter was friendly and helpful. The food and drinks were great. Everyone enjoyed what they ordered.

I should've come in here early. I wasted a lot of my money in extravagant restaurants with average food. This is a place where you get quality food at an average price. I am coming here again. All these high priced restaurants these days are having this "All show no go " kinda attitude but this place has great food.
Love the food and the staff are very friendly! Also, you gotta get the cinnamon rolls, they're great!
i,m happy this bar is open even though the coronavirus out but it is good I love it

This is a late review from a few months ago.  We took another couple and we were all delighted .   We all ordered various choices ,incl. beets,which were delicious.      We shared our various plates, sipped wine and Manhattans and left raving about our unusual dinner.  Our servers were very patient and certainly knew the menu.         We have also had a delicious Sunday Brunch!   Great restaurant.  We are also great fans and supporters of Blues Egg.  We are fortunate to have such outstanding restaurants  in Tosa and Milwaukee.  Thanks.  PS  great loyal servers.
Excellent food and outstanding service. Best service I have received in a few years. Definitely will be going back when in town.
Excellent food, friendly service! Beautiful atmosphere
Great find! Stopped by just as they were opening to get a meal.  Great service and the food was fantastic!
It is hard to beat the Crepes Monsieur! Crepes, excellent ham, pickles, and dijonais sauce! Unfortunately, I have not tried much else, as this is my go-to favorite. (Go Bucks!)
Professional staff, impressive food, never had a bad experience or mimosa even when slammed.

I have to eat Gluten Free and this place doesn't disappoint. The creperito is delicious. It is slightly spicy, but its so nice to be out and get a delicious meal that is carb-y but still safe for me to eat. The servers are all really nice, dressed well, and happy. Very refreshing experience every time we dine.

Awesome crepes! And so much more!This is in my neighborhood so I have been here many times. I do recommend that you try it for both breakfast/brunch AND dinner as the menus are very different. Breakfast menu has a lot of specialty crepes, of which I have never had one I didnt like! Dinner menu is more small/shared plates with some really unique options. I most recently was here on Sunday for the Crepe Monsieur which features their delicious pulled ham on the inside and the right amount of pickles for that little added somethin' somethin'. The service is always great and they have an awesome little liquor store inside that sells a surprisingly unique and diverse selection of wine, craft beer, and liquor. Check this place out when you have the chance! Use the "no wait" app to get your place in line if it's during peak hours as there isn't much waiting room inside.
Great food and service staff is attentive, food is fresh and the location is great. Plenty of natural light and a great lunch environment.
Awesome. You should go. The food was amazing.

We have eaten there several times! Food is very good and staff is very friendly and receptive to your needs!
I can't believe my unforgettable experience of this place. Nice place to be. I will be visiting g with friends sometime soon.
Excellent food and interesting decor. We have been here a couple of times and every time is enjoyable experience

I really appreciate their appetizers. The quality of their food and drinks are amazing! I got two of their flights and it was plenty for two people! The beer was great and the cocktails were as well. I would recommend this place to anybody who loves quality, fresh food and drink!
Awesome experience! Every plate was amazing and with a cool laid back dining experience you can't go wrong!

This is exactly what you call as real food. First time i came here, was properly entertained and offered to choose a great food for me. The staffs really knew what they are offering and talking about.
Just delicious!  as well as excellent service!

The food is excellent. This is definitely my favorite place for lunch in the Wauwatosa area. The prices are reasonable and the service is consistently good. There is usually street parking available nearby.
Everything I have ever eaten here has been fun and unique and not to mention: fresh!  It's worth the wait.

I brought my mother here when I moved to the neighborhood. I didn't know what to expect but was completely blown away. The service and coffee was fantastic and the food was out of this world. Best brunch in town!

Just recently saw DH and The Movement at The Rave. We drove up from Chicago and spent the weekend. I previously heard some positive things about the place and wanted to give it a shot. Unfortunately, this was by far the worst concert venue I've ever been to. I think any individual that actually gives this dump a positive review has never truly experienced a good concert. First off, the acoustics are horrible, absolutely awful. Vocals were nearly impossible to pick up. I understand you can make the argument that it's an old building, but the right amount of money and technology will fix anything. At $5 a 6oz water and $9 a beer, you would think the venue would have enough money to upgrade.  We purchased "VIP" balcony tickets. The fine print stated that the balcony seats were first come first serve. We understood that and arrived early only to find that there were no seats available. About 60% of the seats we're reserved, which was not stated when purchasing the tickets. So the venue sells these "VIP" balcony tickets but then reserves most of the seats. We tried to speak with the box office and security staff to see how to purchase these reserved seats and they had no idea, all I received were blank dumbfounded looks and answers like "they're reserved". Yeah, no shit, all I want to know if it's possible to purchase a section. Also, if you're going to charge me $5 for water, actually pour me the entire bottle. I ordered two bottles, the "bartender" poured barely one and a half of them into two small cups. I proceeded to grab the remaining half filled bottle to finish it, and she snatched it from me like I was a maniac. She said I couldn't have it, I guess a half filled plastic bottle was a danger to other concertgoers. I'm used to spending money on concerts and understand mark up costs, but this lacked common sense.The Rave is a heaping pile of garbage that should be remodeled or torn down completely. Save your money and see a show at the House of Blues, Red Rocks, or The Greek.

However, if you enjoy tortuous sound quality, clueless managers, and paying nine dollars for a Bud Light in the city of Milwaukee, Wisconsin, then this venue is your Garden of Eden.

(I cant hear what ya say?) what the fuck dude (punched), (you wanna fuck around bitch"" backhanded) and when i finally got sick of being hit and kicked and punched I was like your'a fucking pussy man, ahahaha u have to jump a 19-teen year old? and he kicked me in the balls!! and they walked away as I was lifeless in there parking lot for agood 5-10 mins laying there....THE RAVE IS HORRIBLE. ITS SUCHA JOKE, I HONESTLY GIVE IT NEGATIVE -5 Stars and any parents out there thinking it'l be a safe enviroment, its not. Body Gaurds will punch and attack your siblings.

Fuck this place. Fuck it right in its carny ass. If you like this place, you're either stupid or from out of town. If you're at this place, you're either stupid, from out of town, work there (sorry), or the band you came to see is too stupid to book at a venue that doesn't feel like a trailer park was shaken over it and everything that fell out filled the place to its claustrophobic limit. Hey, want to get in the show for free? There are always free tickets all over town! And in your mail box! And under your windshield wipers! What's that you say? Two drink minimum? No problem. The Chicago Syndicate owners have seen fit to only charge you $11 per drink. How nice of them! Good luck pissing if you're a guy. They have approximately 1 urinal for every 64,000 concertgoers. I imagine it's not much better for the ladies, but if you're a lady, you shouldn't be at The Rape/Eagles Club. Go home. Or to Victor's. It's less likely you'll get roophied there. The security staff fucking hates you. They will feel up your underbits looking for your flask, pipe, or switchblade that you were going to stab DJ Funk with. Don't worry, there's plenty of parking in the safe, well-lit neighborhood surrounding The Rape. No more than 3 friends have had their windows smashed and stereos ripped off, so your odds are pretty good. The cops LOVE to come help you out at the edge of the hood after a few thousand drunks pour into the streets, so make sure you call them if/when your car gets got. They'll be there in a jiffy! One thing I'll share, if you're sneaky, you can find an unlocked door on the balcony level of the ballroom when the shows are downstairs. After you come down from the roof after your smoke break, wait till the stoned high school dropout security guard by the pissers fucks off for whatever reason. Jump the half-assed barrier stopping you from going out onto the balcony. Start opening doors (be quiet). You can find your way to the catwalk above the ceiling, it's cool.  There may be bodies or drugs or cash stashed up there, who knows? Also, the far stairs on the other side of the balcony will lead you directly to the backstage area of The Rape. There's fucking tape arrows on the floor that say "back stage" and "busses". So go meet Vince Neil or that goon from Hinderback or whatever. Tell 'em Large Marge sent ya!

Anyone who's been there before knows it's a real dump and probably thinks twice about buying tickets to any show there.  I went to the Umphrey's McGee show last night only to find out that it's gotten even worst than before.  Let's face it - it's located in the hood.  I was able to find street parking, but had to walk on broken glass almost the entire way to the building.  Lots of rednecks speeding up and down the streets in their beater cars.  Got in the building and went through the so-called security search, only to have a security guard tell my date that she had to take a container of VITAMINS back to the car, so we did.  Went through again and made it.  Got upstairs and sat down in the VIP balcony, only to have some fat-ass security guard tell us we had to move because that was the owner's box.  No signs posted indicating that.  They probably don't post it intentionally so they can spend all night running people out of their seats.  During the show, the owner (I'm assuming) showed up and sat in the box next to us and the whole time, 2-3 other fat-ass security guards had fun shining their super-duper flashlights on people in the crowd.  I still have no idea why, other than to harass people.  One guard was so fat, I swear I thought his gut was going to pull him over the rail and crashing into the sound/lighting equipment below.  If you think this is a smoke free environment - forget it.  The smoke (legal and illegal) was horrible.  How could they have searched anyone properly with that much weed getting past them?  I was ready to get the hell out of there well before the show was over.  If you do go to a show, get ready to be treated like a criminal by a bunch of fat guys who have obviously never done a sit-up in their miserable lives.
still awful after all these years.

I've been to the Rave twice, once 2 years ago to see Primus and this past Saturday to see Korn.  Let me also add that my boyfriend and I live in Charlotte, NC and have flown both times to see these bands b/c neither were coming anywhere near us.  The Primus show was overall great and we were on the floor.  This time he paid BIG $$$ to have VIP seats on the upper level so we'd have actual seats.  We arrived an hour early to get drinks and veg b4 the show only to discover there were only about 100 VIP seats for first come arrivals for well over 1,000 people even though we had seat numbers printed on our tix and no warning about getting there early to secure an actual seat.  AND, the dumbass owner had 2 sections, right in the front middle RESERVED for him and his friends.  The opening band was so bad that the crowd was screaming at them to get off the stage, in much more graphic terms though, and Korn went on at least an hour after the opening band had ended their set.  (Seriously Jonathan?  Are you really that much of a prima donna or were you busy getting blow-jobs in the back?)  His vocals were drowned out and if you didn't actually know the words to their songs you'd have no idea what he was singing.  Lastly, it was so freaking hot in that place that it was like a portal to HELL and I had to call paramedics for my boyfriend that started having medical issues because of the heat, lack of seating and possibly kidney probs.  WE WILL NEVER GO BACK NOR WILL MANY OF THE PEOPLE THAT WERE AROUND US THAT WE TALKED WITH THAT FELT THE SAME WAY!!!  Oh and to the blond 'security' guard that thought he was the shit in the VIP section, telling people to not crowd the people that actually got a place to sit b/c they would need to get up to get drinks, GET A REAL JOB!!!  I'm not a violent person but you were seriously close to getting a beat-down for your very rude and uncool attitude!
Great venue.  But exceptionally rude Security. I witnessed numerous physical assaults on dancing concert goers.

This place really sucks, I am sorry, why the fuck are miller lites $7.50?!?!?!?! And mixed rails are $8???? Who is in charge of pricing drinks, Bernie Madoff?Also why the hell are the bouncers so stupid? I worked the door at a couple places, worked with some real yams, but these guys were tator tots. You can't remember I was just upstairs and now I am going downstairs? I hate shitty bouncers, the job is so easy. And they did nothing to stop illegal behavior from happening. Not that I am trying to narc or anything, but dude, your like 5 deep in the entrance where nobody is chilling but upstairs (which is pretty awesome BTW) where there are 50+ 19 year olds doing whipits, there is no fat moron with an orange security shirt.But the only reason this place gets 2 stars instead of 1 is the cool ass upstairs on the roof area. Its is realy nice, all stone 2 un covered areas for smokers, and a bar. There was a killer dance floor where I shook my ass. But everything else sucks, seriously, including the neighborhood. I never go the sense that I was going to get robbed, but I did feel like the element hanging outside have been preying on white kids from Wisco & their cars for decades, so that may be a problem the Milwaukee PD should handle, but I digress.Everything else sucks. The schedule was so hard to understand I almost missed the godamn headliner. I feel bad for those living in Milwaukee, cuz this is probably the biggest place around & the only exposure a lot of people get to Wisco. I remember seeing Ween here like 8 years ago and it was not that bad, but then again I was not Yelp elite then so I was not so cynical.
The atmosphere is great, but there is way too much mosh pitting. Also it can get really really hot!

Okay so I've been to the rave for many many concerts for like rap and various artists. Im 15 and just me and my girlfriends went and we felt safe the entire time. The security was over extensive and a little annoying at times, even making me throw things out of my purse. Rarely did I see fights going on and when I did security kicked them out rather quickly. Love the rave and will be going back asap!!!
Ok

seen a ton of shows here! always a good crowd. The drinks are a lil pricie but where arent they. I seen a guy get kicked out for trying to tie peoples shoes. the sound is pretty good upstairs, not so much for metal shows down though.

I saw Five Finger Death Punch in the ballroom...it was AWESOME!!! I've been to maaaaaany shows at the rave, and this one was the best. They have really made a lot of improvements. The penthouse smoking area is really cool, the bathrooms are nice, and, maybe I was lucky, but all of the staff that i talked to were really nice. And FYI, those 2 drink minimum tickets are WORTH IT!!! Dude, you're not even paying full price, and getting two drinks with it....and to the people bitching about "extra fees"...EVERY PLACE DOES IT!!! Get over it. It's part of the business.Yes, i think everyone agrees that drink prices are little crazy. I paid $8 for a drink at the Mid in chicago. So, I can't complain too much. But,  when you reeeeeally want a beer, $8 bucks isn't gonna stand in your way!My advise...If a band you love is playing at the rave, go see them. Have fun. Don't let other people, or drink prices ruin your night. You're going for the music anyway!!!

Parking sucks, drinks are expensive, bathrooms are dirty, staff is rude...what more could you possibly want when you go to a show?  A bathroom attendant?  Guided tour?  Come on people!  The Rave is a great place to see a show.  If you're looking for special service then go to Applebee's.Oh yea...Did you sneak downstairs after Cold War Kids??  Ice Cube was sick right!

Ok. So...I like The Rave!!! It's actually a REALLY great venue! I've been to a ton of shows there. All of my favorite bands have played there. The building is HUGE. They have like 7 different stages...all of which sound awesome. The ballroom is the best though...eveyone should experience a show in the ballroom. Girl Talk was AWESOME!!!! People (including myself) were having so much fun! And as far as drink prices go....has anyone been to bars in Chicago lately?!?!? The Rave's prices are actually fairly reasonable. Yes, the building does need an ATM...It's cold now, and I really don't wanna walk across the street to get money...so bring cash with you!!! AND!!! The smoking lounge off of the ballroom balcony!!!....You can see the whole city...and there's a bar up there with TVs so you don't miss the show!!! Woot woot!! Really cool addition to the building!!! GO RAVE GO!! FYI: Don't do stupid shit, and you won't get kicked out :)
Been going here for years, and still love it! Acoustics are amazing here. Place is pretty clean. The history of it is what makes it great! Look forward to seeing many more shows here.

Oh The Rave! What can I say about you? I've been attending shows here for over 6 years and have yet to experience anything terrible. Unless you count the occasional inebriated patron, but you get that any where there is being alcohol being served.  You can hardly blame that on the business.My first show at The Rave was The Blood Brothers back in 2006, I had just moved to Milwaukee and it is one of my favorite concerts to date.  The crowd was super into the music, they immediately scooped up any one that fell, and were just generally pleasant to be around.Since the first time I attended a show here the building has seen numerous improvements. Many of bathrooms have been remodeled, the basement is now a great red color, you can watch the concert at almost any bar via closed circuit television and they opened the penthouse lounge, which is absolutely gorgeous during the summer!  It's a great building and it's unique in the Midwest, I look forward to see what they change next!After reading many reviews on here, I feel like most people would have avoided their frustrations had they been prepared.  If I'm attending a place I have never been before, especially a concert venue, I always Google or call to find out what I need to get my tickets and if I need cash beforehand. If a place serves alcohol....it's usually better to just assume you need cash.No place is without its faults, but I have had nothing but great experiences there.  I really enjoy The Rave and will continue to see shows there for as long as I live in Milwaukee.

The Rave is the best music venue in Milwaukee.  They have the best concerts year round.  Ticket prices are always fair and comparable (if not cheaper) to tickets for the same show in Chicago.  Plus, their tap beer is soo good.  Tastes soo much better than bottled beer for some reason.For a good time, come to the Rave for a concert.

The Rave is one of my favorite venues ever!! Great sound, great staff, and most importantly, great music! They book a wide variety of acts, which sets it apart from most venues in the area. The building itself is pretty awesome as well. Highly recommended!

Food was bland and bag was soaking in grease when delivered. I used to really like this place but the prices have gotten so high and the portions have gotten so much smaller that I cant justify this place as my go-to anymore. The staff was always good and it's a nice environment overall, but my Shepard's Pie had so little flavor and veggies that I ended up seasoning it at home. The lamb was gamey as well, which is something I've never experienced with lamb before. The veggies were a big draw for me as well, but I seldom found a piece. Also, I had no clue it was topped with cheese (I don't handle dairy well so that's why I ordered it) so that was a turn off as well. Ugh.
It's a bar.  Not great, not bad, just a bar.

This place has surprisingly good food.  We end up stopping by quite frequently in the summer, and we continue to be impressed by the solid the food and service.  It's pretty unassuming, but definitely a good choice for a beer and a bite to eat.
Great place uptown to have amazing food, great drink selection and teeriffic service. Bar tended by authentic charming Brit. Really good music all night!
Its a great spot to stop on my way home from work.
Great food. Great service. Authentic and fun! Great spot to watch a game, have dinner, or grab a drink with friends. True gem!

Bringing the British Pub feeling of being comfortable in a community living room. International staff, Voted Best Pub Food in Milwaukee a number of time in Shepherd Express, On Milwaukee, M Mag, etc, great scratch cook food with British options including the usual, plus Sausage Rolls, Sticky Toffe Pudding, Pasties, Steak and Ale Pies, and also plenty of traditional American style options too.Hosts many different events, specials,  and continues to add new things, such as expanding into new space, Patio, Parklet, Game Room, Fireplace with leather Chesterfield couches, Steal tip darts, Pool Table, interesting collections from Britain, a lot of great soccer memorabilia, and staff from all over the world.

My fiancé and I stopped in to check it out as a possibility for hosting our small wedding reception as they do private events, and we were not disappointed. I ordered their Bloody Mary for my drink and it was quite delicious, probably one of the best that I've had. We got an order of scotch eggs and those were awesome. My fiancé ordered the Reuben which he said was very tasty, I didn't try it since I'm not a sauerkraut fan. I got the Lions Feast burger. If you go to this pub do yourself the biggest favor you've ever done for yourself in your entire life and order this burger. Seriously. Do it. It was by far the BEST burger I've ever had. It was this super thick patty of ground up, chipotle seasoned, onion ring topped awesomeness with a side of chips. The pub itself is nice and clean, played some pretty decent music, and our server was attentive, friendly, and just all around a good guy. I would absolutely go back there.
Consistent and also holds the neighborhood together!
great pub!  try to eat here whenever i'm on this side of town.  everything on the menu is great, especially fish friday.  especially love the accents
Awesome bartender

Great Place, Great People, Great Food and more importantly Great Beer!!!Love this place. I am always in there, whether it is for a few swift ones, or all of the night! Great atmosphere, good crowd and always a good time!Eaten most things on the menu and I can't say that I am disappointed. I have heard a lot of people saying the same thing. I am a massive fan of the fish 'n' chips and the chicken curry, which never fails to satisfy my tastebuds! I know there is more to be added to the menu, like Shepherd's Pie and, Bangers and Mash, so I am looking forward to that. Staff there are fantastic, welcome you as soon as you walk in the door with an "ello mate" and a welcoming smile on their faces. Great option for the people of Shorewood as it is in a very convenient spot for most people.My advice to you all would be to GET INVOLVED, THE THREE LIONS IS THE PLACE TO BE!!!!!

In the six years I've lived in Milwaukee I have never been to a bar that makes me feel more welcome than Three Lions Pub. From day one, the employees have gone above and beyond to ensure everyone who walks through their doors has a great experience. The beauty of Three Lions is that it's perfect for every outfit, occasion or mood. Dressed up or down, in a group or alone, you'll never feel out of place. In fact, I feel just as at home there as I do in my own living room.Whether you're going for the karaoke, trivia, wonderful bartenders or the newly opened kitchen, Three Lions will not disappoint. Shorewood is lucky to have them.

Definitely the place to be ! Great atmosphere, great music and great beer!They recently started serving food and I have nothing but positive things to say about it ! The Fish and chips is just the best and I recommend it to all! It is the talk of my neighbourhood and my husband can't get enough of the Strongbow!The quiz night which is held on Thursday's is a great time and should not be missed!Finally, the staff here make the place ! Very friendly and pleasant!
Cool place to hang on a Thursday night-bike night.  It was cold the night we were there but none the less, pretty cool.

terribly rude staff.  the things that he just said to my fiance today were some of the worst things i've ever heard one human say to another.  we will never visit this bar for a drink again.  plenty of other wonderful places to have a drink in bay view.

I've been to the Highbury a couple of times for karaoke - over Labor Day weekend this past year and another time this fall. I had a lot of fun both times! The environment, the crowd, the drinks, and the karaoke selection were all great. However, I went with a few friends last night and experienced a complete 180. The karaoke DJ was still great, but everyone else in the bar... Man, be careful. If you go for karaoke on Sundays, here are a couple tips. 1) Don't try to sing along with those at the mic! They won't consider it a compliment; they'll consider it a challenge. And I'm not talking American Idol kind of challenge, like you sing then I try to sing better. More of the glare from across the bar and harass you and make you feel uncomfortable and unsafe because for whatever reason, they don't like you. That kind of challenge. I can't remember the last time I felt that much animosity from total strangers in public. All because we were singing along and they thought we were mocking them. 2) Use cash. That way, if you need to get out, you can do so immediately. It took forever to close out our tab, mostly because one of the bartenders simply refused out of wanting to be an asshole to us. There was definitely a homophobic and sexist vibe to this bar. Which is disappointing because I really wanted to make it my new karaoke spot!

I can't even bring myself to give this place one star. That would be an insult to stars. But I have to (thanks Yelp).The Highbury represents all that is dark and evil in the world. I'm fairly certain ISIS hates Americans because they stopped here for about five seconds. The bar, upon entering, emits the rancidness you'd expect from your toilet the day after a Taco Bell binge combined with the sweaty armpit of Lyle Alzado minutes after smashing a car on his worst 'roid rage night. If I was allowed to define "pungent" in the dictionary, I would say it's "the best case scenario at the Highbury on a Saturday morning". Speaking of Saturday mornings... if you like Futbol, and I do, this place will be open to come and endure the game. Note, I didn't say "enjoy" the game, and I barely said "watch" the game. The air of shame coming from the clientele for lowering their standards to drink here and watch soccer, combined with the tight spaces and sardine-can quality of how many people they pack in leads me to head straight to the nearest bidet to wash the musky goo off my bottom from all the man-junk pressed against me when so many people are pushing forward toward the bar to buy the over-priced rail drinks and Campbell's Tomato Soup Bloody Mary's. Psychologists must make a fortune from the mental health issues coming from all the people who've had to walk through the gauntlet of turgid Manchester United fans after they score a goal. Thankfully that's a rare occasion this season.  I'm pretty sure when you order a Miller Lite here in a bottle, you get the tiny leavings of a hundred previous customer's bottles all funneled into yours with a topper of seltzer to give it bubbles. I have no proof of this, but let me just say the Miller Lite here makes Natty Ice taste like Dom Perignon. The ATM in the bar is a joke and a half too. With fees like that, you'd think the bar owner is getting a major kickback per transaction, or works for the ATM company, or both. Speaking of the bar owner, I don't think I've met a more incorrigible self-righteous asshat in my life. I think he's been sober once in his life, and that was because there's no booze in amniotic fluid. Usually he's stumbling around his domain, scratching his little bits, and muttering about how "back in the day when he had hair" business was much better. Don't get me started on the bartenders. I thought this was a service industry, boy was I mistaken. This Scottish tosser was there slinging drinks... to his buddies... and essentially ignored everyone else. Let me correct myself, "ignored" would have been an upgrade to the treatment I fell victim to. I ordered a bottle of beer with a pop off top, and instead of using the bottle opener, he threw the bottle at my head and said SOMETHING in that godawful accent of his that I THINK translated to "USE YOUR HANDS AND MAKE THEM BLEED IF YOU WANT TO DRINK IT!" Which, when your breath reeks of haggis, really just adds to the aroma. I may quit drinking thanks to this place. Or even worse, I may buy two bottles of Malort, sit in a corner and guzzle them down until I can't remember ever having been there. It's Malort, so it will be hell, but at least not the lowest circle this bar spawned from.

This place is the height of obnoxiousness. It has to be the only Man Ure bar named for an ARSEnal stadium. It isn't big enough for the number of people that come for USA matches and while they sing, everyone is off-key. The only saving grace is the female bartenders are attractive, but that's offset by the guys that make Rowan Atkinson look like Fabio.Also...chalkboards suck. What is this, preschool?

Highbury is a little pub smack in the heart of the Bay View KK strip. It is a great place to watch a football (soccer) match if you don't mind standing. Getting a seat during a big game can be a challenge. Seems to have a lot of "regulars" which is good or bad, depending on your preference. The live music on weekends has never suited my style and can be a bit too loud for the size of the place. But again, this is a matter of preference. No food there, but a great selection of bottled beers and a full bar. Decent enough for a drink or a speciality place for soccer.
I like the selection of beers. Totally my kind of place.  Only probem its a bit too sporty for my liking.

This is my favorite spot to watch soccer. Nice selection of beer, and always a friendly and fun crowd here. I keep meaning to stop by for a drink some evening, but never find myself there.I still would like to see what the nightlife is like here.
Best bar in Milwaukee, hands down.
Come for the footie.  This is the place to be.
Best place to watch a game. Football, soccer, doesn't matter. Joe the owner is always trying new inventive ways to feed and entertain people and he does a great job at it.
Closed for business and run down!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!! This place is closed. Like do not enter, do not pass go.
What happened to the Irish music at Paddy's Pub? It used to be a lively place; bring back a taste of Ireland, please.

Admittedly this is my personal favorite. Decor may seem touristy, but is authentic. Irish import taps. May be a bit more for a drink but sitting in Paddy's leaves you no question as to why. Slightly awkward to navigate through. Lots of separate seating, not to loud to talk, intimate on good scale. Bartenders always smiled and even made rounds to table to clean and offer to bring rounds. I wonder how they keep this bar clean with every nook and cranny, but they do somehow. Lots of people around us groups of smiles playing cribbage or showing each other projects. Seems like the good times place despite quirks.
i use to come here after work i loved the atmosphere as well as the great food i miss this place alot

Paddy's Pub has great music, cosmos and ambiance.  The outside patio is perfect in the summer time and one of the few outside patio's in Milwaukee that offers outside entertainment.  I live in Austin, Texas during the majority of the year so one of the great summertime treats for me while I am in Milwaukee is enjoying your great weather with good friends.  Paddy's is the perfect place for that.  I have never taken a friend there, from Texas or Wisconsin, that doesn't just fall in love with it.  And the owners, Paddy and Woody, are as nice, consistently present and hospitable as any two owners could ever be.  Thanks to Paddy's Pub for such a class act place.  I would recommend it to anyone.

Few establishments achieve the respect and endearment that Milwaukeeans have for Paddy's pub. I don't know a fellow townie who doesn't have a soft spot and a good story for Paddys. IMO Paddys is the best Irish pub in town and probably one of the best bars, period. Even though it is a large establishment it can often feel crowded. But it's part of the crowdedness that gives Paddys such a homey feel. All the bars decorations were done by Woody, the bars owner, and are impressive. His selections for décor are a large part of what Paddys is. Two fireplaces in the main bar make Paddys a warm place in the cold Milwaukee winters. The leaf covered patio and statues give the sense of being in another place AND time. The non-smoking area upstairs is a welcome haven for some. The live Irish music is always good. And who doesn't love the M&Ms and peanuts? The smiling faces of Paddy and Woody make this bar a must visit if you're in town. Grab a pint of Guinness and a shot of Jamo. Enjoy the black and white movies playing on the wall. Make sure you expeience Paddys Pub. It's one of Milwaukees finest.
There's no place like home, and that home is Paddy's Pub.

My son and I come here quite a bit. In the 5th inning we came to get a table. We waited in their virtual line for AN HOUR. Finally went up to find out when we would get our table and they told us they decided to stop serving 30 minutes ago. I was furious! I asked when we're you going to tell me? The response. Oh we thought we sent you a text. Meanwhile the other vendors at the game have shut down. No offer to make it right. Just, I understand why you are upset. So frustrating.

We were excited to try the new restaurant after being fans of the old TGI Friday's. They really need to invest in some memorabilia for the walls. Really bland look. The loaded nachos were good but our burger was overdone and so it needed to be redone. The waitress was nice about it but the manager never came out to apologize. Overall with the time lost due to COVID I was hoping for better. I hope it improves

Absolutely the worst customer service I have ever received.... first off the hostess refused to seat meAnd my wife upstairs saying it's sunny and they are limiting the number of foot traffic on the stairs. When we did go upstairs it was basically no one upstairs.... The server took 15 minutes to come and even greet us... when he finally did we orders appetizers the food cane out first, the gave us the wrong order, and then they gave us the wrong appetizer... When we did get the right appetizer it had hair in it!!!Disgusting!!!!When we told them that we needed napkins and silverware he stated "for a burger" I absolutely refuse to do business here again and I will make sure everyone I know hears about this.... and when I asked for a manager they said they're not available to see me at this time.... I am appalled that there is customer service this horrible. And the food wasn't even good on top of that!

I have enjoyed this place, have have been here many, many times. However, over the past year the service has gone downhill quite a bit. One server in particular, Kayleigh has been awful. Unfortunately I have had her enough times to dread her coming to my table, and I finally got her name last time. She absolutely does not check on people (or at least us), no refills, new drink orders, nothing on the food and is INCREDIBLY RUDE. A) We would have spent more money on our visit, and B) I used to refer people here and bring out of town guests myself, as I live in the neighborhood. No more until it is fixed, and until Kayleigh undergoes some additional training or has an exit. Please fix this Benelux - I would love to be back there. Some of the servers are stellar, but clearly a baseline level of training needs to occur.

Yes, Cafe Benelux has a great beer and wine selection, no one can deny that. There's a catch however: you have to put up with lousy service and rude waitresses to get that beer or wine.  I was here last week with a group of friends it took us 15 minutes just to talk to our server. The food took over an hour to come out after we ordered. The excuse we kept hearing from the server was that the kitchen is too small with room for only two cooks. Also said one of the bartenders recently quit. Totally not the server's fault and we still gave a healthy tip, but come on! Build a bigger kitchen and hire another bartender! If people love your drinks and food, then as a restaurant owner you should be more than willing to make that investment. If you hate waiting, like I do, then this is not the place for you.

Went to this location with a large group a few months ago. When the food was being delivered, our waitress attempted to reach the plate over my head and hit me in the face with the plate. This resulted in immediate bleeding at the base of my nose and later bruising and swelling. After this happened, the waitress just said, "He turned into it," and walked away without apologizing. I figured a supervisor would come check on me, but no supervisor until I went and found one (after getting the bleeding to stop). The supervisor had me leave my information, and I figured a general manger would call me the following day and at least say sorry. Three days later, no call. Felt like they really didn't care they injured someone at their restaurant. And who reaches a plate over someone's head like that when they are looking the other way? At least say excuse me or something!

The menu and beer selection is great. The food was tasty, even though our experience was a NIGHTMARE and they didn't serve us some things as they were described in the menu.Let me be very clear: THE WHOLE NIGHT WAS SNAFU AFTER SNAFU AND IT WAS ALL THE FAULT OF THE MANAGER ON DUTY.Our server MAKAYLA was amazing and did her best to mitigate the screw-ups of the rest of the floor team and the poor management. First: they didn't have the beer I ordered nor the that of another in our party but took two trips back to the table to tell us both. The runner entered my drink in wrong and I was served the wrong beer. I didn't end up getting the right drink until well after our appetizer was served. Another person in our party did not get her drink until after me and they had what she wanted in stock. By this point we've been helped by 3 different people. We have also had 2 other people stop to ask if we ordered the food they were carrying around aimlessly.I ordered the 2lbs of mussels and fries. Mussels, fries and beer go together. My mussels came out a solid 15min or so before anyone else's food. My fries did not arrive until about 10min after even that. So I was without a crucial part of my meal experience for 25min, long enough for my mussels to cool down and detract greatly from the experience. They brought me a third pound of mussels with my order of two pounds, which I pointed out I did not order. They took the extra mussels after maybe 10 minutes then brought them back before the fries got there and said I could have them. There was a stark contrast in quality between that third pound and the first two, I speculate that the first pound had sat out under lamps for longer or something. Up to this point another 3 runners have stopped by our table to ask us if we ordered the food they were carrying. We were also delivered another incorrect drink.Next, when the rest of the party's food arrived, yet another runner was carrying the plates haphazardly and literally dumped a bowl of tomato soup onto the table which then splashed everywhere, into our drinks, onto our food, all over the table and worst, onto our clothes. The runner and server grabbed some handfuls of flimsy napkins, handed them to us and walked away for us to clean up ourselves after they made a few superficial swipes at the bulk of the mess. They left soup all over the table , see pics for the umbrella pole covered in it. Our drinks were ruined with tomato soup so I requested replacements to which they agreeably obliged, yet we didn't receive them until after 3 additional requests and well after our food was finished. The server MAKAYLA was extremely apologetic and was obviously mortified at the horrible performance of her management and team. She brought the manager up to us to address our experience. He immediately the all his staff under the bus when this is clearly a managerial issue. This man was not running his floor. He offered to reimburse us for dry-cleaning costs and a $30 comp on our $150(+tax and tip) cheque. We declined the dry-cleaning reimbursement as we don't live in the area. When our cheque arrived, we were charged for the replacement drinks and had to wait another 15min to clear that up. I am willing to give this place another shot despite all this because the atmosphere and food were good. We all have bad days, especially when the manager is not on his shit. I hope someone sees this and reprimands that manager, especially as he just threw his staff under the bus instead of taking responsibility for his poor management.

Review of Cafe Benelux:Cafe Benelux is a delightful spot that offers a cozy atmosphere and a menu filled with delicious options. During my recent visit, I had the pleasure of trying their Blood Orange Mule and Turkey Pesto Sandwich, and I must say, it was a fantastic culinary experience.Let's start with the Blood Orange Mule, a refreshing and unique twist on the classic cocktail. The combination of tangy blood orange and zesty ginger beer created a delightful burst of flavors that perfectly complemented the smooth vodka. It was a fantastic choice for a refreshing beverage, and I found myself ordering more than one throughout my meal.Moving on to the Turkey Pesto Sandwich, I was blown away by the fantastic combination of ingredients. The tender slices of turkey were perfectly paired with a generous spread of flavorful pesto, adding a delightful herbaceous touch. The sandwich was further elevated by the addition of fresh lettuce, juicy tomatoes, and creamy provolone cheese, all enclosed in a perfectly toasted bread. Each bite was a harmonious blend of textures and flavors, leaving me thoroughly satisfied.Aside from the outstanding food and beverages, Cafe Benelux also deserves praise for its charming ambiance. The cafe's cozy interior, with its warm lighting and comfortable seating, creates a welcoming and relaxed atmosphere. The staff members were friendly, attentive, and knowledgeable, adding to the overall enjoyable dining experience.In conclusion, if you find yourself in Cafe Benelux, don't miss out on the Blood Orange Mule and the Turkey Pesto Sandwich. These menu items showcase the cafe's commitment to quality ingredients and culinary expertise. With its inviting atmosphere and delicious offerings, Cafe Benelux is definitely worth a visit for anyone looking for a delightful meal in a cozy setting.
